The Krall Crags ( 77 ° 27′S 166 ° 49′E ) are two rock summits rising to over 1,400 metres ( 4,600 ft ) on the northwestern slope of Mount Erebus , Ross Island , Antarctica .
The Commonwealth Range is a north - south trending range of rugged mountains , 144 kilometres ( 89 mi ) long , located within the Queen Maud Mountains on the Dufek Coast of the continent of Antarctica .

Kelley Nunatak ( 85 ° 39′S 146 ° 44′W ) is a nunatak on the north side of Leverett Glacier in Antarctica , 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) northeast of Mount Gould .
Goreme Col ( Bulgarian : Горемска седловина , `` Goremska Sedlovina '' \go-'rem - ska se - dlo - vi-'na\ ) is the col of elevation 2700 m linking Doyran Heights to the east to Mount Mohl on the northeast side of Craddock Massif in Sentinel Range , Ellsworth Mountains in Antarctica .
Lizards Foot ( 77 ° 13′S 162 ° 52′E ) is a rocky spur forming the east end of the Saint Johns Range in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Frazier Islands are a group of three rocky islands - Nelly , Dewart and Charlton - in the eastern part of Vincennes Bay , East Antarctica , 15 km ( 9 mi ) west - north - west of Clark Peninsula , and 16 km offshore from Australia 's Casey Station .
McManus Glacier ( 69 ° 28′S 71 ° 27′W ) is a glacier flowing north into Palestrina Glacier , in northwestern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Cape Monakov ( 67 ° 9′S 48 ° 41′E ) is a cape on the west coast of Sakellari Peninsula , Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Gossard Channel ( 66 ° 5′S 101 ° 13′E ) is a narrow channel extending in an east -- west direction between the Mariner Islands and Booth Peninsula in the central portion of the Highjump Archipelago , Antarctica .
Guile Island ( 65 ° 44′S 65 ° 11′W ) is an island lying 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) southwest of Duchaylard Island , in the Biscoe Islands of Antarctica .
Mount Fidjeland ( 71 ° 42′S 25 ° 36′E ) is a mountain , 1,630 metres ( 5,350 ft ) high , standing close northeast of Mehaugen Hill on the west side of the mouth of Byrdbreen in the Sør Rondane Mountains of Antarctica .
Lettau Bluff ( 76 ° 57′S 167 ° 0′E ) is a rock and ice bluff that forms the central part of the western edge of Beaufort Island , and rises 200 metres ( 660 ft ) above the Ross Sea off Antarctica .
The Bermel Peninsula is a rugged , mountainous peninsula , approximately 15 mi ( 24 km ) long and 7 mi ( 11 km ) wide , located at 68 ° 27′S 65 ° 22′W between Solberg Inlet and Mobiloil Inlet on the Bowman Coast , Graham Land , Antarctica .
The Anckorn Nunataks ( 70 ° 14′S 63 ° 12′W ) are a group of nunataks and snow - covered hills , 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) long , between Mount Bailey and Mount Samsel in the eastern part of Palmer Land , Antarctica .

Johnson Bluff ( 84 ° 49′S 170 ° 31′E ) is a conspicuous rock bluff 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) east - northeast of Ranfurly Point , overlooking the east side of Keltie Glacier at its confluence with Beardmore Glacier , Antarctica .
Mount Leckie ( 70 ° 26′S 66 ° 0′E ) is a roughly circular outcrop about 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) east of Martin Massif in the Porthos Range , Prince Charles Mountains , Antarctica .

Mount Freeman ( 72 ° 43′S 168 ° 21′E ) is a prominent mountain , 2,880 metres ( 9,450 ft ) high , surmounting the base of Walker Ridge , 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) northwest of Mount Lepanto , in the Victory Mountains of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Grinder Island is one of the ice - covered islands in the Marshall Archipelago , located within the Sulzberger Ice Shelf off the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .

The Byrd Glacier is a major glacier in Antarctica , about 136 km long and 24 km wide , draining an extensive area of the polar plateau and flowing eastward between the Britannia Range and Churchill Mountains to discharge into the Ross Ice Shelf at Barne Inlet .

Knuckle Reef ( 67 ° 50′S 67 ° 22′W ) is a reef lying off Beacon Head , Horseshoe Island , Antarctica .

Mount Reina Sofía ( Spanish : Monte Reina Sofía ) is the mostly ice - free peak rising to 275 m on Hurd Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and surmounting Johnsons Glacier to the east and northeast , and the Spanish Antarctic base Juan Carlos Primero to the north - northwest .

Zalian ( Persian : زاليان‎ , also Romanized as Zālīān , Zāleyān , and Zālīyān ) is a village in Zalian Rural District , Zalian District , Shazand County , Markazi Province , Iran .

Tursunzoda ( Tajik : Турсунзода , also Tursunzade from Russian spelling ) is a city in western Tajikistan , known for its aluminium smelting plant TadAZ .

Cayo Santa María ( Cay or `` Key '' of Santa Maria ) is an island off Cuba 's north central coast in the Jardines del Rey archipelago .
Najjera , sometimes spelled as Najjeera is a location in Kira Municipality , Wakiso District , Central Uganda .
Vila Nova River is a river of Amapá state in Brazil .
The Fred Hollows Reserve is a local government -- administered reserve that is located in the eastern suburbs of Sydney , in the state of New South Wales , Australia .
Roche Jacques is a mountain in Alberta 's Rockies , Canada .
The 2013 European Short Course Swimming Championships took place in Herning , Denmark , from 12 - -15 December 2013 .
Churchill Park School is a co - ed primary and intermediate school in Glendowie , Auckland , New Zealand .

Chatrud District ( Persian : بخش چترود‎ ) is a district ( bakhsh ) in Kerman County , Kerman Province , Iran .
La Santísima Church is located 12 La Santísima Street at corner of Emiliano Zapata Street in the historic center of Mexico City .
Tikmah Ajam ( Persian : تيكمه عجم‎ , also Romanized as Tīkmah `` Ajam ) is a village in Qaleh Darrehsi Rural District , in the Central District of Maku County , West Azerbaijan Province , Iran . At the 2006 census , its population was 130 , in 30 families .
Al Rostamani Maze Tower is a skyscraper located along Sheikh Zayed Road in Dubai , United Arab Emirates .
The Adelaide Morning Chronicle was a newspaper published in Adelaide , South Australia during 1852 and 1853 .
Tresticklan National Park ( Swedish : Tresticklan nationalpark ) is located in the municipality of Dals - Ed in northwestern Dalsland , Sweden , along the Norwegian border .
The Amsterdam Pipe Museum ( formerly Dutch : Pijpenkabinet , `` pipe cabinet '' ) is a museum in Amsterdam , the Netherlands , dedicated to smoking pipes , tobacco , and related paraphernalia .
The Museo Nacional Centro de Arte Reina Sofía ( MNCARS , also called the Museo Reina Sofía , Queen Sofía Museum , El Reina Sofía , or simply The Sofia ) is Spain 's national museum of 20th - century art . The museum was officially inaugurated on September 10 , 1992 and is named for Queen Sofía .
Jugirkanda is a village in Otra Union or Wazirpur Upazila , Barisal District in Bangladesh .
The Voies Ferrées des Landes ( VFL ) was founded in 1916 from the merger of three short line railway companies in the Landes forest region of Gascony , France .
Johan Nygaardsvolds plass is a town square in Oslo , Norway .
UK Islamic Mission is an Islamic organization in the United Kingdom founded both to `` serve the Muslim community '' , and as `` an ideological movement '' to `` mould the entire human life according to Allah 's revealed Guidance '' .
Agios Georgios Lefkas ( Greek : Άγιος Γεώργιος Λεύκας ) is an abandoned village in the Nicosia District of Cyprus , and it lies within the UN Buffer Zone .
The World Trade Centre Montreal ( in French , Centre de Commerce mondial de Montréal ) is an office and hotel complex located in the Quartier international district of Montreal , Quebec , Canada .

The Contemporary Singers of Australia were a chamber choir based in Sydney , New South Wales , dedicated to the choral music of the 20th century .

Čepin ( Hungarian : Csepin ; German : Tschepin ) is a town and municipality in Osijek - Baranja County , Croatia .

Cerro Sechín ( also Sechín de las Estelas ) is an archaeological site in Casma Province of Ancash Region in northern Peru .

The Prodigal Son in the Brothel is a painting by the Dutch master Rembrandt .

Joking Apart is a BBC television sitcom written by Steven Moffat about the rise and fall of a relationship .
The New Shmoo is a 30-minute Saturday morning animated series based on the character from the Li'l Abner comic strip created by Al Capp , produced by Hanna - Barbera Productions and broadcast on NBC from September 22 , 1979 to November 15 , 1980 .

Lassie is a fictional female Rough Collie dog character created by Eric Knight in a short story that was later expanded to a full - length novel called Lassie Come - Home .
Big Train is a surreal British television comedy sketch show created by Arthur Mathews and Graham Linehan , writers of the successful sitcom Father Ted .

Louis - Alphonse de Valbelle ( 1640 - -1708 ) was a French Roman Catholic Bishop .

Fray Mocho died on 23 August 1903 , just 3 days short of his 45th birthday ; an illness that had troubled him for years eventually causing his death .

Johan Kievit ( 1627 - -1692 ) was an Orangist Rotterdam Regent , who may have been one of the instigators of the murder of former Grand Pensionary Johan de Witt , of the Dutch Republic , and his brother Cornelis de Witt on 20 August 1672 , together with his brother - in - law , Cornelis Tromp .

Joseph Barss ( 21 February 1776 -- 3 August 1824 ) was a sea captain of the schooner Liverpool Packet and was one of the most successful privateers on the North American Atlantic coast during the War of 1812 .
Jan Kjellström ( born 1940 , died 1967 ) was an orienteer from Sweden who played an important role in the development of the sport of orienteering in Great Britain .
Frieda Dänzer ( 16 November 1930 -- 21 January 2015 ) was a Swiss Alpine skier , successful in the second half of the 1950s .
Thomas Richardson Colledge ( 1796 -- 28 October 1879 ) was a Scottish surgeon with the East India Company at Guangzhou ( Canton ) who served part - time as the first medical missionary in China .

Thomas Augustine Hendrick ( 29 October 1849 at Penn Yan , New York , U.S.A. -- 29 November 1909 at Cebú , Philippines ) was an American Catholic priest ; he became the 22nd Bishop of Cebú , the first American to hold this position .
Thomas Weihs ( born 30 April 1914 Vienna ( then the Austro - Hungarian Empire ) , died 19 June 1983 Aberdeen , Scotland ) was a doctor , farmer and special needs educator , one of the founders and leading co - workers of the Camphill Movement and a pioneer of Anthroposophical curative education .

Margarida Cabral de Melo ( 1570 - -1631 ) was a Portuguese noble lady who settled with her husband and sons in Buenos Aires .

José Emilio Rabasa Estebanell ( 22 May 1856 -- 25 April 1930 ) was a prominent 19th century Mexican writer , diplomat and liberal politician .
Etta Wriedt ( 1859 - 1942 ) was an American direct voice medium .
Wolfgang Fischer ( 11 December 1888 -- 1 February 1943 ) was a German career military officer and panzer commander in World War II . He was killed on 1 February 1943 near Mareth in Tunisia when his staff car drove into a poorly marked Italian minefield and hit a land mine .
The Reverend Jacob Rutsen Hardenbergh , D.D. , S.T.D. , ( 22 February 1735/6 -- 30 October 1790 ) was an American Dutch Reformed clergyman , colonial and state legislator , and educator .

Kristen Feilberg or Christen Schjellerup Feilberg ( 1839 - -1919 ) was an early Danish photographer who is known mainly for his images captured far beyond the borders of Denmark .

Rafael Frontaura ( 7 February 1896 in Valparaiso - 15 August 1966 in Santiago ) was a Chilean actor who worked in both Chilean and Argentine cinema .

Benjamin Parry ( February 1634 -- 4 October 1678 ) was Church of Ireland Bishop of Ossory from 27 January 1678 until his death later the same year .

Jaan Eilart ( 24 June 1933 -- 18 May 2006 ) was an Estonian phytogeographer , landscape ecologist , cultural historian and conservationist .
Timothy L. Mounts ( died 1997 ) made significant contributions to the advancement of agriculture technology .
Luigi Villoresi ( 16 May 1909 -- 24 August 1997 ) was an Italian Grand Prix motor racing driver who continued racing on the Formula One circuit at the time of its inception .
The Rt . Hon . Christopher Palles , PC , QC ( 25 December 1831 -- 14 February 1920 ) , was an Irish barrister and perhaps the most eminent Irish judge of his time .

Lelio Cantoni ( 1802 , Gazzuolo , Dukedom of Mantua -- 1857 , Turin ) was an Italian rabbi .

George Cowell ( 1 November 1870 -- 27 April 1937 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Mary Mackellar ( née Cameron ; 1 October 1834 -- 7 September 1890 ) was a prominent Highland Scottish poet and Scottish Gaelic - English translator of the 19th century .

George Pettie ( 1548 - -1589 ) was an English writer of romances .

William Highett ( 1807 -- 29 November 1880 ) was a banker and politician in colonial Victoria , a member of the Victorian Legislative Council .
Andrew Eliot ( 1718 - 1778 ) was a prominent Boston Congregational minister of the New North Church ( now St. Stephen 's in the North End ) .
Powers Hapgood ( 1899 - -1949 ) was an American trade union organizer and Socialist Party leader known for his involvement with the United Mine Workers in the 1920s .
William Maule McDowell Webster ( 3 January 1885 -- 20 April 1958 ) was an Australian unionist and station agent .
Jean - Claude Chambellan Duplessis ( 1699 -- 1774 ) , called Duplessis père to distinguish him from his son , Jean - Claude - Thomas Chambellan Duplessis ( c. 1730 -- 1783 ) , was a goldsmith , sculptor and ceramics modeller , bronze - founder and decorative designer working in the Rococo manner .
Ras Shorty I ( 6 October 1941 -- 12 July 2000 ) , born Garfield Blackman and also known as Lord Shorty , was a Trinidadian calypso and soca musician , known as the Father of Soca and The Love Man .
Fairlie Harmar , Viscountess Harberton ( 1876 - -1945 ) was an English painter .
Leonard Krieger ( 1918 - -1990 ) was an American historian who paid particular attention to Modern Europe , particularly being known as an author on Germany .
Sir John Heathcoat - Amory , 3rd Baronet ( 2 May 1894 -- 22 November 1972 ) was an English cricketer .
Charles Campbell Worthington , or C.C. Worthington , ( January 1854 -- October 1944 ) was an American industrialist whose efforts were in part responsible for the foundation of the Professional Golfers Association .
Exupérien Mas , F.S.C. ( 7 June 1829 -- 31 January 1905 ) , was a French member of the Brothers of the Christian Schools .
Jacob S. Rogers ( born c1824 , died 2 July 1901 aged 77y ) was an American businessman .
Morris Robinson , 3rd Baron Rokeby ( 14 July 1757 -- May 1829 ) , was a British politician .
Bill Lever ( 20 April 1904 -- 25 September 1986 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Hutchins Williams , 1st Baronet ( c. 1700 -- 4 November 1758 ) born in London , England , to William Peere Williams and Anne Hutchins .
Jan Pieter van Bredael the Younger or Jan Peeter van Bredael the Younger ( 27 July 1683 -- 1735 ) was a Flemish painter known for his cavalry battle scenes and landscapes with genre scenes of village festivals and fairs .
Frank Vosper ( 15 December 1899 , in London -- 6 March 1937 ) was a British actor and playwright .
Holger Peter Roed , known as Holger Roed ( 2 November 1846 - 20 February 1874 ) , Danish painter , was born in Copenhagen to painter Jørgen Roed and wife Emilie Mathilde .

Fred Heintz ( 22 July 1913 -- 20 February 1942 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Naziha Salim ( Arabic : نزيهة سليم‎ , 1927 - -15 February 2008 ) was an Iraqi artist and painter , described by the country 's president , Jalal Talabani , as `` the first Iraqi woman who anchored the pillars of Iraqi contemporary art . Naziha Salim was born into a family of Iraqi artists living in Turkey .
Max Kalman ( 24 December 1884 , Russia - 14 June 1963 , Texas ) was a Jewish architect and attorney in Boston , Massachusetts in the early 1900s , most notable for designing the Vilna Shul synagogue on Beacon Hill , Boston in 1919 .
Istvan Rozanich ( 1912 - -1984 ) was a Hungarian poet and , while living in exile in Venezuela during the second half of his life , newspaper editor .
Charles L. Brainard ( 1903 - -1988 ) was active in preserving the papers of Dwight D. Eisenhower .
István Réti ( 26 December 1872 -- 17 January 1945 ) was a Hungarian painter , professor , art historian and leading member , as well as a founder and theoretician , of the Nagybánya artists ' colony , located in what is present - day Baia Mare , Romania .
Abdul Hamid Lahori ( died 1654 ) was a traveller and historian during the period of Shah Jahan who later became a court historian of Shah Jahan .
Georges Henein ( 1914 -- 1973 ) was an Egyptian surrealist author .
John Thornton Masser ( 24 June 1855 - 23 February 1929 ) was an organist and composer based in Nottingham .

Tora Teje ( 17 January 1893 -- 30 April 1970 ) was a Swedish theatre and silent film actress .

Florence Elsie Inman ( 5 December 1891 -- 31 May 1986 ) was a long serving member of the Canadian Senate .

Edward Cowey ( 9 April 1839 -- 16 December 1903 ) , often known as Ned Cowey , was a British trade unionist .
Terry Gill ( 25 October 1939 -- 25 February 2015 ) was an English Australian character actor , as well as theatre owner , producer , director and writer , he carved a nichè in Australian television playing police officers .
John Cecil Clavering OBE ( 17 April 1910 -- 6 October 2001 ) was an English architect , best known for his work designing Odeon Cinemas as part of Harry Weedon 's architectural practice in the 1930s , and his later work as the architect of the Public Record Office in Kew , London .
Louis Du Guernier ( 1677 - -1716 ) was an engraver .

Zvi Lurie ( Hebrew : צבי לוריא‎ , 1 June , 1906 -- 21 May 1968 ) was a Jewish political figure in Mandate Palestine .

Reverend Stephanus Jacobus du Toit ( 9 October 1847 -- 29 May 1911 ) was a controversial South African nationalist , theologian , journalist and failed politician .

Rudolph Beyer ( October 30 , 1889 -- February 1970 ) was an American bookkeeper , chemical and surgical glassblower and Socialist politician from Milwaukee , Wisconsin .

Hans Frankenthal ( July 15 , 1926 -- December 22 , 1999 ) was a German Jew who was deported to the Auschwitz concentration camp in occupied Poland in 1943 .
Carl Degenkolb ( 1796 - 1862 ) was a German industrialist , who is generally understood to have pioneered the first codetermination plans in his factories , as well as participating in drafting the first codetermination law during the failed 1848 Revolutions .
Henry Wickham Wickham ( 1800 -- 23 September 1867 ) was British Conservative party politician .
Count Karl Wilhelm von Toll ( Russian : Карл Вильгельм Фёдорович Толль ; 9 April 1777 , Keskvere , Governorate of Estonia - 5 May 1842 ) was a Baltic German aristocrat and Russian subject who served in the Imperial Russian Army in the campaigns against the Napoleonic Army .
Adeline Oppenheim Guimard ( 1872 -- 1960 ) was an American painter noted for her portraits in gouache and colored crayons .
Arnold Armitage ( 1899 - -1991 ) was a British - born artist and illustrator , best known for his work with pin - up art . He moved to the United States around 1925 and settled in Hollywood , California , working for the Foster and Kleiser Company , which produced billboards .
Alfred Oscar Elzner ( 1862 - -1933 ) was a prominent American architect in Cincinnati , Ohio .
Bungaree , or Boongaree , ( 1775 -- 24 November 1830 ) was an Aboriginal Australian from the Broken Bay area , who was known as an explorer , entertainer , and Aboriginal community leader .
Thomas Dudley ( 12 October 1576 -- 31 July 1653 ) was a colonial magistrate who served several terms as governor of the Massachusetts Bay Colony .
Lucas Sithole ( 1931 - 1994 ) was a South African sculptor best known for his work in mainly indigenous woods , as well as for his sculptures in bronze , stone and other media .
Yvonne McKague Housser ( 1898 - -1996 ) , Canadian painter and teacher .
Edward Pritchard Martin ( 20 January 1844 Dowlais - 25 September 1910 Harrogate ) was a British engineer , and steel maker .
Frank Raubicheck ( 1857 - -1952 ) was an American painter and etcher who arrived in the United States from Bohemia in the 1870s .
Thomas Arnold Harvey ( known as Arnold ; born 17 April 1878 in Marsh 's Library , Dublin , Ireland ; died 25 December 1966 in Dublin ) was an Irish cricketer and Rugby Union player .
Olav Sandvik ( 2 November 1925 -- 16 February 2010 ) was a Norwegian veterinarian and civil servant .
The Honourable William Cust ( 23 January 1787 -- 3 March 1845 ) , was a British barrister and Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
Marie Louise Habets ( January 1905-May 1986 ) was a Belgian nurse and former religious sister whose life was fictionalised as Sister Luke ( Gabrielle van der Mal ) in The Nun 's Story , a bestselling 1956 book by American author Kathryn Hulme .
Frank Coulton ( February 1862 -- 1929 ) was an English footballer who played in The Football League for Aston Villa .
John Romney ( June 1785 -- 1 February 1863 ) was an English artist in printmaking and watercolour who lived and worked in London and Chester .
Gheorghe Apostoleanu ( 1832 - 1895 ) was a Romanian politician and jurist who served as the acting Minister of Justice from March 30 , 1860 until April 30 , 1860 .
Mary Knight Wood Mason ( 17 April 1857 -- 20 December 1944 ) was an American pianist , music educator and composer .
Geneviève Behrend ( 1881 in Paris -- 1960 in United States ) was a French - born author and teacher of Mental Science , a New Thought discipline created by Thomas Troward .
Henry Hampton ( 8 January 1940 -- 22 November 1998 ) was an American filmmaker .
Peter Füri ( 9 October 1937 -- 11 May 2015 ) was a Swiss football player and manager , who played during the 1950s and 1960s .
Delia Murphy Kiernan ( 16 February 1902 -- 11 February 1971 ) was a singer and collector of Irish ballads .
Mona Vasquez ( 1960 -- 2 September 2011 ) was a former Scientologist who was active in Scientology 's headquarters in Europe , in Copenhagen , in the 1980s .
Carl Heinrich Schnauffer ( 4 July 1823 Heimsheim - 4 September 1854 Baltimore , Maryland ) was a poet , soldier and editor .
Rosina Ferrara ( 1861 - -1934 ) was an Italian girl from the island of Capri , who became the favorite muse of American expatriate artist John Singer Sargent .
John William Beatty ( 1869 - -1941 ) was a Canadian painter who was a forerunner in the movement which became the Group of Seven in 1920 .
The Reverend William Lubbock MA BD ( Cantab ) ( baptized North Walsham , Norfolk , 17 January 1701 , died North Walsham 20 April 1754 ) was an English divine , Fellow of Caius College , Cambridge , and Church of England clergyman .
Maryon Lane ( 15 February 1931 -- 13 June 2008 ) was a South African ballet dancer who became well known in England as a ballerina of the Sadler 's Wells Theatre Ballet and as a soloist with the Royal Ballet .
Francis Annesley , 1st Earl Annesley ( 27 November 1740 - 19 December 1802 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and peer .
Wilhelm Grube ( Chinese : 葛祿博 ; pinyin : Gé Lùbó ) ( 17 August 1855 -- 2 July 1908 ) was a German sinologist and ethnographer .
General José Ignacio de Gorriti ( 1770 -- 9 November 1835 ) was an Argentine statesman , soldier and lawyer .
Mary Boomer Page ( ? - December 3 , 1927 ) of Chicago , Illinois was director of the Gertrude House settlement and president of the Kindergarten Literature Company .
Ettore Tavernari ( 6 January 1905 - 1981 ) was an Italian athlete who competed mainly in the 400 metres and 800 metres .
Robert Baudin ( 1918 - -1983 ) was a counterfeiter , conman and aerial photographer .
Tama Kurokawa , Lady Arnold ( 1869 - 1962 ) was the third wife of Sir Edwin Arnold .
Maureen Mollie Hunter McIlwraith , more commonly known as Mollie Hunter ( 30 June 1922 -- 31 July 2012 ) was a Scottish writer .
Cristóvão da Costa or Cristóbal Acosta and Latinized as Christophorus Acosta Africanus ( c. 1525 -- c. 1594 ) was a Portuguese doctor and natural historian .
Vicente Acero y Arebo ( c. 1675/1680 -- 1739 ) was a Spanish Baroque architect whose contributed significantly to the design and construction of the cathedrals of Granada , Guadix , Cádiz , and Málaga .
Wu Mingche ( 吳明徹 ) ( 512 - -578 ) , courtesy name Tongzhao ( 通昭 ) , was a general of the Chinese dynasty Chen Dynasty .
Kadri Gjata ( 1865 - -1912 ) was an Albanian patriot , writer and educator .
Margaret Bernadine Hall ( 1863 -- 2 January 1910 ) was an English painter who spent most of her career in Paris .
Mervyn Burtch MBE ( 7 November 1929 -- 12 May 2015 ) was a Welsh composer , best known for his work with children 's music projects .
Friedrich - Erdmann von Hake ( 14 August 1898 -- 22 March 1982 ) was a highly decorated Oberst in the Wehrmacht during World War II who commanded the 13 .
Pola Weiss Álvarez ( born , died Mexico City ; 1947- 1990 ) was a Mexican independent television producer , scholar , and video and performance artist known as a pioneer in video art in Latin America .
William Brockie ( 1811 - -1890 ) was a 19th - century Scottish born writer , newspaper editor , poet and songwriter who lived for many years in Sunderland .
Frank Harris Patterson ( 1890 -- 1976 ) was a Nova Scotian lawyer , jurist and historian .
Duke Ligong of Qin ( Chinese : 秦厲共公 ; pinyin : Qín Lìgòng Gōng , died 443 BC ) was from 476 to 443 BC the 22nd ruler of the Zhou Dynasty Chinese state of Qin that eventually united China to become the Qin Dynasty .
Carel Hendrik Bartels ( 29 September 1792 -- 10 February 1850 ) was the wealthiest and most important mulatto trader and businessman on the Dutch Gold Coast in the second quarter of the nineteenth century .
Charles Guillaume Alexandre Bourgeois ( 16 December 1759 -- 7 May 1832 ) was a French physicist and painter .
Doloris Bridges ( ca . 1916 -- January 16 , 1969 ) , widow of 25-year U.S. Senator H. Styles Bridges , was the first woman to seek election to the U.S. Senate from New Hampshire .
Zacarías Yanzi ( February 1801 - August 1888 ) was an Argentine soldier and politician who participated in the war of independence and served briefly as Governor of San Juan Province .
General Sir John Murray , 8th Baronet , GCH ( c.1768 -- 15 October 1827 ) led a brigade under Arthur Wellesley , 1st Duke of Wellington in the Peninsular War .
Russell Lant Carpenter ( December 17 , 1816 -- 1892 ) , a Unitarian minister who carried on the works of his father , Dr. Lant Carpenter and wrote his biography .
Frederick Whittaker Dixon ( 1854 - -1935 ) was an architect practising in Oldham , Lancashire .
Mark Colton ( 17 March 1961 -- 5 August 1995 ) was a British racing driver and software author .
Rūsiņš Mārtiņš Freivalds ( 10 November 1942 -- 4 January 2016 ) was a Latvian computer scientist and mathematician .
Paulus van de Perre ( Middelburg ? , 1598 ? -- London , 14 December 1653 ) was a Dutch politician and diplomat .
Thomas Weaver ( 1773 - -1855 ) was an English mining engineer and geologist .
Jacob van Reesbroeck or Jacob van Rysbroeck ( c. 6 December 1620 -- 27 February 1704 ) was a Flemish portrait painter and engraver from Antwerp whose patrons included prominent local families as well as foreign aristocrats and monarchs .
Lieutenant Colonel Mahmood Khan Durrani , GC ( 1914 - -1995 ) was a South Asian recipient of the George Cross , awarded for acts of the greatest heroism or of the most conspicuous courage in circumstances of extreme danger .
Emil Fick ( 18 July 1863 -- 20 February 1930 ) was Swedish fencer .
Vuko Vukadinović ( Serbian : Вуко Вукадиновић ) ( 11 August 1937 -- 3 November 1993 ) was a member of the League of Communists of Montenegro and the President of the Executive Council of the Socialist Republic of Montenegro from 1986 - -1989 .
Benedetto Justiniani ( 1550 -- 19 December 1622 ) was a Jesuit theologian and Biblical writer from Genoa , in what is today Italy .
Alfred Newman Gilbey ( 1901 - -1998 ) was a British Roman Catholic priest and monsignor .
Ælfwaru ( died 27 February 1007 ) was an Anglo - Saxon noblewoman , who bequeathed her lands to churches such as Ely , and Ramsey .
Zlatomir Obradov ( 25 January 1941 -- 24 April 2013 ) was a Croatian footballer during the 60s of the 20th century and later coach .
Peter Gladstone ( 16 October 1928 -- 25 July 2000 ) was a British naturalist and wildfowl expert .
Joseph Henry Chesterton ( c.1840 -- 26 January 1883 ) was a plant collector who was sent by James Veitch & Sons to search for orchids in South America with much success .
Alexander Bedward ( born 1848 in St. Andrew , a rural parish north of Kingston , Jamaica - died 1930 ) was the founder of Bedwardism .
Ibtihal Salem ( 1949 -- 15 August 2015 ) was an Egyptian short story writer , novelist and translator .
George Michael Singleton CBE MC ( 12 May 1913 - -11 December 2002 ) was an English cricketer who played three first - class games , appearing once for Cambridge University and twice for Worcestershire .
John Troutbeck ( 12 November 1832 , Blencowe , Cumberland -- 11 October 1899 , London ) was a Minor Canon of Westminster Abbey and Chaplain in Ordinary to Queen Victoria whose renown rests on his translation of various continental choral texts including the major works of Bach .
Maurice Vidal Portman ( 21 March 1860 in London , Ontario , Canada - 14 February 1935 in Axbridge , Somerset , UK ) was a British naval officer , who is best known for his documentation and pacification of several Andamanese tribes between 1879 and 1901 .
John Giles Eccardt ( 1720 - -1779 ) was a German - born British portrait painter .
J. A. François Héraly ( 1856 -- between 20 and 22 July 1920 ) was a Canadian clarinetist , bandmaster , and music educator of Belgian birth .
Mohamed Sibari ( 1945 -- 28 November 2013 ) was a Moroccan poet , novelist and translator .
William Jowett ( 1787 -- 20 February 1855 ) was a missionary and author , in 1813 becoming the first Anglican clergyman to volunteer for the overseas service of the Church Missionary Society .
Lawrence Alexander Sidney Johnson , ( 26 June 1925 -- 1 August 1997 ) known as Lawrie Johnson , was an Australian taxonomic botanist .
Annette Worsley - Taylor MBE ( 2 July 1944 -- 24 August 2015 ) founded London Fashion Week .
Johann Karl Simon Morgenstern ( 28 August ( O.S. 17 August ) 1770 -- 15 September ( O.S. 3 September ) 1852 ) was a German philologist in Livonia , the first director of the library of the Imperial University of Dorpat .
Yeung Hok - ling ( 楊鶴齡 ) ( 1868 - 29 August 1934 ) , courtesy name Lai - ha ( 禮遐 ) , was a Chinese revolutionary from Cuiheng Village , Heungshan , Kwangtung .
Joseph Beaulieu ( 21 May 1895 -- 1 October 1965 ) was a Canadian composer , folklorist , and music educator .
Richard le Scrope , 1st Baron Scrope of Bolton ( c. 1327 -- 1403 ) was an English soldier and courtier , serving Richard II of England .
Vasile Zavoda , known as Zavoda II or Tigrul Akbar ( 26 July 1929 -- 14 July 2014 ) , was a Romanian football player .
Lawrence York Spear ( 23 October 1870 - -9 September 1950 ) was an American naval officer and businessman who spent the majority of his career working for the Electric Boat Company .
Eldred Pottinger ( 12 August 1811 -- 15 November 1843 ) was an Anglo - Indian army officer and diplomat .
Bruce Charles Savage ( 30 July 1906 -- 4 February 1993 ) was the United States Public Housing Administration Commissioner under President Dwight D. Eisenhower , serving from 1960 to 1961 .
Charles Eric Corbett ( 6 October 1917 - 6 April 2002 ) was a clergyman in the Church of England , who was Archdeacon of Liverpool from 1970 to 1979 .
Qamar Jalalabadi , also known as Qamar Jalabadi ( 1919 -- 9 January 2003 ) , was an Indian poet and lyricist of songs of Hindi movies .
Klauss Vianna ( Belo Horizonte , 1928 -- São Paulo , 1992 ) was a Brazilian dancer , choreographer and theater director .
Louisa Bassano ( 19 February 1818 -- 20 August 1908 ) was an English opera singer .
Hans Schaffner ( 16 December 1908 in Interlaken -- 26 November 2004 ) was a Swiss politician and member of the Swiss Federal Council ( 1961 - -1970 ) .
Ellis Price or Prys ( by 1514 - 8 October 1594 ) was a Welsh administrator and MP .
Princess Li Jingshou ( 李敬受 ) ( died 437 ? ) was a princess of the Chinese / Xiongnu state Northern Liang .
Craig Luebben ( 20 March 1960 -- 9 August 2009 ) was an American rock climber and author .
Colonel Peter Beckford ( 1643 - -1710 ) was acting Governor of Jamaica in 1702 .
George Linnaeus Banks ( 2 March 1821 -- 3 May 1881 ) , husband of author Isabella Banks , was a British journalist , editor , poet , playwright , amateur actor , orator , and Methodist .
Frank Chapple , Baron Chapple of Hoxton ( 8 August 1921 -- 19 October 2004 ) was general secretary of the Electrical , Electronic , Telecommunications and Plumbing Union ( EETPU ) , a leading British trade union .
Antonio Aguilar Barraza ( 17 May 1919 -- 19 June 2007 ) was a Mexican singer , songwriter , film actor , film producer , and screenwriter .
Raja Rajeswara Sethupathi ( Tamil : ராஜ ராஜேஸ்வர சேதுபதி ) or Muthuramalinga Sethupathy ( 3 June 1889 - 1929 ) was the Raja of Ramnad from 1903 to 1929 .
Richard Capel ( 1586 - -1656 ) was an English nonconforming clergyman of Calvinist views , a member of the Westminster Assembly , and for a period of his life a practicing physician .
Nicolas Chevalier , Baron de Grissé ( 1562 - -1630 ) was first president of the Cour des aides in Paris from 20 April 1610 , as well as Councillor of State , superintendent of Navarre and Béarn , and twice ambassador to England .
William Jardine Gresson ( 1869 -- 10 January 1934 ) was a British merchant and politician in Hong Kong and China .
Tomm Murstad ( 2 July 1915 -- 19 January 2001 ) was a Norwegian skier , coach and businessperson .
Charles Gosse ( 26 December 1849 -- 1 July 1885 ) was a surgeon in the early days of the colony of South Australia .
David Ablett ( 4 February 1941 -- 24 July 2010 ) was a Canadian journalist and editor for The Vancouver Sun , the Toronto Star , and other media .
Pawnee Bill ( February 14 , 1860 -- February 3 , 1942 ) , born Gordon William Lillie , was an American showman and performer who specialized in Wild West shows and was known for his short partnership with Buffalo Bill .
Pandit Madhusudan Gupta ( Bengali : মধুসূদন গুপ্ত ) ( 1800 -- 15 November 1856 ) was an Indian doctor and the first Indian trained in Western medicine to dissect a human corpse .
Simon Tortell ( 8 August 1959 -- 15 June 2012 ) was a Maltese footballer .
Sir Richard Kennedy , 2nd Baronet , of Newtownmountkennedy ( c.1615 - 1685 ) was an Irish politician , landowner and judge who held the office of Baron of the Court of Exchequer ( Ireland ) .
Murdo Macfarlane ( 15 Feb 1901 - 1982 ) ( Gaelic : Murchadh MacPhàrlain ) known as ' Bàrd Mhealboist ' ( the Melbost Bard ) he was a published poet and campaigner for Scottish Gaelic , especially during the 1970s , when the ceartas movement was gaining strength .
Eduard Locher ( 15 January 1840 in Zurich -- 2 June 1910 in Zurich ) was a Swiss engineer , inventor and independent contractor who received a doctorate honoris causa for his work .
Sir Edward Herbert Bunbury , 9th Baronet ( 8 July 1811 -- 5 March 1895 ) , known as Edward Bunbury until 1886 , was a British Liberal Party politician .
Sigeberht the Little was king of Essex from 617 to 653 .
Jim Fargie ( 30 October 1886 -- 18 June 1960 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Alessandro Molinari ( 1898 -- 1962 ) was the first General Director of ISTAT , which was then known as the National Institute of Technology , in Fascist Italy .
Bogdan Gavrilović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Богдан Гавриловић ) ( 1864 - -1947 ) was a Serbian mathematician , physicist , philosopher , and educator .
Raoul Gradis ( 15 June 1861 -- 18 June 1943 ) was a French painter , composer and shipowner .
Vojo Dimitrijević ( Sarajevo 20 May 1910 - 12 August 1980 , Sarajevo ) was one of the most notable Yugoslav painters .
Lord Charles Spencer PC ( 31 March 1740 -- 16 June 1820 ) was a British politician and courtier from the Spencer family .
Myrtle Solomon ( 9 June 1921 -- 22 April 1987 ) was an active pacifist .
Jean Salmon Macrin ( 1490 -- 20 October 1557 ) was a Neo - Latin poet of French nationality .
Richard Malone , 1st Baron Sunderlin ( c.1738 -- 14 April 1816 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and peer .
Edgar Stanton Davidson ( May 17 , 1897 to November 1 , 1984 ) was born in Wellsville , Ohio which is in Yellow Creek Township , Columbiana County , Ohio .
Denis Robert Pack - Beresford OBE ( 1864 - -1942 ) was an Irish entomologist and arachnologist .
Edward Waterson ( ? ? -- 7 January 1594 ( NS ) ) was an English Catholic priest and martyr .
Theophilus Dillingham ( 1613 - -1678 ) was an English churchman and academic , Master of Clare Hall , Cambridge and Archdeacon of Bedford .
Rev John Sutherland Black FRSE LLD ( 1846 - -1923 ) was a Scottish biblical scholar and contributor to the Encyclopedia Britannica and Dictionary of National Biography .
Gottfried Ephraim Scheibel ( 1696 - -1759 ) was a German theologian and writer about music .
George C. Griffin ( 1897 - -1990 ) served in various positions at his alma mater , the Georgia Institute of Technology , most notably as Dean of Men from 1946 to 1964 .
The Rev. Joseph Jackson Fuller ( 1825 - -1908 ) , Baptist missionary to the pre - colonial African Chiefdoms of the Cameroons , was one of the earliest slaves to be freed in Jamaica ( initially under the partial freedoms of the `` apprenticeship act '' ) who went on to become well - educated and travel internationally .
Hans Bull Brodtkorb Mohr ( 26 September 1886 -- 29 January 1973 ) was a Norwegian educator and international cooperation activist .
Theodorus Willem van Lidth de Jeude ( 1 February 1853 -- 29 May 1937 ) was a Dutch zoologist and herpetologist .
Joseph Ndandarika ( c. 1941 -- May 1991 ) was a Zimbabwean sculptor known for his figurative works .
Hugh IV , Count of Rethel ( 1244 - 1285 ) was a son of Manasses V and his wife , Elisabeth of Écry .
Enver Ahmed ( 1909 - -1992 ) , pen name Ahmed , was an Indian cartoonist and creator of Chandu , the turbanned , paunchy central character of a popular cartoon strip in the Hindustan Times .
Henry Spencer , 1st Earl of Sunderland , 3rd Baron Spencer of Wormleighton ( c. 23 November 1620 -- 20 September 1643 ) , known as The Lord Spencer between 1636 and June 1643 , was an English peer from the Spencer family who fought and died in the English civil war on the side of the Cavaliers .
Robert Percy Smith , known as `` Bobus '' Smith ( 7 May 1770 -- 10 March 1845 ) , was a British lawyer , Member of Parliament , and Judge Advocate - General of Bengal , India .
Robert Dorsay ( 16 August 1904 -- 29 October 1943 ) was a German actor , dancer , and singer .
Geoff Twentyman ( 19 January 1930 -- 16 February 2004 ) was an English footballer who is mainly remembered for his links with Liverpool Football Club as both a player and as chief scout .
James Relly ( c.1722 -- 25 April 1778 ) was a Welshman , Methodist minister and mentor of John Murray who spread Universalism in the United States .
Knut - Olaf Haustein ( 20 September 1934 -- 10 February 2006 ) was a German physician best known for his work studying the effects of tobacco smoking .
Jacob Valero ( 1813 - -1874 ) was the founder of the first private bank in Palestine , Jacob Valero & Company .
William Aleyn ( fl . 1430 - -1448 ) was a 15th - century English pirate .
Mulla Morad ibn Ali Khan Tafreshi ( 1549 - 1641 CE ) was a theologian , man of wisdom and jurist during the Safavid period .
Pendyala Nageswara Rao ( Telugu : పెండ్యాల నాగేశ్వరరావు ) ( 6 March 1917 -- 31 August 1984 ) was a popular drama actor , singer and music director in Telugu Film Industry for over 25 years from early 1950s to late 1970s .
Nina Kulagina , Ninel Sergeyevna Kulagina ( Russian : Нине́ль Серге́евна Кула́гина ) ( aka Nelya Mikhailova ) ( 30 July 1926 -- April 1990 ) was a Russian woman who claimed to have psychic powers , particularly in psychokinesis .
Martha Magee ( c. 1755 - 1846 ) was a philanthropist and a co - founder and the namesake of Magee College in Ireland .
Josef Velek , ing . ( Master of Art , Technology ) ( November 30 , 1939-April 30 , 1990 ) was a Czechoslovak ( Czech ) journalist , author and environmentalist .
Barbara George ( 16 August 1942 -- 10 August 2006 ) was an American R&B singer and songwriter .
Thomas Coggeshall ( died 1402 ) , of New Hall in Boreham , Great Baddow and Sandon , Essex , was an English politician .
Edward Winslow ( 1595 -- 1655 ) was a Separatist who traveled on the Mayflower in 1620 .
Philippe Le Sueur Mourant ( 1848 -- 21 August 1918 ) was a Jersey writer who wrote in Jèrriais and French .
Vice - Admiral Thomas Butler , 6th Earl of Ossory , KG , PC , PC(I ) ( 8 July 1634 -- 30 July 1680 ) was an Irish politician .
Ferdinando Fairfax ( born in 1766 at Shannon Hill , Jefferson County , Virginia ( now West Virginia ) ; died on 24 September 1820 at Mount Eagle , Fairfax County , Virginia ) was a Virginia landowner and member of the prominent Fairfax family .
Harry Ainsworth ( 1887 or 1888 - -4 August 1965 ) was a British newspaper editor .
Otto Zuckerkandl ( 28 December 1861 , Raab - 1 July 1921 , Vienna ) was an Austrian urologist and surgeon .
Giovanni Baldelli ( 1914 - -1986 ) was an anarchist theorist , best known for his 1971 work Social Anarchism which defines social anarchism and provides a framework for its introduction .
Carlo Bonavia ( died 1788 ) was an Italian painter known for idyllic landscape paintings , engravings and drawings .
Sigurd Jonsson ( 1390s -- December 1452 ) was a Norwegian nobleman , knight and the supreme leader of Norway during two interregnums in the mid-15th century .
John `` Jack '' Rackham ( 26 December 1682 -- 18 November 1720 ) , commonly known as Calico Jack , was an English pirate captain operating in the Bahamas and in Cuba during the early 18th century .
Nina Hunt ( 1932 - -1995 ) was a Manx Latin American dance coach and choreographer .
Captain Federico Caprilli ( 8 April 1868 - 6 December 1907 ) was an Italian cavalry officer and equestrian who revolutionized the jumping seat .
Andrey Chokhov , also spelled Chekhov ( Андрей Чохов ( Чехов ) in Russian ) ( c. 1545 -- 1629 , Moscow ) was one of the most prominent Russian casters .
Kenneth Norman Bell ( 1884 -- 1951 ) was a fellow of Balliol College , Oxford from 1914 to his death in 1951 .
Emily Quihampton ( 19 July 1834 -- 29 March 1909 ) was a 19th - century outdoor enthusiast who was the first woman to climb Mont Blanc and Monte Rosa in the same week .
Michael George ( 18 December 1888 -- 10 June 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Zvi Yehuda Kook ( Hebrew : צבי יהודה קוק‎ , born 23 April 1891 , died 9 March 1982 ) was a rabbi , leader of Religious Zionism and Rosh Yeshiva of the Mercaz HaRav yeshiva .
Daniel Kinnear Clark ( 17 July 1822 -- 22 January 1896 ) was a Scottish consulting railway engineer .
Nancy Dawson was the stage name of Ann Newton ( c.1728 - 1767 ) , a famous London dancer and actress .
John Howison ( or Howisone , Howisoune , or Howieson , c. 1530 -- 1618 ) was Minister in the Parish of Cambuslang during a turbulent time in Scotland 's history .
Charles Armitage Brown ( 14 April 1787 -- 5 June 1842 ) was a very close friend of the poet John Keats , as well as being a friend of artist Joseph Severn , Leigh Hunt , Thomas Jefferson Hogg , Walter Savage Landor and Edward John Trelawny .
Sir Worthington Laming Worthington - Evans , 1st Baronet GBE PC ( 23 August 1868 -- 14 February 1931 ) was a British Conservative politician .
Berto Pisano ( 13 October 1928 -- 29 January 2002 ) was an Italian composer , conductor , arranger and jazz musician .
John Henry Davies ( born c. 1864 , died 24 October 1927 ) was a wealthy brewery owner who in 1902 took over the English football club Manchester United , which was then called Newton Heath .
Sir Henry Oxenden , 1st Baronet ( 1614 - -1686 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1645 and 1660 .
Regina Seiden ( 4 July 1897- 11 January 1991 ) was a Jewish Canadian Woman painter who was an early member of the Beaver Hall Group .
Adam Houghton ( died 13 February 1389 ) , also known as Adam de Houghton , was Bishop of St David 's from 1361 until his death and Lord Chancellor of England from 1377 to 1378 .
Thomas Malton , the elder ( 1726 - -1801 ) was an English architectural draughtsman and writer on geometry .
Arthur Mervyn Stockwood ( 27 May 1913 -- 13 January 1995 ) was the Anglican Bishop of Southwark from 1959 to 1980 .
William Henry Pratt ( 23 November 1887 -- 2 February 1969 ) , better known by his stage name Boris Karloff , was an English actor .
Sat Mahajan ( 27 July 1927 -- 1 September 2012 ) was the Rural Development Minister of the Indian state of Himachal Pradesh .
Herbert Desmond Carter ( 15 June 1895 -- 3 February 1939 ) was a British lyricist who worked with George and Ira Gershwin , Ivor Novello , and others , and also wrote one of the first English language versions of the notorious `` suicide song '' , `` Gloomy Sunday '' .
Admiral Sir George Cranfield Berkeley GCB ( 10 August 1753 -- 25 February 1818 ) , often known as George Berkeley , was a highly experienced , popular , yet controversial naval officer and politician in late eighteenth and early nineteenth century Britain .
Sinibaldo Scorza ( 16 July 1589 -- 5 April 1631 ) was an Italian painter , draughtsman and etcher .
Vernon Andrade ( April 24 , 1902 , Panama -- February 8 , 1966 , New York City ) was an American jazz bandleader active primarily in New York City in the 1920s and 1930s .
Sophia Maria Westenholz , née Fritscher ( 1759 - 1838 ) was a German composer , musician , singer and music educator .
Sebastião Alba ( 11 March 1940 -- 14 October 2000 ) was a Portuguese poet , born in Braga who lived a long period of his life in former Portuguese colony Mozambique .
Thomas Chaundler ( 1418 - -1490 ) was an English playwright and illustrator .
Robert James Graves , F.R.C.S. ( 27 March 1796 -- 20 March 1853 ) was an eminent Irish surgeon after whom Graves ' disease takes its name .
Julius Beerbohm ( 1854 -- April 1906 ) was a Victorian travel - writer , engineer and explorer .
Rajah Tupas ( baptized as Felipé Tupás , c. 1497 -- c. 1565 ) was the last Rajah of Cebu in the Pre - Hispanic Philippines .
Erik Tengström ( 1913 - -1996 ) , Swedish astronomer and geodesist .
Yun Chi - oh ( Korean:윤치오 , Hanja:尹致旿 ; born 5 August 1869 ; died 22 December 1950 ) was a Korean educator and politician .
John Lee Lee ( 11 December 1802 -- 16 August 1874 ) of Orleigh Court in the parish of Buckland Brewer in Devon , and of Dillington House , near Ilminster in Somerset , was a British Tory politician who was Member of Parliament for Wells in Somerset between 1830 and 1837 .
Homer Baker ( June 8 , 1893 - November 25 , 1977 ) was an American , middle - distance track and field athlete .
Dhammalok Mahasthavir ( Devanagari : धम्मालोक महास्थविर ) ( born Das Ratna Tuladhar ) ( 16 January 1890 -- 17 October 1966 ) was a Nepalese Buddhist monk who worked to revive Theravada Buddhism in Nepal in the 1930s and 1940s .
Rafael Valek Moure ( 18 December 1932 -- 17 June 2013 ) was a Colombian footballer who played professionally in the Colombian Professional Football League , Serie A and Mexican Primera División .
Florindo Ferrario ( 25 January 1897 -- 30 May 1960 ) was an Argentine film , stage and radio actor .
Sir Nathaniel Napier , 2nd Baronet ( 1636 - -1709 ) was an English politician , known also as a traveller and dilettante .
Joseph Allan McIver ( 17 January 1904 -- 15 June 1969 ) was a Canadian composer , arranger , pianist , and conductor .
Martin Desjardins , born Martin van den Bogaert ( 1637 -- 2 May 1694 ) was a French sculptor and stuccoist of Dutch birth .
Abisin Abbas ( ( aˈbisɪn aˈbas ) ; 26 February 1902 -- 20 October 1961 ) , better known by his pseudonym Andjar Asmara ( ( anˈdʒar asˈmara ) ) , was a dramatist and filmmaker active in the cinema of the Dutch East Indies .
Fritz Arthur Jusélius ( 13 June 1855 Pori -- 8 February 1930 ) was a Finnish industrialist and a member of parliament .
Cristino García Granda ( Gozón , 1914 - -1946 ) was a fighter with the French Resistance in France during World War II . He was born in Asturias , Spain and also died in Spain .
Muzaffar al - Din Jahan Shah ibn Yusuf ( 1397 in Khoy -- 1467 in Tabriz ) ( Persian : جهان شاه‎‎ ; Azerbaijani : Cahan Şah/جهان شاه ) was the leader of the Kara Koyunlu oghuz Turks tribal federation in Azerbaijan and Arran who reigned c. 1438 -- 1467 .
Henry of Coquet ( died 1127 ) was a Dane who lived in a hermitage on the island of Coquet , off the Northumberland coast .
Lady Alicia Blackwood née Lambart , ( 1818 -- 30 July 1913 ) , the daughter of George Frederick Augustus Lambart , Viscount Kilcoursie ( 1789 - -1828 ) and Sarah Coppin , was an English painter and nurse , married to the Rev. James Stevenson Blackwood ( -1882 ) .
Karol Rzepecki ( 21 June 1865 , Poznań -- 14 December 1931 , Poznań ) was a Polish bookseller , social and political activist , editor of Sokół ( Falcon ) magazine .
Danny Kyle ( 12 December 1939 -- 5 July 1998 ) was a Scottish Folk singer - songwriter .
Eugène Marioton ( 7 April 1857 , Paris - 1933 ) was a French sculptor and medalist .
William Dickie Niven ( 26 April 1879 -- 26 February 1965 ) , of Fyvie , Aberdeenshire , was a Scottish academic .
Allan Dwan ( 3 April 1885 -- 28 December 1981 ) was a pioneering Canadian - born American motion picture director , producer and screenwriter .
Patric Standford ( 5 February 1939 -- 23 April 2014 ) was an English composer , pedagogue and writer .
George Blenkinsop ( 1822 -- 2 June 1904 ) was a Hudson 's Bay Company employee who made important contributions to Canadian history as a pioneer in the British Columbia area of the country .
Adriaen van der Werff ( 21 January 1659 -- 12 November 1722 ) was an accomplished Dutch painter of portraits and erotic , devotional and mythological scenes .
Barry Askew ( 13 December 1936 -- 17 April 2012 ) was a British journalist , editor of the Lancashire Evening Post and briefly of the News of the World .
Talaat Sadat ( 26 February 1954 -- 20 November 2011 ) was an Egyptian politician , lawyer and former political prisoner .
Alex Elmsley ( 2 March 1929 -- 8 January 2006 ) was a Scottish magician and computer programmer .
Karl Yens ( January 11 , 1868 -- 1945 ) , also Karl Jens was a German - American who was noted for both plein - air paintings of the California impressionist movement as well as Modernism .
Alfred Lyttelton QC ( 7 February 1857 -- 5 July 1913 ) was a British politician and sportsman from the Lyttelton family who excelled at both football and cricket .
Sylvie Gaudin ( June 19 , 1950 -- 1994 ) was a French glass painter and stained glass artist and manufacturer .
Valentine Kornienko ( 10 April 1939 -- 22 February 2011 ) was a member of the Writer 's Union of Ukraine and the winner of the Bohdan Lepky award .
Lieutenant Colonel Muhammad Umran ( Arabic : محمد عمران‎ ; 1922 - -4 March 1972 ) was a founding member of the Military Committee of the unitary Ba'ath Party , and a leading personality in Syrian politics from the 8th of March Revolution until the 1966 Syrian coup d'état .
József Ágoston de Kisjóka ( 1800 -- 9 March 1860 ) was a Hungarian lawyer and Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
Ellen Radka Toneff ( 25 June 1952 -- 21 October 1982 ) was a Norwegian jazz singer , daughter of the Bulgarian folk singer , pilot and radio technician Toni Toneff , she was born in Oslo and grew up in Lambertseter and Kolbotn .
Inji Hanimefendi ( Arabic : انجى هانم افندی‎)(Turkish : İncı Hanımefendi)(died 5 September 1890 ) was the first wife of Said Pasha , Wāli of Egypt and Sudan from 1854 until 1863 .
Ronald Knight ( 12 May 1913 -- October 1991 ) was an English cricketer active from 1933 to 1934 who played for Northamptonshire ( Northants ) .
Helge Hagerup ( 21 April 1933 -- 12 August 2008 ) was a Norwegian playwright , poet and novelist .
Louis III de La Trémoille ( 1521 -- 25 March 1577 ) , 1st Duke of Thouars , was a sixteenth - century French nobleman of the La Tremoille family .
Harry Matheson ( 12 June 1891 -- 4 November 1956 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda , Carlton and Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Stoyan Zaimov ( Bulgarian : Стоян Заимов ; 12 August 1853 -- 9 September 1932 ) was a Bulgarian revolutionary , apostle of the April Uprising , enlightener , public figure and writer .
Prof John Norman Collie FRSE FRS ( 10 September 1859 -- 1 November 1942 ) , commonly referred to as J. Norman Collie , was a British scientist , mountaineer , and explorer .
Ruth Egri ( 1911 - -1996 ) was an American artist , painter , muralist , educator , and illustrator who worked in the Federal Art Project and in the WPA New Reading Materials Program during the New Deal .
Rodrigo de Sousa Coutinho , 1st Count of Linhares ( 4 August 1755 in Chaves -- 26 January 1812 in Rio de Janeiro ) was a Portuguese nobleman and politician .
Max Cross ( 11 July 1934 -- 7 March 1985 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Shelford Bidwell FRS ( 6 March 1848 -- 18 December 1909 ) was an English physicist and inventor .
Upon the death of Charles Allanson - Winn , 7th Baron Headley , on 23 February 1994 , the Headley Barony became extinct .
Philips van der Aa ( died after 1586 ) was a politician in the Seventeen Provinces and a statesman of the Dutch Republic during its struggle for independence , the Eighty Years ' War .
John Peile ( 24 April 1838 -- 9 October 1910 ) was an English philologist .
Geoffrey I of Vianden 7th duke of Vianden 1273 - 1310 ( -1310 ) was a son to duke Filips I of Vianden and Mary of Brabant - Perwez .
William Bladen ( 1672 - -1718 ) was an English - born Attorney - General in Maryland and , briefly , Secretary of that Province .
Caroline Birley ( 16 November 1851 -- 15 February 1907 ) was an English geologist , fossil collector and children 's author .
Aniella di Beltrano or Anniella di Rosa ( 1613 - -1649 ) was an Italian woman painter of the Baroque period , active in Naples .
Selby Norton ( 13 September 1836 -- 11 November 1906 ) was an English cricketer who played for Kent .
Arslan Shah I was Sultan of Kerman ( 1101 - -1142 ) , a city in Iran situated at the center of Kerman province .
Captain Keith Robert Martin Kinnier , O.B.E. ( 1902 - -1969 ) Captain Keith R.M. Kinnier was a distinguished British seaman , who on 31 December 1943 , saved his ship from submarine attack in the seas off Karachi for which actions he was awarded the O.B.E.
James Grigson ( January 30 , 1932 in Texarkana , Texas - June 3 , 2004 ) , called by parts of the press as `` Doctor Death '' , was a Texas forensic psychiatrist who testified in 167 capital trials , nearly all of which resulted in death sentences .
Sir Richard de Whitacre ( circa 1300 - 1375 ) was the Lord of the Manors of Nether Whitacre , Over Whitacre , Elmdon , and Freasley .
Zdeněk Liška ( 16 March 1922 -- 13 August 1983 ) was a Czech composer who produced a large number of film scores across a prolific career that started in the 1950s .
Mandell Creighton ( /ˈmændəl ˈkraɪtən/ ; 5 July 1843 -- 14 January 1901 ) , was a British historian and a bishop of the Church of England .
Sacha Zaliouk , born Alexander Davidovich Zaliouk ( 1887 - -1971 ) , was a Russian Empire - born illustrator and sculptor , from a Jewish family in Radomysl , Ukraine .
Knut Bjørnsen ( 26 July 1932 -- 14 November 2008 ) was a sports commentator and journalist for the Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation .
Walter Moyle ( 1672 - -1721 ) was an English politician and political writer , an advocate of classical republicanism .
Lee Barron ( born as Elroy Vernon Lee 1 August 1915 Minnesota ; d. 21 December 1993 , Omaha ) was an American big band leader and radio and TV personality .
Gilles Reingot ( French : Gillequin de Bailleul ; fl . 1501 - -1530 ) was a Franco - Flemish composer of the Renaissance , associated with the Habsburg court of Philip I of Castile .
Matilda Ridout Edgar ( 29 September 1844 -- 29 September 1910 ) was a Canadian historian and feminist .
Clément Barbot ( 1914 -- 14 July 1963 ) was a top aide to Haitian President Francois Duvalier .
Hans Hirschfeld ( Bremen , 29 May 1899 -- The Hague , 4 November 1961 ) was a Dutch economist and a founder member of the Council for a Democratic Germany .
Konstantin Vyrupayev ( 10 October 1930 -- 31 October 2012 ) was a Soviet wrestler and Olympic Champion .
Blessed Maria Josefa Alhama y Valera ( 1893 -- 8 February 1983 ) was a Roman Catholic Spanish nun and she was the founder of both the Handmaids of Merciful Love in 1930 and the Sons of Merciful Love in 1951 .
Rudolf Vanmoerkerke ( 7 October 1924 -- 4 December 2014 ) ( Dutch pronunciation : ( ˈryː.dɔlf vɐn.ˈmur.kɛr.kə ) ) was a Belgian businessman and a pioneer of the Belgian travel industry .
Charles Foden ( 1868 -- 14 October 1908 ) was a British tug of war competitor .
Sir Robert Wilmot , 1st Baronet ( 1708 - -1772 ) was an English servant of the Crown , Secretary to successive Viceroys of Ireland from 1740 to 1772 , and after 1758 Secretary to the Lord Chamberlain of the Household .
Emil Zeiß ( July 2 , 1833 -- April 14 , 1910 ) was a German Protestant minister and painter .
Franz Kohaut ( -- - died 1822 ) was a Czech botanical collector and gardener from Neuhaus , Bohemia .
Archibald Hood ( 1823 - -1902 ) was a Scottish engineer and coalowner who became an important figure in the industrial growth of the Rhondda Valley .
John Chorlton ( 1666 , Salford -- 16 May 1705 , Manchester ) was an English presbyterian minister and tutor .
Frances Foy ( April 11 , 1890 - 1963 ) was an American painter , muralist , illustrator , and etcher born in Chicago , Illinois .
James Holworthy ( 1781 - -1841 ) was a British watercolour artist .
John Robert Tait , known as Jock Tait ( 20 November 1886 -- 13 April 1945 ) was a Scottish cricketer who played in English and Welsh leagues .
Richard Alfred Davenport ( 1777 - -1852 ) was an English miscellaneous writer .
Sir John Harvey - Jones MBE ( 16 April 1924 -- 9 January 2008 ) was an English businessman .
Andrew Lumisden or Lumsden ( 1720 - -1801 ) was a Scottish Jacobite .
Vic Hey ( born Monday 18 November 1912 in Liverpool , New South Wales -- died Tuesday 11 April 1995 ( aged 82 ) ) was an Australian rugby league national and state representative five - eighth / stand - off and later a successful first - grade and national coach .
Dave Clohessy ( 1905 - -1986 ) was an Irish sportsperson .
Edward Neil McKelvey O.C. , C.D. , Q.C. , ( 1925 - -2011 ) was a Canadian lawyer .
Keith Edward Abbott ( 1814 - -1873 ) was a British diplomat and consul general at Tabriz and later Odessa .
Gertrude of Baden ( before 1160 -- before 1225 ) was a Margravine of Baden by birth and by marriage a Countess of Dagsburg .
Zhou Jianren ( Chinese : 周建人 ; 1888 - 1984 ) was a politician and biologist of the People 's Republic of China .
Eusebius of Laodicea ( Greek : Εὐσέβιος ; date of birth uncertain ; died about 268 ) was an Alexandrian , a deacon who had some fame as a confessor , and became bishop of Laodicea in Syria .
Gilbert Marshal , 4th Earl of Pembroke ( 1194 -- 27 June 1241 ) was the third son of William Marshal , 1st Earl of Pembroke and Isabel de Clare , 4th Countess of Pembroke , the daughter of Richard de Clare .
Mary Bonaparte ( Mary Léonie Eugénie Mathilde Jeanne Julie Zénaïde Bonaparte ; 10 December 1870 -- 1947 ) was the eldest surviving daughter of Prince Napoléon Bonaparte of Canino and Christine Ruspoli .
Hansel Mieth ( 1909 - -1998 ) was a German - born photojournalist who worked on the staff of LIFE Magazine .
Yang Zhuoxin ( simplified Chinese : 杨卓新 ; traditional Chinese : 楊卓新 ; pinyin : Yáng Zhuóxīn ; 10 October 1890 -- 10 June 1963 ) was a Chinese educator and mathematician who served as President of Hunan University from August 1930to March 1931 .
Raffaello Tancredi ( Naples , 1837 - -1890 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of historical subjects .
William MacGillivray FRSE MWS ( 25 January 1796 -- 4 September 1852 ) was a Scottish naturalist and ornithologist .
George William Francis ( 1800 - -1865 ) was an English botanical and general science writer .
Harold Comte ( 10 March 1909 -- 30 May 1945 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) , and Sandringham in the Victorian Football Association ( VFA ) during the 1930s .
Radhey Shyam Kori ( 7 July 1939 -- 12 August 2015 ) was an Indian politician who was MP for Ghatampur in Uttar Pradesh from 2004 to 2009 .
Walram of Jülich ( c. 1304 -- 14 August 1349 ) was Archbishop of Cologne from 1332 to his death in 1349 .
Theodor von Oppolzer ( 26 October 1841 -- 26 December 1886 ) was an Austrian astronomer and mathematician of Bohemian origin .
William Leighton Leitch ( 22 Nov 1804 -- 25 April 1883 ) was a master Scottish landscape watercolour painter and illustrator .
George Edmund Butler ( 15 January 1872 -- 9 August 1936 ) was a landscape and portrait painter specialising in oils and watercolours .
Susanna Duncombe née Highmore ( 1725 - -1812 ) was a British poet and artist .
Johannes Hadlaub ( fl . 1300 , d. before 1340 ) is one of the Minnesingers whose works are recorded in Codex Manesse .
Kommareddi Suryanarayana ( Telugu : కొమ్మారెడ్డి సూర్యనారాయణ ) ( b : 8 March 1907 - d : 6 May 1995 ) was a Rajya Sabha and Lok Sabha member in Indian Parliament , Indian freedom activist and Gandhian .
Fred E. Miller ( 1868 -- 1936 ) was an American photographer , who worked at Crow Agency .
Hensleigh Wedgwood ( 21 January 1803 -- 2 June 1891 ) was a British etymologist , philologist and barrister , author of A Dictionary of English Etymology .
John Russell Colvin ( 29 May 1807 -- 9 September 1857 ) was a British civil servant in India , part of the illustrious Anglo - Indian Colvin family .
Edward Mortelmans ( 1915 - -2008 ) was an English artist and illustrator .
Albert Mansbridge , CH ( 10 January 1876 , Gloucester , Gloucestershire , England -- 22 August 1952 , Torquay , Devon ) was an English educator who was one of the pioneers of adult education in Britain .
Leszek of Racibórz ( Polish : Leszek raciborski ) ( c. 1292 -- 1336 ) was a Duke of Racibórz since 1306 and Duke of Koźle from 1334 until his death .
Michael Bowyer ( 1599 - -1645 ) was an actor in English Renaissance theatre in the Jacobean and Caroline eras .
Daniel Maynard Burgess ( December 21 , 1828 - -1911 ) was a surgeon and explorer born in Otsego County , New York .
Carl Gustaf Axel Örbom ( 29 July 1836 -- 30 May 1889 ) , was a Swedish jurist and government figure who , in the final eight months of his life , served as the Minister for Justice .
Arnold Perlmutter ( 1859 - -1953 ) was a composer for Yiddish theatre , born in Zlotshev , Galitsia .
Ee Tiang Hong ( 1933 - -1990 ) was a Malayan poet of Chinese ancestry .
Parduman Singh Brar ( 15 October 1927 -- 22 March 2007 ) was an Indian athlete who specialized in shot put and discus throw events .
Ivica Mlivončić ( 1931 - 2013 ) was a controversial Croatian author and columnist in Slobodna Dalmacija from Split .
Ohn Maung ( Burmese : အုန်းမောင် ( ʔóʊɴ màʊɴ ) ; 2 February 1913 -- 19 July 1947 ) was a Burmese politician who served as the Deputy Minister of Transport in Myanmar 's pre - independence government .
The Venerable Thomas Kurialacherry ( 14 January 1873 -- 6 February 1925 ) was a Catholic bishop , born in the Indian village of Champakulam .
Marie Carré ( died 1984 ) was a French Protestant nurse who later in life converted to become a Roman Catholic nun .
Maurits Coppieters ( 14 May 1920 -- 11 November 2005 ) , Flemish politician for the Volksunie , member of the Belgian Chamber ( 1965 - -71 ) , the Belgian Senate ( 1971 - -1979 ) and the European Parliament ( 1979 - -81 ) .
Montague Ainslie ( 28 April 1792 -- 1 February 1884 ) was an English forester and businessman whose interests included the iron ore company Harrison Ainslie .
Julius Mayr ( 7 January 1855 -- 8 May 1935 ) was a German physician , chairman of the German Alpine Club and writer who wrote a biography of the painter Wilhelm Leibl .
Giuseppe Nardulli ( 6 July 1947 -- 26 June 2008 ) was an Italian physicist based in Bari .
Juan Núñez II de Lara ( c. 1276 -- 1315 in Burgos ) , nicknamed el Mozo or el de la Barba ( the bearded one ) , was a Spanish noble , and head of the House of Lara in the service of the Kingdom of Castile .
Achilles Daunt ( 1832 - -1878 ) was a noted Irish preacher and homilist , and Anglican dean of Cork .
Marjabelle Young Stewart ( 16 May 1924 -- 3 March 2007 ) was an American writer and expert on etiquette .
Constance Adelaide Smith ( 28 April 1878 -- 10 June 1938 ) , also known as C. Penswick Smith in her published works , was an English woman who was responsible for the reinvigoration of the Christian holiday of Mothering Sunday in the UK in the early 20th century .
Jan Sanders van Hemessen ( c. 1500 -- c. 1566 ) was a leading artist of the second generation of Dutch and Flemish Renaissance painting , belonging to the group of Italianizing Flemish painters called the Romanists , who were influenced by Italian Renaissance painting .
Frederick William Conway ( 1782 - -1853 ) was an Irish journalist , newspaper founder and editor .
Nachman Syrkin ( or Nahman Syrkin or Nahum Syrkin ; b. 11 February 1868 ; d. 6 September 1924 ) was a political theorist , founder of Labour Zionism and a prolific writer in Hebrew , Yiddish , Russian , German and English language .
Jacob Heerbrand ( 12 August 1521 -- 22 May 1600 ) was a German Protestant theologian and controversialist .
Dariusz Ratajczak was found dead in a car parked near the shopping centre in Opole on 11 June 2010 .
Rinzō Shiina ( 椎名 麟三 Shiina Rinzō ; né 大坪 昇 Noboru Ōtsuka ; 1 October 1911 -- 28 March 1973 ) was a Japanese writer , novelist , short story writer and playwright .
Janet McEwan ( 1860 -- 1921 ) , née Janet Landells , known as Jenny McEwan , was a British Liberal Party politician and one of the first women to stand for election to the UK Parliament .
The Honourable Montagu Curzon ( 21 September 1846 -- 1 September 1907 ) was a British soldier and Conservative politician .
Francis Bellinger ( died September 1721 ) was an English physician .
Joseph Jaquet , sometimes written Joseph Jacquet , ( 30 January 1822 - 9 June 1898 ) was a Belgian sculptor .
Sarah Platt Doremus ( born 3 August 1802 New York City ; died there 29 January 1877 ) was noted for her philanthropy .
George Parker Tuxford ( ca.1810 -- 24 October 1870 ) of Barnes , London , was a British magazine publisher .
John Kinder Labatt ( 1803 -- 26 October 1866 ) was an Irish - Canadian brewer , and the founder of the Labatt Brewing Company .
William Rhys - Herbert ( 1868 - 1921 ) was an American composer , conductor , organist and pianist of Welsh origin .
Jean Renaud ( c. 1734 -- 16 March 1794 ) is first noted in Canadian history in 1768 when he married at Quebec City .
Mohammad Jawad Balaghi ( 1865 - -1933 ) , was an Iraqi Shia Muslim religious authority , author , poet and polemicist .
Johann Michael Seligmann ( 1720 - -1762 ) was a German artist and engraver best known for his ornithological artwork in Sammlung verschiedener ausländischer und seltener Vögel ( Collection of various foreign and rare birds ) which included plates based on the works of Mark Catesby and George Edwards .
Linda Haglund ( 15 June 1956 -- 21 November 2015 ) was a Swedish Olympic sprinter .
Brian Cumby ( 9 October 1950 - 26 February 2015 ) was a British shipwright who built a full - size replica of a Bronze Age boat for the National Maritime Museum Cornwall in Falmouth using only the tools available to Bronze Age man .
Al - Mutawakkil III ( Arabic : المتوكل على الله الثالث‎ ) ( died 1543 ) was caliph from 1508 to 1516 , and again in 1517 .

Evan Griffiths ( 18 January 1795 -- 31 August 1873 ) was a Welsh clergyman , born near Bridgend , Glamorgan .

Jacques de La Palice ( or de La Palisse ) ( 1470 -- 24 February 1525 ) was a French nobleman and military officer .
Naemul of Silla ( died 402 ) ( r. 356 - -402 ) was the 17th ruler of the Korean kingdom of Silla .
Carlo Michele Bonelli , Cardinal Alessandrino ( 25 November 1541 - - 28 March 1598 ) was an Italian senior papal diplomat with a distinguished career that spanned two decades from 1571 .
Saint Ignatius of Santhià ( 5 June 1686 -- 22 September 1770 ) , born Lorenzo Maurizio Belvisotti , was an Italian Roman Catholic priest and a professed member of the Order of Friars Minor .
Trevor Pearcey ( 5 March 1919 -- 27 January 1998 ) was a British - born Australian scientist , who created CSIRAC , one of the first ever stored - program electronic computers in the world .
Gertruda Komorowska ( born 1754 in Suszno -- 13 February 1771 in the river Rata near Sielec Bełski , Poland ) was a Polish noble lady .

Eiler Holck ( 4 June 1627 - 28 June 1696 ) was a Danish military officer , from 1671 with the title of baron .

General Sir Frederick William Hamilton KCB ( 8 July 1815 -- 4 October 1890 ) was a British Army officer who became Major General commanding the Brigade of Guards .
Sir Henry Whatley Tyler ( 7 March 1827 - 1908 ) was a British Inspector of Railways , Railway Company director and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1880 to 1892 .
Richard of Pudlicott ( died 1305 ) , also known as Richard de Podelicote ( or Pudlicote , or Dick Puddlecote ) , was an English wool merchant who , down on his luck , became an infamous burglar of King Edward I 's Wardrobe treasury at Westminster Abbey in 1303 .

John Gordon , 3rd Earl of Aboyne ( died 7 April 1732 ) was the son of Charles Gordon , 2nd Earl of Aboyne and Elizabeth Lyon .

Giovanni Domenico Cassini ( 8 June 1625 -- 14 September 1712 ) was an Italian mathematician , astronomer , astrologer and engineer .

Chicot ( c. 1540 - -1592 ) , real name Jean - Antoine d'Anglerais , was the jester of King Henry III of France and later Henry IV . He was sharp - tongued and very cunning and spoke with the king without formalities .
Karin Juel ( 26 May 1900 , Kungsholmen , Stockholm -- 2 May 1976 , Stockholm ) was a Swedish singer , actor and writer .

William de Beaumont , 3rd Earl of Warwick ( before 1140 -- 15 November 1184 ) was an English nobleman .
Gao Lishi ( Chinese : 高力士 ; pinyin : Gāo Lìshì ) ( 684 - -762 ) , formally the Duke of Qi ( 齊公 ) , was a eunuch official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty , becoming particularly powerful during Emperor Xuanzong of Tang 's reign .
Włodzimierz Kołos ( 6 September 1928 -- 3 June 1996 ) - Polish chemist and physicist who was one of the founders of modern quantum chemistry , and pioneered accurate calculations on the electronic structure of molecules .

Fu Chong ( Chinese : 苻崇 ; died 394 ) was an emperor of the Chinese / Di state Former Qin .
