Betty Morrissey ( 1908 -- 20 April 1944 ) , was an American film actress .
Empress Deng Mengnü ( 鄧猛女 ) ( died 165 ) , also briefly known as Liang Mengnü ( 梁猛女 ) then as Bo Mengnü ( 薄猛女 ) , was an empress during Han Dynasty .
Karl Babor ( 23 August 1918 - 18 January 1964 ) was a Nazi , SS doctor of the Third Reich , and officer at Camp Gross - Rosen with the rank of Hauptsturmführer .
Benjamin Wardill ( 15 October 1842 -- 15 October 1917 ) , often referred to as Major Wardill , was an Australian cricketer and cricket administrator .
William C. K. Irwin , also known as William C. Irwin and Will Irwin ( 3 January 1907 -- 23 October 1998 ) , was an American pianist , conductor , and songwriter .
Vasant Rai ( 1942 - -1985 ) was one of world 's most acclaimed performers of Indian music and virtuoso of the Indian - Persian - Afghan instrument Sarod .
Bronislav Poloczek ( Polish : Bronisław Poloczek ) ( 7 August 1939 -- 16 March 2012 ) was a Polish - Czech theatre and television actor .
Emme Gerhard ( 1872 - -1946 ) was a professional American photographer who worked with her sister Mayme Gerhard ( 1876 - -1955 ) in St. Louis , Missouri .
Charles Fenwick ( 5 May 1850 -- 20 April 1918 ) was a British trade unionist and Liberal--
Khaled al - Hassan also known as Abu Said ( 1928 - 1994 ) was an early adviser of Yasser Arafat , PLO leader and a founder of the Palestinian political and militant organization Fatah .
Elliott Marks ( 3 December 1941 -- 9 July 2003 ) was a movie stills photographer who was posthumously awarded the first Still Photographer Award by the International Cinematographers Guild Publicists Awards in 2004 .
Johannes Vallentin Dominicus Werbata ( Padang , 22 September 1866 - Magelang , 2 June 1929 ) , better known by his initials JVD , was a military superintendent , first class sensor and knight in the Military William Order fourth grade .
James C. Kellogg III ( 1915 - -1980 ) was Chairman of the Port Authority of New York & New Jersey and Chairman of the Board of Governors of the New York Stock Exchange .
John William Fordham Johnson ( 28 November 1866 -- 28 November 1938 ) was a Canadian businessman and the 14th Lieutenant Governor of British Columbia .
Ralph Eure , 3rd Baron Eure ( 24 September 1558 -- 1 April 1617 ) , of Ingleby and Malton , Yorkshire , was an English nobleman and politician .
Isham Randolph ( December 1684 -- November 1742 ) , sometimes referred to as Isham Randolph of Dungeness , was the maternal grandfather of United States President Thomas Jefferson .
Lucia Mantu ( pen name of Camelia Nădejde ; September 22 , 1888 -- November 1971 ) was a Romanian prose writer .
Augustus of Brunswick - Lüneburg ( 10 April 1579 -- 17 September 1666 ) , called the Younger , was duke of Brunswick - Lüneburg .
Ya'akov Geri ( Hebrew : יעקב גרי‎ , born 18 September 1901 , died 18 December 1974 ) , also known as Jack Gering .
Carlo Ruini ( 1530 - -1598 ) was one of the most noted anatomists of the horse of the 16th century .
Jürgen Wattenberg ( 28 December 1900 -- 27 September 1995 ) was a German naval officer and U - boat commander during the Second World War .
Gerard de Malynes ( fl . 1585 - -1641 ) was an independent merchant in foreign trade , an English commissioner in the Spanish Netherlands , a government advisor on trade matters , assay master of the mint , and commissioner of mint affairs .
Talimeran Ao ( 28 January 1918 -- 13 September 1998 ) was an Indian footballer and physician .
Idalguer ( Latin : Hidelherius , Idelherus ; died 914 ) was the second bishop of Vic ( 899 - -914 ) after the see was re - founded .
Risteárd de Tiúit ( anglicised as Richard Tuite ) ( ob . 1210 ) was a member of Richard de Clare , 2nd Earl of Pembroke 's Irish invasion force , and Lord Chief Justice of Ireland .
Sigeric ( ? -- 22 August 415 ) was a Visigoth king for seven days in 415 AD .
Adolphe Chenevière , D.ès . L. ( 1855 - -1917 ) was a fin de siècle Swiss novelist , short story writer , and literary scholar .
Francesco Antonio Begnudelli - Basso ( born at Trento ; died at Freising , 9 October 1713 ) was an Austrian canon lawyer .
Volmar Wikström ( 27 December 1889 -- 10 June 1957 ) was a Finnish wrestler from Pargas , Olympic medalist in freestyle wrestling .
Joseph Stretch Crowther ( 1820 -- March 1893 ) ( usually known as J. S. Crowther ) was an English architect who practised in Manchester .
Christina Anna Skytte af Dudenhof ( Stockholm , 9 November 1643 --21 January 1677 , Hagelsrum ) , was a Swedish baroness and pirate .
Giacomo Rondinella ( born 30 August 1923 - 25 February 2015 ) was an Italian singer and actor .
Cristóbal Galán ( ca . 1630 - -24 September 1684 ) was a Spanish Baroque composer .
Áed mac Néill ( died 819 ) ( Irish pronunciation : ( ˈaið mak niːˈəl ) ) , commonly called Áed Oirdnide , was King of Ailech .
Patrick Lindsay , 4th Lord Lindsay of the Byres ( died 1526 ) was a reputed advisor of James IV of Scotland , and counsellor to Margaret Tudor .
Xavier Petulengro ( 25 December 1859 - 16 June 1957 ) , more often known as Gipsy Petulengro ( or Gypsy Petulengro ) , was a British Romanichal horse trader , violinist , businessman , writer and broadcaster , known as the `` King of the Gypsies '' .
George Metochites ( Greek : Γεώργιος Μετοχίτης ; c. 1250 -- 1328 ) was an archdeacon in Constantinople during the 1270s and early 1280s , and an important , fervent supporter of the Union of the Greek and Latin Churches that was agreed to at the Second Council of Lyons ( 1274 ) .
Samuel Noble ( 1779 - -1853 ) was an English engraver , and minister of the New Church ( Swedenborgian ) .
Major Wellesley Tudor Pole O.B.E. ( 23 April 1884 -- 13 September 1968 ) was a spiritualist and early British Bahá'í .
Sir Evan Nepean , 1st Baronet ( 9 July 1752 -- 2 October 1822 ) was a British politician and colonial administrator .
James Rhodes Stanley Raper ( 9 August 1909 -- 9 March 1997 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played three matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club against Derbyshire and Gloucestershire in 1936 , and after World War II , versus Nottinghamshire in 1947 .
Antony Nicholas Allott ( 30 June 1924 -- 3 June 2002 ) was an English academic , Professor of African Law at the University of London .
Sir Arthur Forbes , 1st Baronet of Castle Forbes , County Longford , Ireland ( c. 1590 - -1632 ) took part in the Scottish Plantation of Ireland , and died in a duel at Hamburg , Germany .
Although a doctor was called , Frank Paton died from heart failure at around 5.30 am on 13 November 1909 , just 10 days short of his 54th birthday .
Blessed Stefan Wincenty Frelichowski ( 22 January 1913 in Chełmża -- 23 February 1945 in Dachau ) was a Polish priest and Scout , and is the patron of Polish Scouts .
Edith Hipkins ( 1854 - -1945 ) was a British portrait painter who exhibited regularly at the Royal Academy between 1883 and 1911 .
Franz Gürtner ( 26 August 1881 -- 29 January 1941 ) was a German Minister of Justice in Adolf Hitler 's cabinet , responsible for coordinating jurisprudence in the Third Reich .
Prof Tom Leadbetter Cottrell DSc FRSE ( 1923 -- 1973 ) ( usually simply referred to as Tom Cottrell ) was a short - lived but influential Scottish chemist .
David Morier Evans ( 1819 - -1874 ) , was a Welsh financial journalist .
Thomas Nicholas Burke ( 8 September 1830 in Galway -- 2 July 1882 in Tallaght , Ireland ) was an Irish Dominican preacher .
He died on 17 November 1871 at Hume Towers , his residence at Bournemouth , leaving issue , of whom H. M. Walmsley wrote The Life of Sir Joshua Walmsley ( London 1879 ) .
Govind Mukkaji Rathod ( death 26 October , 2014 ) was a member of the 13th Maharashtra Legislative Assembly .
Jovan Cvetković ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јован Цветковић ; 1860 - -1915 ) , known as Jovan Dolgač ( Јован Долгач ) , was a Serbian Chetnik commander in Macedonia , who also participated in the Balkan Wars and World War I in the Chetnik detachments of the Serbian Army .
Sue Hastings ( May 10 , 1884 -- 1977 ) was an American puppeteer known for popularizing the ancient art of puppetry in the 1930s and 1940s .
Andrés Díaz Venero de Leiva ( died 1578 ) was the first president of the New Kingdom of Granada , appointed in 1564 .
Deng Conghao ( Chinese : 邓从豪 ; Pinyin : Dèng Cóngháo ; 1920 - -1998 ) was a Chinese educator .
John Preston , 1st Baron Tara ( 4 November 1764 -- 18 July 1821 ) , was an Irish politician .
Franz von Lauer ( 11 May 1736 -- 11 September 1803 ) began his service in the Austrian army as an engineer officer and became a general officer while fighting against Ottoman Turkey .
Alexander McCabe ( Irish : Alasdar Mac Cába ; 5 June 1886 -- 31 May 1972 ) was an Irish Sinn Féin ( later Cumann na nGaedheal ) politician .
Elizabeth Phillips Hughes ( 12 July 1851 -- 19 December 1925 ) was a Welsh scholar , teacher , and promoter of women 's education .
John Batmanson ( died 1531 ) , was prior of the Charterhouse in London .
Edmund Gayton ( 1608 - -1666 ) was an English academic , physician and author , now considered a hack writer .
Dinqinesh Mercha ( 1815 -- August 1907 ) was Empress - Consort of Emperor Tekle Giyorgis II . Empress Dinqinesh was the daughter of Shum Mercha of Tembien , and his wife Woizero Silass of Enderta .
Virginia North , Lady White ( 1 January 1945 -- 5 June 2004 ) was an Anglo - American actress who appeared in small roles in five films and one TV programme between 1967 and 1971 .
Bartholomew Price ( 1818 -- 29 December 1898 ) was an English mathematician and educator .
Charles Fritts ( 1850 -- 1903 ) was the American inventor credited with creating the first working Selenium Cell in 1883 .
Bartolomé Sureda y Miserol ( 1769 - -1850 ) was a Spanish artisan .
Sir Hugh Plat ( 1552 - -1608 ) was an English writer on agriculture and inventor , known from his works The Jewell House of Art and Nature ( 1594 ) and his major work on gardening Floraes Paradise ( 1608 ) .
Tord Godal ( 27 June 1909 -- 27 February 2002 ) was a Norwegian theologian and bishop for the Diocese of Nidaros .
Karl Harris ( 21 October 1979 -- 3 June 2014 ) was a three - time British Supersport champion .
Jack Fitzsimons ( 26 April 1930 -- 4 November 2014 ) was an Irish chartered architect and surveyor based in Kells , County Meath .
Joam Yama(1566 ? -- 29 September 1633 ) was a Japanese Jesuit monk born in Tsu Province , at the center of Japan 's main island .
Talbot Dilworth - Harrison ( 5 July 1886 - 16 May 1975 ) was Archdeacon of Chesterfield from 1934 until 1943 .
Arabella Elizabeth Roupell ( 23 March 1817 Newport , Shropshire -- 31 July 1914 Swallowfield , Berkshire ) was an English flower painter , noted for an anonymous set of flower paintings published in 1849 under the title ' Specimens of the flora of South Africa by a Lady ' .
Anna Petronella van Heerden ( 1887 - -1975 ) , was the first Afrikaner woman to qualify as a medical doctor .
Grace Stone Coates ( 1881 - -1976 ) wrote short stories , poetry , and news articles .
Magnus O'Donnell ( q4 1882 -- after 1906 ) was an English footballer who scored 13 goals from 64 appearances in the Football League playing for Lincoln City and Barnsley .
Sir George Matthew McNaughton CB ( 31 January 1893 -- 31 August 1966 ) was a British civil engineer who specialised in hydraulic engineering .
Cyril Lord ( 12 July 1911 -- 29 May 1984 ) was a British entrepreneur known principally for the manufacture of carpets during the 1960s .
Bengt Lindskog ( 25 February 1933 -- 27 January 2008 ) was a Swedish footballer who played at both professional and international levels , as a midfielder .
Harald Hennum ( 29 May 1928 -- 14 October 1993 ) was a Norwegian footballer .
Arden John Arden Maddison ( 12 February 1900 -- 19 August 1987 ) was an English footballer who played at half - back for Stoke , Port Vale , Oldham Athletic , Mansfield Town , SC Nîmes ( France ) , Gresley Rovers and Sutton Town .
Robert Morehead Cook ( 12 January , 1919 -- 29 December , 1999 ) was a United States Army Colonel , who served as an inspector general during the Vietnam War .
George Riddle Banta , Sr . ( July 16 , 1857 -- September 23 , 1935 ) was the founder of the George Banta Company ( later the Banta Corporation ) and an influential figure in the development of the collegiate Phi Delta Theta fraternity and Delta Gamma women 's fraternity .
Baron Francis van Aarssens or Baron François van Aerssen ( 27 September 1572 - 27 December 1641 ) , from 1611 on lord of Sommelsdijk , was a diplomat and statesman of the United Provinces .
Catherine Edith Macauley Martin ( 1848 -- 15 March 1937 ) was an Australian novelist who used the pseudonyms M. C. , Mrs Alick MacLeod or anonymous .
Fritz Bennewitz ( 20 January 1926 -- 13 September 1995 ) was a German Theatre Director .
William Bateman , 1st Viscount Bateman KB , FRS ( 1695 -- December 1744 ) , was a British Whig politician .
Sir John Henry Orr OBE QPM ( 1918 - -1995 ) , was a Scottish police officer and was the first Chief Constable of the Lothian and Borders Police .
William Philip Hiern ( 19 January 1839 -- 28 November 1925 ) was a British mathematician and botanist .
Norman John MacMillan , CC , QC ( 1909 -- 30 October 1978 ) was a president of Canadian National Railway .
Alberts Jērums ( 1919 , Karula Parish - 1978 ) was a noted Latvian composer .
Ugolino Gonzaga ( 1320 -- 13 October 1362 ) was an Italian condottiero , a member of the House of Gonzaga .
John Inglis , Lord Glencorse FRSE ( 21 August 1810 -- 20 August 1891 ) was a Scottish politician and judge .
Müezzinzade Ali Pasha ( Turkish : Müezzinzade Ali Paşa ; also known as Sofu Ali Pasha or Sufi Ali Pasha or Meyzinoğlu Ali Pasha ; died 7 October 1571 ) was an Ottoman statesman and naval officer .
Air Marshal Sir Charles Edward Chilton KBE , CB ( 1 November 1906 -- 4 August 1992 ) was a Royal Air Force officer who served as Air Officer Commanding - in - Chief Coastal Command from 1959 to 1962 .
Paolo Stoppa ( 6 June 1906 -- 1 May 1988 ) was an Italian actor and dubber .
Hugh Trumble ( 12 May 1867 -- 14 August 1938 ) was an Australian cricketer who played 32 Test matches as a bowling all - rounder between 1890 and 1904 .
Herbert du Parcq , Baron du Parcq PC , KC ( 5 August 1880 -- 27 April 1949 ) was a British judge .
Friedrich Weichelt ( December 1894 -- November 1961 ) was a leading German explosives engineer .
Augusto Gansser - Biaggi ( 28 October 1910 -- 9 January 2012 ) was a Swiss geologist who specialised in the geology of the Himalayas .
Shukur Burkhanov ( Russian : Бурханов , Шукур ; 15 September 1910 -- 15 August 1987 ) was a Soviet theatre and cinema actor .
Vorn Vet ( 1934 - -1978 ) born Pen Thuok , was a deputy prime minister for the economy of Democratic Kampuchea .
Shivaramaiah Ramachandra Aithal ( Kannada : ಶಿವರಾಮಯ್ಯ ರಾಮಚಂದ್ರ ಐತಾಳ ; 16 November 1948 -- 10 January 2011 ) , popularly known as S. Ramachandra , was a National Award winning Indian cinematographer .
James Stanton V ( 1771 - -1829 ) is the namesake of Stantonsburg , North Carolina .
Eric Cheney ( 5 January 1924 -- 30 December 2001 ) was an English motorcycle racer , designer and independent constructor .
Otmar Mácha ( Mariánské Hory , Ostrava , 2 October 1922 - -Pardubice , 14 December 2006 ) was a Czech composer .
Countess Dorothea of Hanau - Münzenberg ( 4 February 1556 -- 5 September 1638 ) , was a German noblewoman member of the House of Hanau by birth and by virtue of her two marriages Countess of Ortenburg and Gleichen - Kranichfeld - Ehrenstein - Blankenhain .
Cully Richards ( 1908 - -1978 ) was an American singer , film and television actor .
Apichet Kittikorncharoen ( Thai : อภิเชษฐ์ กิตติกรเจริญ ; rtgs : Aphichet Kittikoncharoen , name later changed to Panrawat ( ปาณรวัฐ ) , 2 December 1982 -- 9 December 2007 ) was a Thai singer known under the stage name Big D2B.
Katharina Dalton ( 11 November 1916 -- 17 September 2004 ) was a British physician and pioneer in the research of premenstrual stress syndrome .
Anna of Masovia ( c. 1498 -- after 26 January 1557 in Jaroslaw ) was Princess of Mazovia and a member of the House of Piast .
Friedrich Burmeister ( 1890 - -1969 ) was a German geophysicist .
Louis E. Eliasberg , Sr . ( 1896 - -1976 ) was an American financier and numismatist .
Samuel Mearne ( 20 April 1624 -- May 1683 ) was an English Restoration bookbinder and publisher whose work is considered a high point of pre - industrial bookbinding .
Hieronymus Karl Graf von Colloredo - Mansfeld ( 30 March 1775 -- 23 July 1822 ) was an Austrian corps commander during the Napoleonic Wars .
Eduard Hedvicek ( Czech : Eduard Hedvíček ) was born in 1878 in Kojetín , Moravia , Austria - Hungary , now in the Czech Republic , and died 1947 in Vienna , Austria .
Trudeliese Schmidt ( 7 November 1942 − 24 June 2004 ) was a German operatic mezzosoprano who had an international career , performing at major opera houses and festivals in Europe .
Harvey Ladew Williams , Jr. ( 1900 - 1986 ) was an American businessman who received induction into the National Order of the Legion of Honour in 1962 for 47 years of service to the French government .
Publius Ostorius Scapula ( died 52 ) was a Roman statesman and general who governed Britain from 47 until his death , and was responsible for the defeat and capture of Caratacus .
Johann Bayer ( 1572 -- 7 March 1625 ) was a German lawyer and uranographer ( celestial cartographer ) .
Christopher Columbus Rogers ( 1846 - -1888 ) was a controversial and colorful Texan marshal and gunfighter .
Henry Opitek ( January 6 , 1911-March 1981 ) became the first patient to survive open heart surgery in 1952 .
Baron Karl Clodt von Jürgensburg ( Russian : Карл Фёдорович Клодт фон Юргенсбург ; 1765 - 1822 ) was a general in the Imperial Russian Army during the Napoleonic Wars .

Henrik Kacser FRSE ( 22 September 1918 -- 13 March 1995 ) was a biochemist and geneticist .
Sir Walter Massy - Greene KCMG ( 6 November 1874 -- 16 November 1952 ) was an Australian politician and businessman .

Jakov Nenadović ( Serbian : Јаков Ненадовић ; 1765 -- 1836 ) was the first Serbian interior minister .

Kilambi Ramanujachari ( 1853 - -1928 ) , shortly K. Ramanujachari , was an Indian lawyer and administrator .
Jacques de Chambly ( died 1687 ) was from a French military background and became a seigneur in the New World and a governor of Acadia .
Renié Conley ( 31 July 1901 - 12 June 1992 ) was a prominent Hollywood costume designer .
Aedh Ailghin ( died 767 ) was the 22nd King of Uí Maine .
Avrom Yanovsky ( 1911 - -1979 ) was a Canadian editorial cartoonist .
Frank Negri ( 1 November 1918 -- 8 August 1994 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Minkhaung II ( Burmese : ဒုတိယ မင်းခေါင် ( dṵtḭja̰ mɪ́ɴɡàʊɴ ) ; 9 October 1446 -- 7 April 1501 ) was king of Ava from 1480 to 1501 .
Ned Kick ( 12 October 1904 -- 24 February 1991 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Robert Otway - Cave ( 1796 -- 29 November 1844 ) , styled The Honourable from 1839 , was a British politician .
Richard Hambro ( 1946 - 2009 ) was a British heir , investment banker , horsebreeder and philanthropist .
Angel Metodiev ( Angel Metodiev Angelov , Bulgarian : Ангел Методиев Ангелов ) ( 16 March 1921- 29 April 1984 ) was a Bulgarian fine art painter ( Classical Realism ) and teacher .
Enzo Fiermonte ( 17 July 1908 -- 22 March 1993 ) , sometimes credited as William Bird , was an actor and boxer .
Leonard Albert Wiseman OBE BSc ARI.C CText FTI ( 4 November 1915 - 24 Jan 2009 ) , organic chemist , scientific intelligence analyst and scientific administrator .
Walter McFarland ( 1945 -- 15 August 2014 ) was a Northern Irish footballer and coach , who played for Irish League side Crusaders during the 1960s and 70s .
Frances Kirby Smith ( 1785 - -1875 ) was the mother of U.S. Civil War general Edmund Kirby Smith and a confederate spy who orchestrated transport of mail and military intelligence to the Confederate troops .
Sir Francis Simon , ( 2 July 1893 -- 31 October 1956 ) , was a German and later British physical chemist and physicist who devised the method , and confirmed its feasibility , of separating the isotope Uranium-235 and thus made a major contribution to the creation of the atomic bomb .
Isokichi Komine ( 1866 -- 3 October 1934 ) was an Australian pearl diver , merchant , and trader .
Wallace Woodworth ( 1832 - -1882 ) was a wealthy businessman and rancher in Los Angeles County , California , in the 19th century .
Vangjel Meksi ( 1770 - -1821 ) was an Albanian physician , writer , and translator .
Elizabeth Gould Davis ( 1910 - -1974 ) was an American librarian who wrote a feminist book called The First Sex .
Prof Chaudry Mohammad Aslam ( 1900 - -1965 ) was a Pakistani mathematician and renowned cartographer .
Joseph Schipfer ( 8 April 1761 -- 27 January 1843 ) was a German landowner and vine producer , today mostly known for his creation of the language Communicationssprache .
Nicholas Ivor Gotham , known as Nic Gotham , ( 27 September 1959 -- 25 July 2013 ) was a Canadian jazz saxophonist and composer .

Nicholas E. Wagman ( 1905 -- 1980 ) was an American astronomer and astrometrist .
Jan Pauwel Gillemans the Elder ( 1618 , Antwerp -- 1675 , Antwerp ) , was a Flemish Baroque painter .
Jabez Turner ( 1828 - -1899 ) was a former Mayor of Sacramento , California .
Rev Robert Boog Watson BA FRSE ( 26 September 1823 -- 23 June 1910 ) was a Scottish malacologist and minister of the Free Church of Scotland best known as the author of the report on the Scaphopoda and Gastropoda collected during the H.M.S. Challenger expedition to survey the world 's oceans from 1873 - 1876 .
Aḥmad III Abū Yaʿfar ibn ʿAbd al - Malik al - Mustanṣir ( died 5 February 1146 ) , called Sayf al - Dawla ( `` Sword of the Dynasty '' ) , latinised as Zafadola , was the last ruler of the Hudid dynasty .

Pope Sylvester II or Silvester II ( c. 946 -- 12 May 1003 ) was Pope from 2 April 999 to his death in 1003 .
Thomas Beighton ( 25 December 1790 -- 14 April 1844 ) was an English Protestant Christian missionary who served with the London Missionary Society to the Chinese people of Malaysia in the early nineteenth century .
Andrew George Malcolm ( 1818 - -1856 ) was an Irish physician and medical historian , who was employed by the General Hospital in Belfast .
Rodolfo Ostromann ( 22 December 1903 -- 5 September 1960 ) was an Austrian professional footballer , who played as a striker .

John Henry Alexander ( 1812 - -March 2 , 1867 ) was a noted scientist and businessman , born in Annapolis , Maryland in 1812 .
Henry Godolphin ( 1648 - -1733 ) was a Provost of Eton College and Dean of St. Paul 's Cathedral in London , a position in which he clashed with Sir Christopher Wren in the period when the new cathedral had reached the finishing touches .
Ma Sicong ( Chinese : 馬思聰 ; pinyin : Mǎ Sīcōng ; Wade -- Giles : Ma Szu - ts'ung ; May 7 , 1912 -- May 20 , 1987 ) was a Chinese violinist and composer .
Edward Lawrence Levy ( born 21 December 1851 -- May 1932 ) was a British weightlifter .
Huitzilatzin ( or Huitzillatzin ) ( died in the year Seven Reed/1499 ) was the first tlatoani ( ruler ) of the pre - Columbian altepetl ( ethnic state ) of Huitzilopochco ( now Churubusco ) in the Valley of Mexico .
Seydi Ali Reis ( 1498 - -1563 ) , formerly also written Sidi Ali Reis and Sidi Ali Ben Hossein , was an Ottoman admiral .
Alfred Barnard Basset FRS ( 25 July 1854 -- 5 December 1930 ) was a mathematician working on algebraic geometry , electrodynamics and hydrodynamics .
Sir James Alfred Ewing KCB FRS FRSE MInstitCE ( 27 March 1855 − 7 January 1935 ) was a Scottish physicist and engineer , best known for his work on the magnetic properties of metals and , in particular , for his discovery of , and coinage of the word , hysteresis .
Al - Mansur Yahya ( died 976 ) was an imam of the Zaidi state in Yemen , whose tenure as imam is counted from 934 to 976 .
James Lord Bowes ( 21 June 1834 -- 27 October 1899 ) was a wealthy Liverpool ( UK ) wool broker , art collector and patron of the arts , author and authority on Japan and its art , and benefactor .
Larry Cunningham ( 13 February 1938 - 28 September 2012 ) was an Irish country music singer , who was one of the leading figures of the showband scene in the 1960s and 1970s .
William Thornhill ( c.1500 - -1557 ) , of Thornhill in Stalbridge , Dorset , was an English politician .
Ma'mun al - Hudaybi ( May 28 , 1921 -- January 8 , 2004 ) was the sixth General Guide of the Egyptian Muslim Brothers .
Girolamo Ruggieri ( 1662 - -1717 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .

Johannes Heer of Glarus ( 1489 - -1553 ) was a song composer and copyist , and later minister in the Reformed Church .
Alan Rowlands ( 1 March 1929 -- 2 January 2012 ) was an English pianist ( though born in Swansea , Wales ) who made notable contributions to British musical life both as a teacher and as a performer .
Jim Hitchmough ( 21 September 1934 -- May 1997 ) was a TV comedy writer , teacher and academic .
Sir George Sowley Holroyd ( 1758 - -1831 ) was an English lawyer and justice of the King 's Bench .
Eliyahu Speiser ( Hebrew : אליהו שפייזר‎ ; 23 March 1930 -- 12 November 2009 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment between 1977 and 1988 .
C. Kesavan ( 23 May 1891 -- 7 July 1969 ) was the Chief Minister of Travancore - Cochin during 1950 - -1952 .
Digby Willoughby , 7th Baron Middleton ( 29 November 1769 -- 5 November 1856 ) was an English nobleman and sailor , the eldest son of Francis Willoughby of Hesley and Octavia Fisher , and grandson of Thomas Willoughby .
Jumabek Ibraimov ( Жумабек Ибраимович Ибраимов ) ( 1 January 1944 -- 4 April 1999 ) was a Kyrgyz politician .

William de Brit was Sheriff of Connacht until his death at the battle of Termon MacGrath in 1247 .

Arthur Edmondston , M.D. ( 1776 - -1841 ) was a Scottish physician and writer on the Shetland Isles .
Joseph Ashby ( 1859 -- 1919 ) was an agricultural trade unionist born in Tysoe , Warwickshire , England .
Charles Constantine Pise , SJ , ( 1801 - -1866 ) was a Roman Catholic priest and writer .
John Alured ( 1607 - -1651 ) was an army officer who fought for the parliamentary cause in the English Civil War and was one of the regicides of King Charles I in 1649 .
Te Rata Mahuta ( 1877 - -1880 ? -- 1 October 1933 ) was the fourth Māori King , reigning from 1912 to 1933 .
Air Marshal Sir ( Alfred ) Clifford Sanderson KBE , CB , DFC ( 19 February 1898 -- 28 January 1976 ) was a British Royal Air Force officer who became Air Officer Commanding Far East Air Force .
Isaac ben Abba Mari ( c. 1122 -- c. 1193 ) was a Provençal rabbi and author of Ittur Soferim .
Polissena of San Macario ( died 1571 ) was an alleged Italian witch .
At age sixty - seven , Thomas Peter Lee died of a coronary occlusion on February 4 , 1939 , and he was buried at Glenwood Cemetery in Houston , two days later .
Percy Jeeves ( 5 March 1888 -- 22 July 1916 ) was a first - class cricketer from England , playing 50 matches for Warwickshire County Cricket Club from 1912 to 1914 .
Sir Thomas Glemham ( c. 1594 -- 1649 ) was an English soldier , landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1621 and 1625 .
Bert Pronk ( 24 October 1950 -- 15 March 2005 ) was a Dutch road cyclist who won the Tour de Luxembourg and Ronde van Nederland in 1977 .
Sonya Noskowiak ( 25 November 1900 - 28 April 1975 ) was an American photographer and member of the famous San Francisco photography collective Group f/64 that included Ansel Adams and Edward Weston .
Angelo Di Pietro J.U.D. ( 22 May 1828 -- 5 December 1914 ) was a Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church and Prefect of the Congregation of the Council .
Hellmuth Kneser ( 16 April 1898 -- 23 August 1973 ) was a Baltic German mathematician , who made notable contributions to group theory and topology .
Paul Erickson ( 22 November 1920 -- 27 October 1991 ) was a British screenwriter , most active in the 1950s and 1960s .
Imam - Quli Khan ( Persian : امامقلی خان‎‎، Emāmqolī Khan ) ( died 1633 ) was an Iranian military and political leader of Georgian origin who served as a governor of Fars , Lar and Bahrain for the shahs Abbas I and Safi .
John Patrick Morris ( 1894 - 31 July 1962 ) was a British Conservative Party politician who served as the Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Salford North from 1931 until 1945 .
George Malcolm - Smith ( 1901 - 1984 ) was an American novelist and jazz musicologist .
Joachim Lubomirski ( died 1610 ) was a Polish nobleman ( szlachcic ) .
Joe Lucy ( 2 February 1930 -- 21 July 1991 ) was a British boxer who was British lightweight champion between 1953 and 1955 and again between 1956 and 1957 .
Alfred Wainwright ( `` A.W. '' ) MBE ( 17 January 1907 -- 20 January 1991 ) was a British fellwalker , guidebook author and illustrator .
Subhashis Nag ( 14 August 1955 -- 22 December 1998 ) was an Indian mathematician who specialised in complex analytic geometry , particularly Teichmuller theory , and its relations to string theory .
Kaigetsudō Ando ( 壊月堂安度 , c. 1671 - -1743 ) , also known as Ando Yasunori , was a Japanese painter and the founder of the Kaigetsudō school of ukiyo - e art . Though influential and prolific , it is probable that many of the works attributed to him were painted by his disciples .
Iris Owens ( 1929 - 2008 ) , also known by her pseudonym Harriet Daimler , was an American novelist .
Johan Frederik ( Frits ) Nikolai Vermehren , also known as Frederik Vermehren , ( 12 May 1823 -- 10 January 1910 ) , Danish realistic genre and portrait painter , was born in Ringsted to glazier Peter Frederik Nikolai Vermehren and his wife Sofie Amalie .
Nageswara Rao Panditharadhyula ( 26 March 1912 - 13 November 1976 ) was a Telugu - language Indian journalist .
Nathaniel Elliot or Sheldon ( 1705 - 1780 ) , was an English Jesuit scholar .
Carl ( or Karl ) Heinrich Schultz ( 8 July 1798 in Altruppin -- 22 March 1871 ) , known as Carl Heinrich ' Schultzenstein ' Schultz , was a German physician and botanist .
Božidar Petranović ( 18 February 1809 -- 12 September 1874 ) was a Serbian author , scholar , journalist , and one of the leading historians of Serbian literature and a distinctive proponent of world literature .
Ivaniš Berislavić ( Latin : Joannes Berizlo ) was the Despot of the Kingdom of Serbia ( regni Rascie despotus ) from 1504 to 1514 .
Geordie Bourne ( or Burn ) ( died 1597 ) was a well - known thief or raider in the English East Marches land that bordered Scotland .
Edward Coke , Viscount Coke ( 2 February 1719 -- 31 August 1753 ) , styled The Hon . Edward Coke from 1728 to 1744 , was a British Member of Parliament .
Creighton Carvello ( 14 November 1944 -- 18 November 2008 ) was a British mnemonist .
Elsie Randolph ( 9 December 1904 -- 15 October 1982 ) was an English actress , singer and dancer .
Private Minnie Spotted - Wolf ( 1923 - -1988 ) was the first Native American woman to enlist in the United States Marine Corps .

Thrillville is a simulation and strategy video game that depicts theme park management , very similar to RollerCoaster Tycoon 3 , which Frontier Developments also developed .
Hidden Invasion is a video game designed by Toka .
Azure Dreams ( アザーライフ アザードリームス Azā Raifu Azā Dorīmusu ) , is a PlayStation video game developed by Konami and was originally released in Japan on November 13 , 1997 .
4th & Inches is an American football sports game by Accolade .
Thomas Ferguson Rodger CBE FRCP Glas FRCP Ed FRCPsych ( 4 November 1907 -- 1 June 1978 ) was a Scottish physician who was Professor of Psychological Medicine at the University of Glasgow from 1948 to 1973 , and Emeritus Professor thereafter .
Charles Martin Le Quesne , son of Charles Thomas Le Quesne , was educated at Shrewsbury School and Exeter College , Oxford .
Colin de Land ( 1955- 2003 ) was a New York art dealer who ran `` Vox Populi '' , and then American Fine Arts , Co. De Land studied philosophy and linguistics at New York University and founded the Armory Show .
Rose Ann Scamardella graduated from Marymount Manhattan College with a B.A. in sociology in 1968 .

Alain Badiou ( French : ( alɛ̃ badju ) ( listen ) ; born 17 January 1937 ) is a French philosopher , formerly chair of Philosophy at the École Normale Supérieure ( ENS ) and founder of the faculty of Philosophy of the Université de Paris VIII with Gilles Deleuze , Michel Foucault and Jean - François Lyotard .
Born in Bydgoszcz , Poland , Joanna Rajkowska studied painting at the Academy of Fine Arts in Kraków , Poland ( 1988 - -1993 ) , and art history at Jagiellonian University , Kraków , Poland ( 1988 - -1993 ) .
Adolphus Ypey or Adolphus Ypeus or Adolf Ypey ( 4 June 1749 , Franeker - 27 February 1822 , Leiden ) , was a Dutch botanist and Doctor of Philosophy and Medicine who graduated at the University of Franeker and stayed on to lecture in botany .

John Newbery ( 9 July 1713 -- 22 December 1767 ) , called `` The Father of Children 's Literature '' , was an English publisher of books who first made children 's literature a sustainable and profitable part of the literary market .
Norman Robert Campbell ( 1880 - -1949 ) was an English physicist and philosopher of science .
Christian Rohlfs ( November 22 , 1849 -- January 8 , 1938 ) was a German painter , one of the important representatives of German expressionism .

Julian Croft ( born 31 May 1941 ) is an Australian poet and Emeritus Professor of English , University of New England .

Hermann Baumgarten ( 28 April 1825 in Wolfenbüttel , Duchy of Brunswick -- 19 June 1893 ) was a German historian and a political publicist whose work had a major impact on liberalism during the unification of Germany .
Hugo Häring ( 11 May 1882 -- 17 May 1958 ) was a German architect and architectural writer best known for his writings on `` organic architecture '' , and as a figure in architectural debates about functionalism in the 1920s and 1930s , though he had an important role as an expressionist architect .
Eva Gonzalès ( April 19 , 1849 -- May 6 , 1883 ) was a French Impressionist painter .

Antoine Faivre ( born in Reims June 5 , 1934 ) is a prominent French scholar of Western esotericism .
Hans Steinhoff ( 10 March 1882 - 20 April 1945 ) was a German film director , best known for the films he made in the Nazi era .

Alfonso Sánchez Izquierdo ( born 1949 in Sidi Ifni ) is a Spanish journalist and broadcast executive .

Stanisław Trembecki ( 1739 - -1812 ) was a Polish Enlightenment poet , well known for his poems Na dzień siódmy września and Nadgrobek hajduka , which are said to have started a new trend in Polish political lyric poetry .

Barry Kelley ( August 19 , 1908 -- June 5 , 1991 ) was an actor on Broadway in the 1930s and ' 40s and in films during the 1940s , 1950s , and 1960s .

Edward Jackson Lowell ( October 18 , 1845 , Boston -- May 11 , 1894 , Cotuit , Massachusetts ) was a United States ( Massachusetts ) lawyer and historian .
David Stromeyer ( born 1946 ) is an American abstract sculptor who is best known for his large - scale , outdoor , painted steel sculptures .

Master D. M. L. is an unidentified German painter of the Renaissance period .

In 2004 he and several other astronomers discovered 30 supermassive blackholes at the European Astrophysical Virtual Observatory using pioneering techniques .

Plant 's gulella snail , scientific name Gulella plantii , is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .

Rhachidosoraceae is a family of ferns in the order Polypodiales .
The Cape dune mole - rat ( Bathyergus suillus ) is a species of solitary burrowing rodent in the family Bathyergidae .
The Tucumán mountain finch ( Compsospiza baeri ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
Dregea is a genus of vines in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus with this name in 1838 .
The Virgin Islands dwarf sphaero or Virgin Islands dwarf gecko ( Sphaerodactylus parthenopion ) is a species of gecko and also one of the smallest terrestrial vertebrates .
The Solomons white - eye or New Georgia white - eye ( Zosterops kulambangrae ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Bean yellow mosaic virus ( BYMV ) is a plant pathogenic virus in the genus Potyvirus and the virus family Potyviridae .
Anisolabididae is a family of earwigs , in the suborder Forficulina and the order Dermaptera .
The Niue rail ( Gallirallus huiatua ) is an extinct species of flightless bird in the Rallidae , or rail family .
The Durango salamander or pine woods salamander , Ambystoma silvense , is a mole salamander .
Metarctia is a genus of moth in the family Erebidae , subfamily of Arctiinae .
Tetragonoceras is an extinct prehistoric nautiloid genus from the nautilid family Tetragonoceratidae that lived during the Middle Devonian , found in Canada .
Fukuia is a genus of amphibious freshwater snails and land snails with an operculum , gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Stromateoidei is a suborder of the Perciformes , the largest order of fish .
Gahniacarus is a genus of flat mites in the family Tenuipalpidae , containing the following species :
Didymoglossum is a tropical genus of ferns in the family Hymenophyllaceae .
Hildegarde 's tomb bat ( Taphozous hildegardeae ) is a species of sac - winged bat in the family Emballonuridae .
Drimiopsis is a genus of African bulbous perennial herbs in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae , native to sub - Saharan Africa .
Hodotermes is a genus of African harvester termites in the Hodotermitidae .
Garantiana is a strongly ribbed , generally evolute ammonite from the Bajocian stage at the beginning of the Middle Jurassic , included in the family Stephanoceratidae .
The Sudan golden sparrow ( Passer luteus ) is a small bird in the sparrow family , found to the south of the Sahara Desert in Africa .
The Mullah spiny mouse ( Acomys mullah ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Djibouti , Eritrea , Ethiopia , and Somalia .
Phaeochoraceae is a family of sac fungi in the order Phyllachorales .
The Loria 's satinbird or velvet satinbird ( Formerly known as the Loria 's bird - of - paradise ) ( Cnemophilus loriae ) is a species of bird in the Cnemophilidae family .
In taxonomy , Pleurotaenium is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Placoderm desmids ( Desmidiaceae ) .
Palophaginae is a small beetle subfamily within the family Megalopodidae .
In taxonomy , Chaetomorpha , also called Chaeto for short , is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Cladophoraceae .
Bats are the second largest order of mammals ( after the rodents ) , representing about 20 % of all classified mammal species worldwide , with about 1,240 bat species divided into two suborders : the less specialized and largely fruit - eating megabats , or flying foxes , and the highly specialized and echolocating microbats .
Nozeba is a genus of very small , somewhat amphibious land snails that have a gill and an operculum , semi - terrestrial gastropod mollusks or micromollusk in the family Iravadiidae .
Micropterigoidea is the superfamily of `` mandibulate archaic moths '' , all placed in the single family Micropterigidae , containing currently about 20 living genera .
The Pediciinae are a subfamily of flies in the family Pediciidae , closely related to Tipulidae ( true craneflies ) .
Cnidoscolus is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1827 .
Taxodioideae is a subfamily in Cupressaceae .
According to APG II , the Asclepiadaceae is a former plant family now treated as a subfamily ( subfamily Asclepiadoideae ) in the Apocynaceae ( Bruyns 2000 ) .
Ayres 's hawk - eagle ( Hieraaetus ayresii ) , also referred to as Ayres ' eagle , is a medium - sized bird of prey in the family Accipitridae .
Cephalosporium gramineum or Hymenula cerealis is a plant pathogen that causes Cephalosporium Stripe of Wheat and other grasses .
Mecotetartus antennatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Mecotetartus .
The Sardinata tree frog , Hyloscirtus callipeza , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Colombia .
The African quailfinch , spectacled quailfinch , or white - chinned quailfinch ( Ortygospiza fuscocrissa ) , is a common species of estrildid finch found in eastern and southern Africa .
Alfred 's shieldback ( Alfredectes semiaeneus ) is a species of katydid that is widespread in the Western Cape and Eastern Cape of South Africa .
Ctenogobiops tangaroai , the Tangaroan shrimp - goby , is a species of goby of the family Gobiidae , native to the reefs of the Pacific Ocean where it can be found in fine - grained sand patches at depths of from 4 to 40 metres ( 13 to 131 ft ) .
Abbottella is a genus of operculate land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks gastropod in the family Pomatiidae .
The Bavispe sucker , in Mexican matalote del Bavispe ( Catostomus leopoldi ) , is a species of ray - finned fish in the Catostomidae family .
Palleon nasus nasus was initially described as Brookesia nasus in 1887 by Boulenger and reclassified as a Palleon species in 2013 .
The Malagasy kestrel ( Falco newtoni ) , also known as the Madagascar kestrel , Malagasy spotted kestrel , Newton 's kestrel , Madagascar spotted kestrel , katiti ( Creole ) or hitsikitsika ( Malagasy ) , is a small bird of prey of the genus Falco .
The Samoan flycatcher ( Myiagra albiventris ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Pholadomyidae is a taxonomic family of saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the order Pholadomyoida .
The Landdros moss frog ( Arthroleptella landdrosia ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
The Horus swift ( Apus horus ) is a small bird in the swift family .
The Oriental white - eye ( Zosterops palpebrosus ) is a small passerine bird in the white - eye family .
Conocoryphe is a genus of primarily eyeless trilobites belonging to the family Conocoryphidae .
According to Gerald Mayr , Diogenornis is best considered a stem - group member of the Rheidae .
The Indonesian speckled carpetshark , Hemiscyllium freycineti , is a species of bamboo shark in the family Hemiscylliidae .
According to ' The All - Species Living Tree ' Project Caldithrix is a member of Sphingobacteria , whereas the LPSN assigns it as an unclassified Deferribacterales and the NCBI considers it an unclassified Bacteria .
The Daurian jackdaw ( Corvus dauuricus ) is a bird in the crow family , Corvidae .
The Florida gar ( Lepisosteus platyrhincus ) is a species of gar found in the USA from the Savannah River and Ochlockonee River watersheds of Georgia and throughout peninsular Florida .
Campbellana is a genus of moths of the Carposinidae family , containing only one species , Campbellana attenuata .
The Stemonaceae are a family of monocotyledonous flowering plants placed in the order Pandanales .
Nepalorthogonius monilicornis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Nepalorthogonius .
Tylomyini is a tribe of New World rats and mice in the subfamily Tylomyinae .
Rutilia is a large genus of medium to large ( > 20 mm ) flies in the family Tachinidae native to Australia and the Oriental region .
The St. Michel nesophontes ( Nesophontes paramicrus ) is an extinct species of mammal in the family Nesophontidae .
The describers concluded that Xiongguanlong split off from the main branch of the Tyrannosauroidea before Appalachiosaurus , being the sister taxon of a clade consisting of Appalachiosaurus and the Tyrannosauridae .
Uncarina is a genus of plant in family Pedaliaceae found in Madagascar .
Wimmeria is a genus of shrubs to small trees in the family Celastraceae .
Amphitrema is a genus of testate amoeba in the family Amphitremidae .
Paphiopedilum , often called the Venus slipper , is a genus of the Lady slipper orchid subfamily Cypripedioideae of the flowering plant family Orchidaceae .
Butomus is the only known genus in the plant family Butomaceae , native to Europe and Asia .
Geocoris is a genus of insects in the family Geocoridae ( although in the past the geocorids were subsumed as a subfamily under the family `` Lygaeidae '' ) .
The Henderson reed warbler ( Acrocephalus taiti ) , also known as the Henderson reed - warbler , is a species of Old World warbler in the Acrocephalidae family .
Necepsia is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1910 .
The Malherbe 's parakeet or orange - fronted parakeet ( Cyanoramphus malherbi ) is a small parrot endemic to New Zealand .

Batistospora is a genus of fungi in the Ascomycota phylum .
Celtis tournefortii , commonly known as the ' oriental hackberry ' is a deciduous tree in the Celtis genus .
The Australian cockroach ( Periplaneta australasiae ) is a common species of tropical cockroach , with a length of 23 - -35 millimetres ( 0.91 - -1.38 in ) .
The Cape flat lizard ( Platysaurus capensis ) is a lizard in the Cordylidae family found in Namibia and South Africa .
Böhm 's bee - eater ( Merops boehmi ) is a species of bird in the Meropidae family .
Cripavirus is a genus of viruses in the order Picornavirales , in the family Dicistroviridae .
Monotoca is a genus of about 17 species of shrubs in the family Ericaceae .
Apodiphus is a genus of shield bugs belonging to the family Pentatomidae , subfamily Pentatominae .
Trialeurodes ( Greenhouse whitefly ) is a large genus of whiteflies in the family Aleyrodidae .
The Satyrini are a huge tribe of the Satyrinae , containing the graylings , ringlets , and allies .
Pacific bonito , Sarda chiliensis lineolata , is a marine species of bonito that is a game fighter but not highly thought of as a food fish .
The Mussau monarch ( Symposiachrus menckei ) , also known as the white - breasted monarch , is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Rhodocyclus is a genus of gram - negative bacteria from the family of Rhodocyclaceae which belongs to the class of Betaproteobacteria .
The Central Asiatic frog or Asian frog ( Rana asiatica ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family , found in China , Kazakhstan , and Kyrgyzstan .
The Hysteriaceae ( also known as Dothideomycetes , Ascomycotina , Eumycota ) are a taxonomic family of fungi and the only extant family belonging to the order Hysteriales .
The Luika barb ( Barbus luikae ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Salvadori 's teal or Salvadori 's duck ( Salvadorina waigiuensis ) is a species of bird endemic to New Guinea .
Acanthochelys is a genus of turtles , the spiny swamp turtles , in the family Chelidae , subfamily Chelinae , found in South America .
The Chinese shrew mole ( Uropsilus soricipes ) is a species of mammal in the family Talpidae .
The Kentucky coffeetree , Gymnocladus dioicus , is a tree in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae of the pea family Fabaceae , native to the Midwest and Upper South of North America .
Annesorhiza is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with about 12 to 15 species .
Peterson 's long - fingered bat ( Miniopterus petersoni ) is a bat in the genus Miniopterus which occurs in southeast Madagascar .
Senegalia montis - usti ( Brandberg Acacia ) is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Melozone is a genus of mostly neotropical birds in the Emberizidae family , found mainly in Mexico .
Osteoglossoidei are a suborder of the order Osteoglossiformes ( Latin : `` bony tongues '' ) that contains the butterflyfish , the arowanas and bonytongues , as well as extinct families .
The Siberian large - toothed shrew ( Sorex daphaenodon ) is a species of shrew .
Melanotaenia splendida splendida also known as the Eastern rainbowfish is a subspecies of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family endemic to Australia .
The Antilles catshark ( Galeus antillensis ) is a common but little - known species of catshark , part of the family Scyliorhinidae .
The Triplecross lizardfish ( Synodus macrops ) is a type of lizardfish that lives mainly in the Indo - West Pacific .
The Moluccan flycatcher or dark - grey flycatcher ( Myiagra galeata ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Aletomeryx is an extinct genus of Artiodactyla , of the family Palaeomerycidae , endemic to North America from the early Miocene epoch ( Hemingfordian stage ) 20.6 - -16.3 Ma , existing for approximately 4.3 million years .
The American redstart ( Setophaga ruticilla ) is a New World warbler .
In taxonomy , the Prasiolales are an order of green algae in the class Trebouxiophyceae .
Barley ( Hordeum vulgare L. ) , a member of the grass family , is a major cereal grain grown in temperate climates globally .
The Butiaba naked - tailed shrew ( Crocidura littoralis ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Aulodesmus is a genus of millipedes belonging to the family Gomphodesmidae .
The Sumatran laughingthrush ( Garrulax bicolor ) , also known as the black - and - white laughingthrush , is a member of the Leiothrichidae family .
The American dipper ( Cinclus mexicanus ) , also known as a water ouzel , is a stocky dark grey bird with a head sometimes tinged with brown , and white feathers on the eyelids that cause the eyes to flash white as the bird blinks .
The Zempoaltepec deer mouse ( Habromys lepturus ) , also known as the slender - tailed deer mouse , is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Dorcaschematini is a tribe of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae .
The Puerto Rican rock frog , Eleutherodactylus cooki , also known as the Puerto Rican cave - dwelling frog or rock coqui , and locally as coquí guajón , or guajón for brevity , is a threatened frog species from the coqui genus .
Apristomimus megacephalus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Apristomimus .
The Asian swamp eel , swamp eel , rice eel , or white ricefield eel ( Monopterus albus ) is a commercially important , air - breathing species of fish in the Synbranchidae family .
The Siberian grouse ( Falcipennis falcipennis ) is a medium - sized grouse .
Paramesotriton , or ( Asian ) warty newts , is a genus of salamanders in the Salamandridae family .
Ricardo 's squeaker ( Synodontis ricardoae ) is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Tanzania .
The London Underground mosquito is a form of mosquito in the genus Culex .
Green lacewings are insects in the large family Chrysopidae of the order Neuroptera .
Micrarionta is a genus of medium - sized air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
The Hispaniolan greater funnel - eared bat ( Natalus major ) is a species of funnel - eared bat found on the island of Hispaniola .
The European badger ( Meles meles ) is a species of badger in the family Mustelidae and is native to almost all of Europe and some parts of the Middle East .

Psettichthyini is a tribe of fish in the Pleuronectinae subfamily .
Neobernaya is a genus of tropical sea snail , cowries , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .

The Chuuk monarch , or Truk monarch ( Metabolus rugensis ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Prodeinotherium is an extinct representative of the family Deinotheriidae that lived in Africa , Europe , and Asia in the early and middle Miocene .
In 2010 , a new proposed classification system for the Bivalvia was published in by Bieler , Carter & Coan , revising the classification of the Bivalvia , including the subclass Heterodonta .
Hemichromis lifalili , common name blood - red jewel cichlid , is from a fish the family cichlidae .
Eusthenoceras is an Early Carboniferous nautiloid cephalopod with a large depressed , apically curved shell assigned to the Pseudactinoceratidae , ( previously ranked as the subfamily Pseudactinoceratinae ) .
Plesiothyreus is a genus of very small sea snails or limpets , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Phenacolepadidae .
Fruticicola is a genus of medium - sized , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Bradybaenidae .
The genus Compsognathus gives its name to the family Compsognathidae , a group composed mostly of small dinosaurs from the late Jurassic and early Cretaceous periods of China , Europe and South America .
Hoplocephalus is a genus of snakes in the Elapidae family .
The Amphibolurinae are a subfamily of reptiles ( more specifically , lizards ) in the family Agamidae .
Together with the bulk of the former Sparrmanniaceae , Grewia is in the subfamily Grewioideae and therein the tribe Grewieae , of which it is the type genus .

Lebeckia is a genus of legume in the Fabaceae family native to the fynbos ( Cape Floristic Kingdom ) of South Africa .
The Bear Lake whitefish Prosopium abyssicola is a salmonid fish endemic to Bear Lake on the Utah - Idaho border .
Xylothamia , the desert goldenrods , is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae .
Porolabium is a monotypic genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
N4likevirus is a genus of bacteriophages in the order Caudovirales , in the family Podoviridae .
In taxonomy , Methanoplanus is a genus of the Methanomicrobiaceae , comprising three species of methanogenic , or methane - producing , archaea .

The Gölçük toothcarp ( Aphanius splendens ) is an extinct species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
St. John 's keelback , Xenochrophis sanctijohannis , is a species of natricine snake , which is endemic to Asia .
The Annulatascaceae are a family of fungi in the class Sordariomycetes of the Ascomycota .
The Aural horned toad , Xenophrys auralensis , is a species of amphibian in the Megophryidae family .

Allognathus is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicidae , the true snails .

The Cooloola sedge frog or Cooloola tree frog ( Litoria cooloolensis ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
The Laysan duck ( Anas laysanensis ) , also known as the Laysan teal , is a dabbling duck endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Radde 's shrew ( Sorex raddei ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .

Vauquelinia , commonly known as the rosewoods , is a genus of the rose family Rosaceae .

Phausis is a genus of firefly beetles ( family Lampyridae ) .

The Csorba 's mouse - eared bat ( Myotis csorbai ) is a species of vesper bat .

The Pirre warbler ( Basileuterus ignotus ) is a species of bird in the Parulidae family .

The Aeolidida is a taxonomic clade of sea slugs , specifically aeolid nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Cladobranchia .

Stenostomidae are a family of the flatworm order Catenulida .
The Madagascan ibis ( Lophotibis cristata ) , also known as the Madagascar crested ibis , white - winged ibis or crested wood ibis , is a medium - sized ( approximately 50 cm long ) , brown - plumaged ibis .
Blighia is a genus of four species of flowering plants in the soapberry family , Sapindaceae , native to tropical Africa from Guinea east to Kenya .
Plebidonax deltoides ( previously Donax deltoides ) is a small , edible saltwater clam or marine bivalve mollusc of the family Donacidae , endemic to Australia .
Ocypode africana , commonly known as the African ghost crab , is a species of ghost crabs native to the eastern Atlantic coast of western Africa , from Mauretania to Namibia .
Cynarctoides is an extinct genus of terrestrial canine of the family Borophaginae and tribe Phlaocyonini which inhabited most of North America during the Whitneyan stage of the Early Oligocene to the Barstovian stage of the Middle Miocene 33.3 - -13.6 Mya existing approximately 19.7 million years .
Pillar coral ( Dendrogyra cylindrus ) is a hard coral ( order Scleractinia ) found in the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea .
Cephalaria is a genus of about 65 species of flowering plants in the family Caprifoliaceae , native to southern Europe , western and central Asia , and northern and southern Africa .
Hesperophanoschema hirsutum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Hesperophanoschema .
Robertsiella is a genus of freshwater snails which have a gill and an operculum , gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Danielea moelensis is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae , and the only species in the genus Danielea .
Gryllomorpha is a genus of cricket belonging to the family Gryllidae subfamily Gryllomorphinae .
Amberleyoidea is an superfamily of extinct , small to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda .
Austrochalcophora subfasciata is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Austrochalcophora .
Ovieda is a genus of flowering plant in the Lamiaceae family , first described for modern science in 1753 .

The Eustrotiinae are a subfamily of moths , under family Noctuidae .
The Javan trogon ( Apalharpactes reinwardtii ) is a species of bird in the Trogonidae family .

Pteris ( brake ) is a genus of about 280 species of ferns in the Pteridoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae .

Enneapterygius howensis , known commonly as the Lord Howe Island triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Lophopus is a genus of bryozoans from Lophopodidae family .
The Zambian barbet or Chaplin 's barbet ( Lybius chaplini ) is a bird species in the family Lybiidae , which was until recently united with the other barbets in the Capitonidae .
The type species of this genus is Palaeospheniscus patagonicus , the Patagonian slender - footed penguin .
Bison latifrons ( also known as the broad - headed paleo - bison , giant Ice Age bison or long - horned bison ) is an extinct species of bison that lived in North America during the Pleistocene epoch .

The Cucurbiteae is a tribe of the Cucurbitoideae subfamily , which is a member of the Cucurbitaceae family , or gourd family , of flowering plants .
The Karoo dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion karrooicum ) is a chameleon native to South Africa .

Phyllota is an Australian genus from the family Fabaceae , a biological grouping of flowering plants .

Dismegistus is a genus of true bugs belonging to the family Parastrachiidae .
The Finke River hardyhead ( Craterocephalus centralis ) is a species of fish in the Atherinidae family .
The Indian flapshell turtle ( Lissemys punctata ) is a freshwater species of turtle found in South Asia .
The Monte Escondido salamander ( Bolitoglossa decora ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Carpenter frog ( Rana virgatipes ) is a species of true frog found on coastal plain of the Atlantic coast of the United States between central New Jersey and northeastern Florida .
Ticocystiscus is a genus of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Cystiscidae .
Polystemma is a genus of flowering plants of the family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1844 .
Limnocharis is a genus in the Alismataceae , native to Mexico , Central America , the West Indies and South America ) but naturalized in China , India , and Southeast Asia as well .
Amphiuma is a genus of aquatic salamanders , the only extant genus within the family Amphiumidae /æmfɨˈjuːmɨdiː/.
Gasteria is part of the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , subfamily Asphodeloideae .
Lyrogoniatitinae is one of two subfamilies of the Cravenoceratidae family .
Common wheat ( Triticum aestivum ) , also known as bread wheat , is a cultivated wheat species .
Packera is a genus of about 64 species of plants in the composite family , Asteraceae .
Polyommatini is a tribe of lycaenid butterflies in the subfamily Polyommatinae .
Tropidacris is a genus of grasshopper in the family Romaleidae .
The Wood River sculpin ( Cottus leiopomus ) is a species of fish in the Cottidae family .
The Microascales are an order of fungi in the class Sordariomycetes , subclass Hypocreomycetidae .
Leiopotherapon is a genus of fish in the family Terapontidae , the grunters .
Projovellania is an extinct nautiloid cephalopod belonging to the oncocerid family Jovellaniidae found in mid Silurian sediments in Europe .
The Philippine leafbird ( Chloropsis flavipennis ) is a species of bird in the Chloropseidae family .
Laccobiini is a tribe in the subfamily Hydrophilinae of aquatic beetles , and it contains 367 species in 8 genera .
Oxycarenus is a genus of ground bugs belonging to the family Lygaeidae , subfamily Oxycareninae .
Corylopsis is a genus of nearly 30 species of shrubs in the witch hazel family , Hamamelidaceae , native to eastern Asia with the majority of species endemic in China but with some also in Japan , Korea , and the Himalayas .
The Oriente cave rat ( Boromys offella ) was a species of rodent in the family Echimyidae .
The Clydonitaceae is a superfamily in the ammonoid cephalopod order Ceratitida characterized by generally costate and turberculate shells with smooth , grooved , or keeled venters and sutures that are commonly ceratitic or ammonitic but goniatic in a few offshoots .
Roulletia is an extinct genus of sand sharks ( family Odontaspididae ) .
Succinea , common name the amber snails , is a genus of small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Succineidae .
Acrioceratidae is a family of heteromorph ammonites included in the Ancyloceratoidea comprising ancyloceratid - like forms that start off with a coiled juvenile section , followed by a straight or curved shaft ending in a hook .
Anthracoceratites is an extinct genus belonging to the of the Dimorphoceratidae family .
The Cape shoveler or Cape shoveller ( Anas smithii ) is a species of dabbling duck of the genus Anas .
Antaxius is a genus of ' katydids crickets ' belonging to the family Tettigoniidae .
The Argyrogrammatini are a tribe of moths in the subfamily Plusiinae , consisting of fifteen genera .
Metopocetus is an extinct genus of baleen whale belonging to the family Cetotheriidae .
Hydrotaea is a genus of insects in the housefly family , Muscidae .
Shiho 's seahorse ( Hippocampus sindonis ) is a species of fish in the Syngnathidae family .
Almites is a genus belonging to the Marathonitidae families .
Clohiesia is a genus of fungi in the family Annulatascaceae of the Ascomycota .
Casaleius ferrugineus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Casaleius .
Olyreae is a tribe of grasses in the bamboo subfamily ( Bambusoideae ) .
Platystega is an extinct genus of trematosaurian temnospondyl within the family Trematosauridae of Svalbard during the Triassic .
Blueberry shock virus ( BlShV ) is an Ilarvirus belonging to the Bromoviridae family .
The Philippine forest roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros obscurus ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Chordifex is a genus of plants in the Restionaceae described as a genus in 1998 .
Boenninghausenia is a monotypic plant genus in the family Rutaceae .
Sordes has been assigned to the family Rhamphorhynchidae .
Arhythmacanthidae are a family of parasitic worms from the order Echinorhynchida .
Segmentina is a genus of very small , air - breathing , freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Planorbidae , the ramshorn snails .
Pangora is a genus of moth in the family Arctiidae from Nepal , India and Sri Lanka .
The Pacific hagfish ( Eptatretus stoutii ) is a species of hagfish .
Regelia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Myrtaceae and is endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Aphananthe is a small genus of evergreen trees in the family Cannabaceae .
Aphania is a genus of trees and shrubs of the family Sapindaceae .
Nisoniades is a genus of tufted skippers in the family Hesperiidae .
The Tenasserim lutung ( Trachypithecus barbei ) is a species of lutung .
Abacaelostus filicornis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Abacaelostus .
István Drubina ( Slovak : Štefan Drubina , born August 17 , 1884 , date of death unknown ) was a Slovak track and field athlete who competed for Hungary in the 1908 Summer Olympics and in the 1912 Summer Olympics .
Bert Brinkman ( born April 4 , 1968 in Nijverdal ) is a retired water polo player from the Netherlands , who finished in ninth position with the Dutch team at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona .
Harald Hansen ( March 14 , 1884 in Copenhagen -- May 10 , 1927 in Aarhus ) was a Danish amateur football ( soccer ) player , who played as a defender for the Denmark national football team , with whom he won silver medals at the 1908 and 1912 Summer Olympics .
Bakhtiyar Tyleganov ( Бахтияр Тйлеганов ; born January 5 , 1976 ) is a retired boxer from Kazakhstan , who competed for his native country in the Men 's Featherweight ( -- 57 kg ) division at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , Georgia .
Lisa - Marie Deetlefs ( born 8 September 1987 ) is a South African field hockey player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
On 11 May , Dunga named Grafite among his 23-man 2010 FIFA World Cup squad .
George Cosac ( born 26 January 1968 ) is a former tennis player from Romania , who represented his native country in the doubles competition at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona .
Annabelle Euranie ( born September 4 , 1982 in Gonesse , France ) is a French judoka who competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics in the women 's half - lightweight division .
Luciano Zinali ( born 13 August 1943 ) is an Italian yacht racer who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics and in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Marija Nikolova ( Macedonian : Марија Николова ) is a Macedonian musician who entered Eurovision Song Contest 2000 as part of the group XXL with the song `` 100 % te ljubam '' with band mates Ivona Džamtovska , Rosica Nikolovska , and Verica Karanfilovska .
Natalie Titcume ( born 6 December 1975 in Sydney ) is a softball player from Australia , who won a bronze medal 2000 Summer Olympics and a silver medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
József Vágó ( born 1906 ) was a Hungarian football defender who played for Hungary in the 1934 FIFA World Cup .
Fausto Radici ( 24 September 1953 -- 14 April 2002 ) was an Italian former alpine skier who competed in the 1976 Winter Olympics .
Édouard Candeveau ( 11 February 1898 -- November 1989 ) was a Swiss rower who competed at the 1920 , 1924 and 1928 Summer Olympics .
Arvid Martin Hjalmar Lönnroth ( 11 September 1856 in Kungälv , Bohuslän -- 24 July 1935 in Göteborg ) was a sailor from Sweden , who represented his native country at the 1908 Summer Olympics in Ryde , Isle of Wight , Great Britain in the 8 Metre .
Gary Neist ( born November 1 , 1946 in Albert Lea , Minnesota ) is an American former wrestler who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Bohumil Janoušek ( or Bob Janousek ) ( born September 7 , 1937 ) is a Czech rower who competed for Czechoslovakia in the 1960 Summer Olympics and in the 1964 Summer Olympics , and later moved to Britain as a rowing coach and then a boat - builder .
José Fernando Bulnes Zelaya ( born 21 October 1946 ) aka Azulejo , is a retired Honduran football defender who played for Honduras in the 1982 FIFA World Cup .
Kimie Morita ( Japanese : 森田 貴美枝 ; born February 27 , 1958 ) is a Japanese former volleyball player who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics .
Ján Zachara ( Slovak pronunciation : ( ˈjaːn ˈzaxara ) ) ( born 27 August 1928 in Kubra near Trenčín , now Slovak Republic ) is a former Czechoslovak boxer who won the gold medal in the featherweight division at the 1952 Summer Olympics in Helsinki .
Lin Ying - chieh ( Chinese : 林英傑 ; pinyin : Lín Yīngjié ; born 1 May 1981 ) is a Taiwanese baseball player who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Birte Ove - Petersen was a Danish swimmer who won three medals at the 1938 European Aquatics Championships .
Knud Lundberg ( 14 May 1920 -- 12 August 2002 ) was a Danish multi - talented sportsperson , who most notably won a bronze medal with the Denmark national football team at the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Gao Ming Jie competed in the F44/46 javelin throw at the 2004 Summer Paralympics in Athens , Greece where he won the silver medal .
Otto Ferdinand Muller von Czernicki ( March 13 , 1909 in Magetan , Dutch East Indies -- 1998 ) was a Dutch field hockey player who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics .

Traudl Ruckser ( born 13 February 1925 ) is an Austrian former gymnast who competed in the 1948 Summer Olympics .
Gregor Grilc ( born 13 February 1970 in Šenčur ) is a Slovenian former alpine skier who competed in the 1992 Winter Olympics and 1994 Winter Olympics . His best result in the Alpine skiing World Cup are 6th and 8th place , both in slalom .
Edi Schild ( also Edy , born February 21 , 1919 ) is a Swiss cross - country skier who competed in the 1948 Winter Olympics .
Mari Saarinen ( born in Kangasala on July 30 , 1981 ) is a Finnish ice hockey forward She plays for IlvesTampere and appeared in the 2006 Winter Olympics .

Stefaan Maene ( born May 13 , 1972 in Ostend ) is a former backstroke and medley swimmer from Belgium , who competed for his native country at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona , Spain .

David Pichler ( born September 3 , 1968 ) is an American Olympic diver representing the United States in 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta and in the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney , where Pichler was elected team captain .

Marcel Fischer ( born 14 August 1978 in Biel / Bienne ) is a Swiss fencer who competed in the Men 's Épée Individual at the 2004 Summer Olympics and won the gold medal .

Gintautas Umaras ( born May 20 , 1963 in Kaunas ) is a retired track and road racing cyclist from Lithuania , who represented the USSR at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , South Korea .

Jesús Moraila Morales ( born 1901 in Culiacán , Sinaloa , date of death unknown ) was a Mexican sprinter who competed in the 1928 Summer Olympics and in the 1932 Summer Olympics .

Susan Wessels - Webber ( born 12 November 1977 in Bloemfontein , Free State ) is a field hockey player from South Africa who represented her country at the 2000 and 2004 Summer Olympics .
Maria Lamb ( born January 4 , 1986 , in St. Paul , Minnesota ) is an Olympic speed skater from River Falls , Wisconsin , who competed in 1500 m and the team pursuit at the 2006 Winter Olympics .

Marianne Vermaat ( born 2 May 1955 ) is a former backstroke swimmer from the Netherlands , who competed for her native country at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich , West Germany .

The single species composing the genus is Protarum sechellarum .
Elephant seals are large , oceangoing earless seals in the genus Mirounga .

Sciota hostilis is a species of snout moth in the genus Sciota .
