Melinis repens is a species of grass known by the common names rose Natal grass , or simply Natal grass , and Natal red top .
Gnamptogenys coxalis is a species of ant of the subfamily Ectatomminae , which can be found from Borneo , Sri Lanka , India , and Nicobar Islands .
Parabuccinum is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Buccinulidae .
Arum palaestinum is a species of flowering herbaceous perennial plant in the family Araceae , also known as Black Calla , Solomon 's Lily , Priest 's Hood , Kardi and Palestine Arum .
Ribes colandina is a species of currant found only in Perú .
Agaricus lilaceps , also known as the cypress Agaricus or the giant cypress agaricus is a species of mushroom .
Tylopilus piniphilus is a bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae found in Yunnan , China , where it grows under the conifer species Pinus yunnanensis and P. densata .
Zabrus apfelbecki is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is endemic to Bosnia and Herzegovina .
Jasminum mesnyi ( primrose jasmine or Japanese jasmine ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Oleaceae , native to Vietnam and southern China ( Guizhou , Sichuan , Yunnan ) .
Stanfieldiella is genus of flowering plants within the Commelinaceae family , first described in 1960 .
Gilbertidia is a genus of fatheads native to the northern Pacific Ocean .
The order Diplura is one of the four groups of hexapods , alongside insects , springtails and Protura .
Conus marchionatus , common name the Marquesas cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Cystopteris montana is a species of fern known by the common name mountain bladderfern .
Bulimulus hoodensis is a species of land snail in the family Bulimulidae .
Kyrinion is an extinct genus of baphetid tetrapod from the Late Carboniferous of England .
Austrophyllolepis is an extinct genus of phyllolepid arthrodire placoderm from Middle to Late Devonian freshwater strata of Australia .
Perca fluviatilis , commonly known as the European perch , perch , redfin perch or English perch , is a predatory species of perch found in Europe and northern Asia .
Acanthogobius is a genus of gobies native to marine , fresh and brackish waters of eastern Asia .
Nebria aenea aenea is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Altai , Russia .
Dudleya virens , the Green liveforever or Bright green dudleya , is an uncommon species of perennial , succulent plant in the family Crassulaceae , native to several coastal southern California and Baja California locations .
Amphigerontia contaminata is a species of Psocoptera from Stenopsocidae family that can be found in England , and sometimes Ireland .
Tinognathus parviceps is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Tinognathus .
Capnoides sempervirens is the only species in the genus Capnoides .
Cupressus forbesii , now reclassified by some as Hesperocyparis forbesii , and with the common names Tecate cypress or Forbes ' cypress , is a species of cypress native to southwestern North America .
Syntrophobacter sulfatireducens is a species of bacteria notable for degrading propionate .
Agabus sturmii is a species of beetle native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) and the Near East .
Isopogon fletcheri is a rare shrub species that is endemic to the Blue Mountains in New South Wales , Australia .
Xanthophryne koynayensis ( common names : Humbali Village toad , chrome - yellow toad , Koyna toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Sarcocapnos ( Greek sárx `` flesh '' , kapnós `` smoke '' ) is a genus of at least 6 species of somewhat fleshy , cushion - forming annual to perennial plants , native to cliffs in the French Pyrenees , Spain , and north Africa .
Rayella is a genus of parasitic protozoa of belonging to the phylum Apicomplexia .
Chasmatophyllum is a genus of succulent plants native to the Karoo mountains of South Africa .
†Graecoanatolica macedonica is an extinct species of small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Xanthoparmelia nana is a lichen species in the genus Xanthoparmelia found in Western Australia .
Trichocline is a genus of Australian and South American plants in the gerbera tribe within the daisy family .
Neocrepidodera corpulenta is a species of flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Albania , Bulgaria , France , Italy , Romania , and in all states of former Yugoslavia .
Hemiscyllium galei ( Cenderwasih epaulette shark ) is a species of bamboo shark in the family Hemiscylliidae .
Carex vernacula is a species of sedge known by the common name native sedge .
Cryolophosaurus ( /ˌkraɪoʊˌloʊfoʊˈsɔːrəs/ or /kraɪˌɒloʊfoʊˈsɔːrəs/ ; `` CRY - oh - loaf - oh - SAWR - us '' ) is a genus of large theropods known from only a single species Cryolophosaurus ellioti , known from the early Jurassic period of Antarctica .
Nelson 's milksnake ( Lampropeltis triangulum nelsoni ) is a subspecies of king snake that is found in Mexico from southern Guanajuato and central Jalisco to the Pacific Coast .
Deroplatys moultoni is a species of praying mantis in the genus Deroplatys in the order Mantodea .
Labyrinthus chiriquensis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Labyrinthus .
Ktenoura is a genus of trilobite from the Silurian of Europe .
Pseudaelurus stouti ( originally described as Lynx stouti ) also from the Early and Late Barstovian was a very small and slender form of the genus .
Penstemon eatonii is a species of penstemon known by the common name firecracker penstemon .
Polystichum lonchitis is a species of fern known by the common name northern hollyfern , or simply holly - fern .
Morcocytius is a genus of hawkmoths containing only one species , Morcocytius mortuorum , which is known from Brazil , Ecuador , Peru and Bolivia .
Tripneustes ventricosus , commonly called the West Indian sea egg or white sea urchin , is a species of sea urchin .
Epityches is a genus of clearwing ( ithomiine ) butterflies , named by d'Almeida in 1938 .
Cephalotes fossithorax is a species of arboreal ant of the genus Cephalotes , characterized by an odd shaped head and the ability to `` parachute '' by steering during a fall .
Penicillium rubefaciens is a species of the genus of Penicillium which has been isolated from sandy soil .
The chachalacas , guans and curassows are birds in the family Cracidae .
Parmops is a genus of flashlight fishes found in the deep waters of the central Pacific Ocean .
Boucardicus carylae is a species of land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Cyclophoridae .
Stanhopea cirrhata is a species of orchid endemic to Central America ( Costa Rica , Honduras , Nicaragua and Panama ) .
Anoplosaurus ( meaning `` unarmored or unarmed lizard '' ) is an extinct genus of herbivorous nodosaurid dinosaur , from the late Albian - age Lower Cretaceous Cambridge Greensand of Cambridgeshire , England .
Nebria piperi is a species of beetle from Carabidae family that can be found in Canada and the US state of Washington .
Rhinoraja , the jointnose skates , is a genus of skates in the family Rajidae .
Ornithosuchidae is an extinct family of reptiles from the Triassic period that were distantly related to crocodilians .
Tyson belos ( Tyson 's wriggler or arrow wriggler ) is a species of fish in the monotypic genus Tyson of the Xenisthmidae ( wriggler ) family .
Ephippidae is a family containing the spadefishes , with about eight genera and a total of 20 marine species .
Atrophaneura zaleucus is a species of butterfly from the family Papilionidae that is found in Burma .
Cryptocellus is an arachnid genus in the order Ricinulei .
The Diaphanopterodea or Paramegasecoptera are an extinct order of moderate to large - sized Palaeozoic insects .
Acropora jacquelineae is a species of acroporid coral found in the eastern Indian Ocean and the central and western Pacific Ocean .
Callulina dawida , also known as Taita warty frog , is a species of frog in the Brevicipitidae family .
Anotopterus vorax or south ocean daggertooth is a species of daggertooth .
Euprymna hoylei is a species of bobtail squid native to the tropical waters of the Indo - Pacific , specifically the western Pacific Ocean and northwestern Australia .
Streptomyces cheonanensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from radish growing soil in Cheonan in Korea .
Australopithecus sediba is a species of Australopithecus of the early Pleistocene , identified based on fossil remains dated to about 2 million years ago .
Cantharolethrus luxerii is a species of stag beetle .
Notoraja is a genus of skates in the family Rajidae , with these currently recognized species :
Porites is a genus of stony coral ; they are SPS ( Small Polyp Stony ) corals .
Moehringia macrophylla is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name largeleaf sandwort .
The Vegas Valley leopard frog ( Rana fisheri ) is a species of frog previously declared extinct .
Ganoderma brownii is a species of polypore fungus in the Ganodermataceae family .
Gourmya gourmyi , common name the Gourmya Cerith , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cerithiidae .
Xyris tennesseensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the family Xyridaceae known by the common name Tennessee yellow - eyed grass .
Laudonia is an extinct genus of trilobites that lived during the early part of the Botomian stage , which lasted from approximately 524 to 518.5 million years ago .
Platylestes praemorsus is a damselfly species in the family Lestidae .
Macrurocyttus acanthopodus , the dwarf dory , is a species of tinselfish native to the western Pacific Ocean where it has been found in the waters around the Philippines and Australia at a depth of around 878 metres ( 2,881 ft ) .
Tieghemella africana is a tree species of the genus Tieghemella in the plant family of the Sapotaceae .
Athous curtus is a species of click beetle from Elateridae family which is endemic to Western Caucasus .
Platycnemis acutipennis , known as the Orange Featherleg or the Orange White - legged Damselfly , is a species of damselfly in the family Platycnemididae .
Gymnodactylus is a genus of Brazilian geckos , commonly known as naked - toed geckos .
Pavoclinus laurentii , the Rippled klipfish , is a species of clinid found from Inhambane , Mozambique to Port Alfred , South Africa where it prefers weed - grown tide pools .
The American woodcock ( Scolopax minor ) , sometimes colloquially referred to as the timberdoodle , is a small chunky shorebird species found primarily in the eastern half of North America .
Agathis zamunerae is an extinct species of tree in the genus Agathis from early and middle Eocene rainforest paleofloras of Patagonia , Argentina around 52.2 million years ego .
Gymnocephalus is a genus of perches native to Western Eurasia .
Spermatodus is an extinct genus of prehistoric coelacanth , or lobe - finned fish .
Ancalomicrobium adetum is a bacteria from the family of Hyphomicrobiaceae and the only species in the genus Ancalomicrobium .
Stenodactylus doriae , commonly known as the Middle Eastern short - fingered gecko or Doria 's comb - fingered gecko , is a species of lizard in the family Gekkonidae .
Krigia wrightii , known as Wright 's dwarfdandelion , is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Cuapetes is a genus of shrimp in the family Palaemonidae , comprising the following species :
Padilla javana is the only species of jumping spider in the genus Padilla which occurs on Java , with most others found in Madagascar , and one in China .
Tegula pfeifferi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tegulidae . Tegula pfeifferi is more commonly known as `` Pfeiffer 's Top Shell '' .
Nuphar advena ( spatterdock or cow lily or yellow pond - lily ) is a species of Nuphar native throughout the eastern United States and at least some parts of Canada , such as Nova Scotia .
Spathoptera albilatera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Spathoptera .
Schizopygopsis is a genus of cyprinid fish found in rivers of Asia .
Calopteryx angustipennis is a species of damselfly in the family Calopterygidae known commonly as the Appalachian jewelwing .
Furcina is a small genus of sculpins native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean from around Japan and the Republic of Korea .
Florideophyceae , demoted to subclass Florideae in some classification systems , is a class of red algae .
Phlyctenanthus australis , common names red anemone and southern anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Actiniidae .
Macrosiphoniella yomogifoliae is an aphid species .
Limnonectes poilani is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family from eastern Cambodia and southern Vietnam .
Cacozelia neotropica is a species of snout moth in the genus Cacozelia .
Philodryas is a genus of colubrid snakes endemic to South America , commonly called green snakes .
Syringophilidae is a family of mites , containing the following genera :
Altiphrynoides is a genus of toads , commonly referred to as Ethiopian toads .
The upright snottygobble ( Persoonia longifolia ) , also known as the long - leaf persoonia or just snottygobble , is a species of tall shrub or small tree in the plant genus Persoonia , reaching 1 to 5 metres ( 3 - -17 ft ) in height .
Apodachlya is a genus of water mold within the order Leptomitales .
Xyris platylepis , the tall yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plants in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Cancrocaeca xenomorpha is a species of troglobitic ( cave - dwelling ) freshwater crab from Sulawesi , the only species in the monotypic genus Cancrocaeca .
Anthemis is a genus of aromatic flowering plants in the family Asteraceae , closely related to Chamaemelum , and like that genus , known by the common name chamomile ; some species are also called dog - fennel or mayweed .
Conus clarus , common name the glossy cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Telmatobius espadai , also known as the Inquisivi water frog , is a species of frog in the Telmatobiidae family , one of fourteen species of Telmatobius water frogs endemic to Bolivia .
Almadasuchus is an extinct genus of crocodylomorph known from the early Late Jurassic ( early Oxfordian stage ) Puesto Almada Member of the Cañadón Asfalto Formation of Patagonia , Argentina .
Helianthus laevigatus is a North American species of sunflower known by the common name smooth sunflower .
Crocus graveolens is a species of flowering plant in the genus Crocus of the family Iridaceae , found from south Turkey to Northern Israel .
Conus consors , common name the singed cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Brachylaima is a genus of trematode helminth that , it has recently been discovered , can infect the gastrointestinal tract of human beings .
Gyalecta is a genus of fungi within the Gyalectaceae family .
Lilium formosanum , also known as the Formosa lily or Taiwanese lily ( simplified Chinese : 台湾百合 ; traditional Chinese : 台灣百合 ; pinyin : Táiwān bǎihé ) , is a plant species in the lily family , endemic to Taiwan .
Palacanthilhiopsis is a genus of very small or minute freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Moitessieriidae .
Geranosaurus ( meaning `` sloth reptile '' ) is a genus of ornithischian dinosaur from the Early Jurassic .
Kikiki is a genus of fairyfly wasps containing a single species , Kikiki huna , known from Hawaii , Costa Rica , and Trinidad .
Aphelocephala is a genus of bird in the thornbill family Acanthizidae .
Hippuris , the Mare 's tail , was previously the sole genus in the family Hippuridaceae .
Panulirus homarus is a species of spiny lobster that lives along the coasts of the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Euprymna penares is a species of bobtail squid native to waters of the Indo - Pacific ; its exact distribution is unknown .
Coccinella is the most familiar genus of ladybird ( or , in North America , ladybug ) .
Eomys is an extinct genus of eomyid rodent from the late Oligocene of France , Germany , Spain , and possibly Turkey .
Scabiosa ochroleuca , commonly called cream pincushions or cream scabious , is a species of scabious with creamy yellow flower heads .
Castanea sativa , or sweet chestnut , is a species of flowering plant in the family Fagaceae , native to Europe and Asia Minor , and widely cultivated throughout the temperate world .
Diplodus cervinus , commonly known as the zebra seabream , is a species of seabream belonging to the family Sparidae .
Puck pinnata is a species of dreamer known only from the northwest Pacific Ocean .
Argonectes is a genus of halftooths from tropical South America .
Acapnolymma sulcaticeps is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acapnolymma .
Peachia cylindrica is a large species of sea anemone in the family Haloclavidae .
Calycadenia fremontii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Frémont 's western rosinweed ( after John C. Frémont ) .
Arophyteae is a tribe in the Araceae family .
Physalia is a genus of the order Siphonophora , colonies of four specialized polyps and medusoids that drift on the surface of the Atlantic , Indian and Pacific oceans .
Leontodon taraxacoides is a species of hawkbit known by the common name lesser hawkbit , rough hawkbit , or hairy hawkbit .
Meum athamanticum is a glabrous , highly aromatic ( aroma compound ) , perennial plant - the only species ( monotypic ) in the genus Meum , belonging to the family Apiaceae . Common names in the U.K. include Baldmoney , Spignel,(also Spiknel and Spikenel ) and Meu .
Carex multicostata is a species of sedge known by the common name manyrib sedge .
Onchidorididae are a taxonomic family of sea slugs , dorid nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Onchidoridoidea .
The Irapeao 's Cypripedium or Pelican Orchid ( Cypripedium irapeanum ) is a species of orchid .
Camarophyllopsis is a genus of 26 species of fungi with a widespread distribution , especially in northern temperate areas .
Euphorbia decaryi is a species of plant in the Euphorbiaceae family endemic to Madagascar .
The Flores green pigeon ( Treron floris ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Tagiades menaka , commonly known as the Spotted Snow Flat or the Dark - Edged Snow Flat , is a species of spread - winged skipper butterflies .
Kiisortoqia soperi is a species of arthropod from the Early Cambrian Sirius Passet Lagerstätte in Greenland .
Hepatus epheliticus , known by various names , including the calico crab ( not to be confused with Ovalipes ocellatus ) and Dolly Varden crab , is a species of crab .
Tramea basilaris , also known as the keyhole glider or wheeling glider , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
The Seminole siltsnail or Seminole spring snail , scientific name Floridobia vanhyningi , is a species of small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Onchidoridoidea is a taxonomic superfamily of sea slugs , dorid nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs .
Crataegus marshallii is a species of hawthorn known by the common name parsley haw .
Mammillaria duwei is a species of flowering plant in the cactus family .
Dasycottus setiger , the Spinyhead Sculpin , is a species of fathead native to the northern Pacific Ocean .
Cirrhopetalum maculosum is an orchid species in the genus Cirrhopetalum .
Palaeobenthesicymus is an extinct genus of prawns which existed in what is now Lebanon in the Late Santonian .
Indomyrma is an Asian genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Astragalus ripleyi is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Ripley 's milkvetch .
Tachysphex pechumani is a species of wasp in the family Crabronidae .
Lasius brunneus is a species of ant in the genus Lasius .
Liaochelys is an extinct genus of macrobaenid turtle which existed in western Liaoning , China during the early Cretaceous epoch .
Aluta is a genus of small shrubs in the family Myrtaceae .
Ionopsis ( violet orchid ) is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Iva axillaris , called povertyweed or death weed , is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Gasteracantha sturi , commonly known as the blunt - spined kite spider is a species of spider belonging to the family Araneidae .
Amphisbaena alba , also known as the red worm lizard or less commonly as the white or white - bellied worm lizard , is a species of amphisbaenian in the reptilian order Squamata .
Scoliopus bigelovii is a species of flowering plant in the lily family known by several common names , including California fetid adderstongue , Bigelow 's adderstongue , slinkpod , and brownies .
Guibourtia conjugata is a species of small to medium sized trees from Fabaceae family that can be found in Mozambique , Zambia and Zimbabwe .
Hexinlusaurus is a genus of basal ornithischian dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic of China .
Inermocoelotes microlepidus is a funnel - web spider species found in Italy , Bulgaria and Macedonia .
Oecomys trinitatis , also known as the long - furred oecomys , long - furred rice rat , Trinidad arboreal rice rat , or big arboreal rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oecomys of family Cricetidae .
Didymodon mamillosus , commonly known as Perthshire beardmoss , is a species of moss endemic to Europe .
Sturisoma monopelte is a species of armored catfish endemic to Guyana where it occurs in the Rupununi River basin .
Chaetobranchopsis is a small genus of cichlid fishes from South America , where they are found in the Amazon , Paraná and Paraguay river basins .
Pleioptygma is a genus of large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Muricoidea .
Castilleja praeterita is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name Salmon Creek Indian paintbrush .
Erosaria citrina , common name the orange cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Agnorhiza elata ( syn . Wyethia elata ) is a species of flowering plants known by the common name Hall 's mule 's ears .
Pantherodes colubraria , common name blotched leopard , is a species of moth in the family Geometridae .
Palpares libelluloides is a species of antlion in the genus Palpares belonging to the Myrmeleonidae family .
Psilophytites is a form genus of extinct plants ; it was created by Høeg for spiny stems ( axes ) which can not be assigned to a more precise genus or species , usually because spore - forming organs or sporangia are not present .
Entoloma austroprunicolor is a species of agaric fungus in the family Entolomataceae .
Rhododendron annae ( 桃叶杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to central and western Guizhou and western Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 1200 - -3000 meters .
Stellatospora is a genus of fungi within the Sordariaceae family .
Perilampsis decellei is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Perilampsis of the family Tephritidae .
The Sangha forest robin ( Stiphrornis erythrothorax sanghensis ) is a subspecies of the forest robin that is endemic to south - western Central African Republic , but may also occur in adjacent parts of DR Congo , Cameroon and Republic of the Congo .
Lythrypnus is a genus of gobies native to the Atlantic and Pacific coasts of the Americas including Cocos Island and the Galapagos Islands .
Calamospondylus ( meaning `` quill vertebrae '' ) was a theropod dinosaur genus .
Echeveria elegans ( Mexican snow ball , Mexican gem , white Mexican rose ) is a species of flowering plant in the Crassulaceae family , native to semi - desert habitats in Mexico .
Rhytida patula is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Rhytididae .
Conus vidua , common name the vidua cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Allocota viridipennis is a species of either brownish - green or reddish - blue coloured ground beetle in the Lebiinae subfamily that can be found in such Indonesian islands as Borneo , Java and Sumatra .
Paracanthocobitis pictilis also known as the Ataran zipper loach is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Paracanthocobitis .
Bromus pubescens , common name hairy woodland brome or hairy wood chess , is a grass species found across much of the eastern and central United States , as well as in Arizona , Québec and Ontario .
Diospyros attenuata is a species of tree in the ebony family , Ebenaceae .
Turturoena , commonly called bronze - naped pigeon , is a pigeon subgenus comprising three species : the eastern bronze - naped pigeon , the western bronze - naped pigeon , and the São Tomé bronze - naped pigeon .
Componocancer roberti is an unusual species of fossil crab described in 2008 .
Pimenta pseudocaryophyllus , popularly known as cataia , craveiro or louro - cravo , is a species from the Myrtaceae family largely distributed in pantropical and subtropical regions ( Paula et al . , 2012 ) .
Laminacauda plagiata is a species of sheet weaver found in Argentina , Chile and the Falkland Islands .
Trochus radiatus , common name the radiate top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .

Bunocephalus coracoideus , the guitarrito , is a species of banjo catfish found in the Amazon River basin .
The Christmas thrush ( Turdus poliocephalus erythropleurus ) , ia a subspecies of the island thrush ( Turdus poliocephalus ) .
Plagiantha is a genus of Brazilian plants in the grass family .
Aleurodicus rugioperculatus ( known variously as the rugose spiraling whitefly , the gumbo limbo spiraling whitefly or just the spiraling whitefly ) is a species of whitefly found throughout the Florida Keys .

Ophiodermatidae are a family of brittle stars in the suborder Ophiurina .
Trithemis pluvialis , the river dropwing , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Leptoglanis xenognathus is a species of loach catfish found in the Congo River Basin in the countries of the Central African Republic and the Democratic Republic of Congo .
Locha hyalina is a moth species in the family Geometridae from Central and parts of Southern America .
Floscopa is a genus of plant in family Commelinaceae first described in 1790 .
Acmaeops pratensis is a species of the Lepturinae subfamily in the long - horned beetle family .
Haplochromis nubilus , the Blue Victoria Mouthbrooder , is a species of cichlid found in several lakes and stream in eastern and central Africa .
Rubus spectabilis ( salmonberry ) is a species of brambles in the rose family , native to the west coast of North America from west central Alaska to California , inland as far as Idaho .
The order Ricinulei is a group of arachnids known as hooded tickspiders , though they are not true spiders .
Brasiliorchis gracilis ( syn . Maxillaria gracilis ) is a species of orchid ( family Orchidaceae ) native to eastern and southern Brazil .
Paracetopsis is a genus of whale catfishes found in tropical South America .
Ophiociliomyces is a genus of fungi within the Meliolaceae family .
Plantago maritima ( common names sea plantain , seaside plantain , goose tongue ) is a species of Plantago , family Plantaginaceae .
Spirometra is a genus of Pseudophyllid cestode that reproduces in canines and felines but which can cause pathology in humans .
Marcgravia evenia is a species of flowering vine in the family Marcgraviaceae .
Araneus mitificus , commonly known as the kidney garden spider or pale orb weaver , is a species of orb - weaver spider found in South , East , and Southeast Asia .
Comandra is a monotypic genus containing the single species Comandra umbellata .
Clostridium is a genus of Gram - positive bacteria , which includes several significant human pathogens , most notably the causative agent of botulism .
Laidleria is an extinct genus of unusual armored temnospondyl from Early Triassic of South Africa .
Paraptenodytes brodkorbi is a proposed , but possibly invalid , species of extinct penguin .
Festuca frederikseniae is a species of grass native to Greenland , Newfoundland , Labrador , and to a few islands in eastern Québec ( Mingan Archipelago and Anticosti Island ) .
Azorella macquariensis , also known as Macquarie Azorella or Macquarie Cushions , is a species of cushion plant endemic to Australia 's subantarctic Macquarie Island .
Dianchungosaurus is an extinct genus of mesoeucrocodylian crocodylomorph from the Early Jurassic of China .
Semisulcospira libertina is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Semisulcospiridae .
Brachytarsomys is a genus of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Metallonupserha metallescens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Metallonupserha .
Balanerpeton is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Visean stage of the Early Carboniferous period .
Oxyloma elegans is a species of small European land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk belonging to the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
In 1898 , Nocard and Roux were the first to isolate a mycoplasma species in culture from bovine , however it was n't until 1944 when Mycoplasma pneumoniae , known then as Eaton agent or Eaton 's agent , was isolated and described from a patient with primary atypical pneumonia .
Oxyopsis is a genus consisting of 11 species of mantises in the subfamily Stagmatopterinae .
Hydrellia geniculata is a species of fly in the family Ephydridae .
Acnodon is a genus of serrasalmids found in South America , with three recognized species :
Streptomyces cyaneofuscatus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Daghestan in Russia .
Celtedens is an extinct genus of albanerpetontid amphibian from the Late Cretaceous of Spain , Early Cretaceous of England , and the Late Jurassic of Portugal .
Raillardella scaposa is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name stem raillardella .
Epithelantha ( button cactus ) is a genus of cactus that is native to northeastern Mexico , and in an area from western Texas to Arizona .
Ptychomitrium is a widespread genus of mosses found in many parts of the world .
Solmissus is a genus of jellyfish , the dinner plate jellies .
The Menthidae are a small family of pseudoscorpions that are nevertheless spread around the world .
Eucomis pallidiflora ( giant pineapple lily ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae , native to South Africa .
Enyalioides binzayedi is a species of lizard in the genus Enyalioides known from only one location in the Cordillera Azul National Park in Peru .
Pseudeutropius is a genus of the family Horabagridae native to Asia .
Murdannia dimorphoides is a plant species endemic to Sri Lanka , known from only one location inside Wilpattu National Park .
Tragostomoides pretiosus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tragostomoides .
Nitrospira is a genus of bacteria in the phylum Nitrospirae .
Westringia is a genus of Australian shrubs .
Amorphoscelis pallida is a species of praying mantis found in Cameroon and Nigeria .
Anetia pantheratus is a species of butterfly in the Danaidae family .
Nisaetus is a genus of eagles found mainly in tropical Asia .
Calcancora is an extinct genus of sea cucumber which existed in Poland during the Triassic period , Germany during the upper Jurassic period , France , Brazil , and the United States during the Paleogene period , and Austria during the Tortonian period .
Eubranchus exiguus is a species of small sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Eubranchidae .
Pyrolirion , commonly known as fire lilies or flame lilies , is a small genus of herbaceous , bulb - forming South American plants in the Amaryllis family , native to Chile , Peru , and Bolivia .
Paraschistura lepidocaulis is a species of stone loach that is endemic to Pakistan .
Pseudostellaria oxyphylla , the robust starwort or Robinson 's starwort , is a rare plant species endemic to Idaho , known only from Kootenai and Shoshone Counties .
Condylactis gigantea is a tropical species of ball anemone that is found in shallow reefs and other shallow inshore areas in the Caribbean Sea -- more specifically the West Indies -- and the western Atlantic Ocean including southern Florida through the Florida Keys .
Penicillium sphaerum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from wood in Panama .
Galium tunetanum , the Tunisian Bedstraw , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Myctophum affine , the Metallic lanternfish , is a species of lanternfish native to the Atlantic Ocean .
Heliaea mirabilis is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Heliaea of the family Tachinidae .
Colobothina perplexa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Colobothina .
Orthochromis polyacanthus is a species of cichlid native to the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Zambia , where it is known from the lower Congo River rapids near Pool Malebo ( Stanley Pool ) and the upper Congo River basin from the Kisangani area to the Lake Mweru basin .
Paracyriothasastes marmoreus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paracyriothasastes .
The Balanomorpha are a suborder of barnacles , containing familiar acorn barnacles of the seashore .
Cerithiopsis dominguezi is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Cerithiopsidae , which is known from the Caribbean Sea and the Gulf of Mexico .
Clanculus floridus , common name the florid clanculus , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Neocolobura alboplagiata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neocolobura .
Arnica acaulis is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family , known by the common name Common leopardbane .
Castilleja pruinosa is a species of Indian paintbrush known by the common name frosted Indian paintbrush .
Blanfordia bensoni is a species of land snail which has an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiopsidae .
Aporrhais pespelecani , common name the `` pelican 's foot '' ( or more precisely `` common pelican 's foot '' to distinguish it from congeners ) , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Aporrhaidae .
The genus comprises a single species , the type species , Guamatela tuerckheimii Donn . Sm . , an evergreen shrub with a prostrate habit that is native to Mexico , Guatemala , and Honduras .
Nylanderia vagabunda , is a species of Formicinae ant found in Sri Lanka .
Centaurea collina is a species of Centaurea found in Portugal .
Kibatalia is a genus of trees and shrubs in the family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1826 .
Cephalotaxus wilsoniana is a species of coniferous tree in the plum yew family , Cephalotaxaceae .
Trypeta hysia is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Trypeta of the family Tephritidae .
Physella wrighti , common name the hotwater physa , is a species of small air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae .
The Syngnathidae are a family of fish which includes the seahorses , the pipefishes , the pipehorses , and the leafy , ruby , and weedy seadragons .
Oxystele variegata , common name the variegated topshell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
It was described by Alberti in 1967 , and the type species is Crotalocephalides gaertneri , which the author had originally described under the genus Cheirurus in 1962 .
Gelidiella is a genus of red algae ( phylum Rhodophyta ) .
Luetkenotyphlus brasiliensis ( common name : Sao Paulo caecilian ) is a species of amphibian in the Siphonopidae family .
Fusigobius is a genus of coral reef inhabiting gobies found throughout the Indian and western Pacific Oceans .
Altingia is a genus of 11 species of flowering plants in the family Altingiaceae , formerly often treated in the related family Hamamelidaceae .
Chelonistele vermicularis is a species of orchid in the genus Chelonistele .
The Mexican agouti ( Dasyprocta mexicana ) , also known as the Mexican black agouti , is a species of rodent in the family Dasyproctidae .
Chelonoidis donfaustoi ( commonly known as the eastern Santa Cruz tortoise ) is a species of Galápagos tortoise living on Santa Cruz Island , within the Galápagos .
Ingentidens is an extinct genus of chroniosuchid reptiliomorph from upper Permian ( upper Roadian age ) mudstone deposits of Dashankou locality , Xidagou Formation of China .
The Syndiniales are an order of dinoflagellates , found exclusively as endosymbionts of the tintinnid ciliates , crustaceans , fish , protozoa , algae , and other dinoflagellates .
Epipogiinae is an orchid subtribe in the tribe Nervilieae .
It was described by Pribyl and Vanek in 1985 , and the type species is Courtessolium prepater , which was originally described under the genus Pateraspis by Courtessole and Pillet in 1975 , and was later renamed under the genus Pseudosphaerexochus .
Typhlops hypomethes , known commonly as the Coastal blindsnake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Dolichoderus robustus is an extinct species of Eocene ant in the genus Dolichoderus .
Cunninghamella elegans is a species of fungus in the genus Cunninghamella found in soil .
Rhynia is a single - species genus of Devonian vascular plants .
Brachyspiraceae is a family of spirochaetes .
The single species that makes up the genus is Bognera recondita .
Bidens connata , the purplestem beggarticks or London bur - marigold , is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Jensenobotrya lossowiana is the only species of genus Jensenobotrya , in the Aizoaceae family .
The Hanken 's shrub frog , Pseudophilautus hankeni , is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to the Knuckles Mountain Range , Sri Lanka .
Collomia diversifolia is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name serpentine collomia .
Crepidodera aurea is a species of flea beetles from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in everywhere in Europe , except for Albania , Andorra , Finland , Ireland , Latvia , Moldova , Monaco , Norway , San Marino , Sweden , Vatican City , and various European islands .
Aconogonon phytolaccifolium is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family known by the common name Poke knotweed .
Angraecum aporoides is a species of comet orchid that can be found in Burundi , Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Equatorial Guinea , Gabon , Nigeria , Rwanda and São Tomé and Principe .
Sinezona laqueus is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc or micromollusc in the family Scissurellidae , the little slit shells .
Eubrachiosaurus is an extinct genus of stahleckeriine stahleckeriid dicynodont known from the Late Triassic ( Norian stage ) of Wyoming , USA .
Jamesoniella colorata is a species of liverwort in the Jungermanniaceae family .
Alisea is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Upper Miocene subepoch .
Salix planifolia is a species of willow known by the common names planeleaf willow , diamondleaf willow , and tea - leafed willow .
Oliva hirasei , common name Hirase 's olive , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Olividae , the olives .
It contains only one known species Holozonia filipes , which is known by the common name whitecrown .
Saltoblattella montistabularis is a species of jumping cockroach known only from Table Mountain near Cape Town , South Africa .
Elpistostegalia or Panderichthyida is an order of prehistoric lobe - finned fishes which lived during the Late Devonian period ( about 385 to 374 million years ago ) .
Megalocytivirus is the most recently added genus .
Parvanachis obesa , common name the fat dovesnail , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae , the dove snails .
Streptomyces chattanoogensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Tennessee in the USA .
Ipomopsis polyantha is a rare species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names Pagosa ipomopsis , Pagosa skyrocket and Archuleta County standing - cypress .
The Hesperocyoninae are a subfamily of extinct canids .
Eumorpha ( meaning `` well formed '' ) is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family .
The Torrey pine , Pinus torreyana , is a rare pine species in the United States , an endangered species growing only on the Torrey Pines State Natural Reserve , a bluff above the Pacific Ocean , and on one of the Channel Islands , endemic to the coastal sage and chaparral ecoregion in the U.S. state of California .
Ingerophrynus macrotis is a toad species of the family Bufonidae , which is found throughout most of monsoonal mainland Southeast Asia and in northeast India .
Coelopleurus is a genus of echinoids .
Manchurochelys is an extinct genus of turtle in the order Paracryptodira .
Beltanodus is an extinct genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Triassic period .
Cyprinion acinaces acinaces is a subspecies of Cyprinion acinaces .
Gentiana bavarica , common name Bavarian gentian , is a herbaceous perennial species of flowering plant in the Gentian family Gentianaceae .
The Weymouthiidae are an extinct family of eodiscinid agnostid trilobites .
The Tubariaceae is a family of basidiomycete fungi described by Alfredo Vizzini in 2008 .
Asartodes zapateri is a species of snout moth in the genus Asartodes .
Tegastidae is a family of copepods , which are characterised by having laterally compressed bodies ( resembling that of an amphipod ) , a claw - like mandible in the nauplius stage , and by a modified male genital complex .
Partula planilabrum as a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
The planarian Dugesia is a well - known representative of class Turbellaria .
Gastrochaenidae is a taxonomic family of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the unassigned Euheterodonta .
Kniphofia nana is a plant species in the genus Kniphofia .
Triprion spatulatus is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Mexico .
Niphargobates is a genus of amphipod crustaceans containing two species from European caves .
Diospyros is a genus of over 700 species of deciduous and evergreen trees , shrubs and small bushes .
Tropidosuchus is an extinct genus of carnivorous archosauriform from the Middle Triassic period ( Anisian to Ladinian stage ) .
Adeorbis elegans is a species of very small sea snail with a translucent shell , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tornidae .
Tetraneuris ivesiana is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family , known by the common name Ives ' fournerved daisy .
Carabus monticola is a species of beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in France , Italy , and Switzerland .
Rhomboteuthis lehmani is an extinct species of squid , currently the only described member of its genus .
Surcossus perlaris is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Surcossus .
Pelagophyceae is a class of heterokont algae .
†Omalaxidae is an extinct family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Penicillium cavernicola is a psychrotolerant fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which is found in cool caves .
Rhinotitan ( Giant Snout ) is an extinct genus of brontothere from the Eocene of China .
Barnardichthys fulvomarginata is a species of sole endemic to the coasts of South Africa .
Rhododendron thomsonii ( 半圆叶杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to northern India , Bhutan , Nepal , Sikkim , and southern Xizang in China , where it grows at altitudes of 3000 - -4000 meters .
Eimeriidae is a family of Apicomplexa .
Coelopoeta is a genus of small moths in the superfamily Gelechioidea .
Leptynia attenuata is a species of stick insect from Heteronemiidae family which is endemic to Portugal .
Gigantorhynchus is a genus of parasitic worm , from the family Gigantorhynchida .
Hybognathus nuchalis , the Mississippi silvery minnow is a species of fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Carcineretidae is a prehistoric family of heterotrematan crustaceans .
Myopopone castanea is a species of ant in the genus Myopopone .
Chlorophthalmus is a genus of greeneyes
Fritillaria taipaiensis is a Chinese plant species of the lily family .
Cardiopteridaceae is a eudicot family of flowering plants .
Sapheneutis camerata is a bagworm species in the genus Sapheneutis .
Saitoella complicata is a rare fungus that is one of the nearest relatives of S. pombe , a widely used model species .
Archocentrus is a genus of cichlid fishes from Central America .
The genus Aptenodytes ( from the Ancient Greek a/α ' without ' pteno-/πτηνο- `` feather '' or `` wing '' and dytes/δυτης `` diver '' ) contains two extant species of penguins collectively known as `` the great penguins '' .
The European spadefoot toads are a family of frogs , the Pelobatidae , with only one extant genus Pelobates , containing four species .
Xylococcus is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the heath family which contains the single species Xylococcus bicolor , the mission manzanita .
Alaba martensi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Litiopidae .
Psydrax odorata , known as alaheʻe in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering shrub or small tree in the coffee family , Rubiaceae .
The Orussidae or the parasitic wood wasps represent a small family of sawflies ( `` Symphyta '' ) .
Ophiclinops hutchinsi , the Earspot snakeblenny , is a species of clinid native to reefs with seagrass or weed growth at depths of from 13 to 15 metres ( 43 to 49 ft ) along the coast of southern Australia .
The Trefle Gros , ( Tadehagi triquetrum ) , is a species of flowering plant in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Turbinella angulata , common name the West Indian chank shell or Lamp Shell , is a species of very large tropical sea snail with a gill and an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinellidae .
Crataegus fluviatilis is a species of hawthorn similar to C. flabellata and to C. macrosperma .
Tagetes microglossa is a Mesoamerican species of marigolds in the sunflower family .
Synodontis macrophthalmus is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Ghana where it occurs in the Volta River basin .
Calamagrostis breweri is a species of grass known by the common name shorthair reedgrass .
The Caliciaceae are a family of mostly lichen - forming fungi belonging to the class Lecanoromycetes in the division Ascomycota .
Odontoglossum blandum , the Charming Odontoglossum , is a species of orchid found from Ecuador to Peru .
Meek 's pygmy parrot ( Micropsitta meeki ) , also known as the yellow - breasted pigmy parrot , is a species of small parrot in the Psittacidae family .
Heliamphora elongata ( Latin : elongare = elongated ) is a species of marsh pitcher plant endemic to the Ilu--
Pseudaelara sellaemontis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudaelara .
Millettia stuhlmannii , commonly known as panga panga , is a well - known species of timber tree that is native to the southeastern Afrotropics .
Cyathea elongata is a species of tree fern native to Venezuela and Colombia , where it grows in montane areas at an altitude of 2000 - 3000 m. The trunk is erect and up to 11 m tall .
Palaeolagus ( ' ancient hare ' ) is an extinct genus of lagomorph .
Burkholderia tuberum is a species of bacteria that is capable of symbiotic nitrogen fixation with the legume Aspalathus carnosa .
Cyathea glaberrima is a species of tree fern endemic to the D'Entrecasteaux Islands , specifically Fergusson Island and Goodenough Island , where it grows in mossy forest at an altitude of 900 - -1,400 m ( 3,000 - -4,600 ft ) .
Scolopendra abnormis ( Serpent Island centipede ) is a species of centipede in the family Scolopendridae that is endemic to Mauritius .
Carpilius corallinus or Batwing Coral Crab is a species of crab .
Penicillium pimiteouiense is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from sandy beach soil from the Penang Island in Peninsular Malaysia .
Spirostreptida is an order of long , cylindrical millipedes .
Hyperolius atrigularis is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
Zygopetalum crinitum is a species of orchid native to southeastern and southern Brazil and grows at elevations of 600 to 1200 meters .
Gymnopilus abramsii is a species of mushroom in the family Strophariaceae .
Chorizanthe howellii is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common names Mendocino spineflower and Howell 's spineflower .
Paraschistura is a genus of stone loaches most of which occur in Central , South and Western Asia .
Michelia punduana is a species of plant in the Magnoliaceae family .
Agelenopsis is a genus of spiders , known as American grass spiders .
Ammi visnaga is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by many common names , including toothpick - plant , toothpickweed , bisnaga , and khella .
Adenophyllum wrightii is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common names San Felipe dogweed , San Felipe dyssodia and Wright 's dogweed .
Ammodytes is a genus of sand lances native to the northern oceans .
Papilio antonio is a member of the fuscus species - group .
Peperomia rubella is a plant species in the Piperaceae family , endemic to Jamaica .
Micrurus browni , commonly known as Brown 's coral snake , is a species of venomous elapid snake native to southwestern Mexico and Guatemala .
Callicarpa mollis is a species of beautyberry that is cultivated and grown in gardens and parks as ornamental plant .
Zephyranthes refugiensis , the Refugio zephyrlily , is a rare plant species known from only two counties in southern Texas ( Goliad and Refugio ) .
Pseudacanthicus fordii is a species of armored catfish endemic to Suriname where it occurs in the coastal river drainages .
Acropora awi is a species of acroporid coral that was first described by Wallace and Wolstenholme in 1998 .
Symplocos is a genus of flowering plants in the order Ericales .
Trigodon gaudryi is an extinct species of the family Toxodontidae , a large bodied notoungulate which inhabited South America during the Miocene living from 11.61 - -7.25 Ma and existed for approximately 4.36 million years .
Parhippopsis columbiana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parhippopsis .
Xanthophyllum sulphureum is a species of plant in the family Polygalaceae .
Holdenius is an extinct genus of arthrodire placoderm fish which lived during the Late Devonian period .
The Kashmir gray langur ( Semnopithecus ajax ) is an Old World monkey , one of the species of langurs .
Austrolittorina cincta is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles , found in New Zealand .
Callimantis is a genus of mantis of the family Mantidae consisting of only one species , Callimantis antillarum .
Partulina crassa was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Kalyptatherina helodes , the marine sailfin silverside is a species of sailfin silverside endemic to Indonesia , where it is only known from mangrove swamps around Misool and Batanta Islands .
Agyneta pseudorurestris is a species of sheet weaver found in Portugal , Spain , Cyprus , Sardinia , Algeria , Tunisia and Israel .
Zonitoides excavatus is a European species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Gastrodontidae .
Saxifraga paniculata ( also known by the English common names alpine saxifrage , encrusted saxifrage , lifelong saxifrage , lime - encrusted saxifrage , livelong saxifrage , White Mountain saxifrage , and silver saxifrage ) is a species of saxifrage native to the United States , Europe and Asia .
The Indochinese box turtle , Vietnamese box turtle , or flowerback box turtle ( Cuora galbinifrons ) is a species of Asian box turtles from China ( Hainan and Guangxi ) , northern and central Vietnam , Laos , and possibly northeastern Cambodia .
Scartella caboverdiana is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern central Atlantic ocean , around Cape Verde .
The Sumba green pigeon ( Treron teysmannii ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Qianosuchus is an extinct genus of aquatic archosaur from the middle Triassic ( Anisian ) Guanling Formation of Pan County , China .
Gyalopion canum , commonly known as the Western hooknose snake , is a species of small colubrid snake endemic to the United States and Mexico .
Atheris squamigera , common names green bush viper , variable bush viper , leaf viper , and others , is a venomous viper species endemic to west and central Africa .
The Actinidiaceae are a small family , the Chinese gooseberry family , of plants .
Burkholderia terricola is a species of bacteria in the phylum Proteobacteria .
Abaraeus cuneatus is a species beetle in Cerabycidae family which can be found in Grand Batanga , Cameroon .
Caecorhamdella brasiliensis is a species of fish in the Pimelodidae family .
Archachatina knorri is a species of large air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinidae .
Eimeria is a genus of apicomplexan parasites that includes various species capable of causing the disease coccidiosis in cattle and poultry , among other animals .
Chaetomitrium elegans is a moss species in the genus Chaetomitrium .
Ramphotyphlops exocoeti ( also known as Christmas Island blind snake ) is a blind snake species endemic to Christmas Island .
Vappodes is a genus of orchids from Indonesia , New Guinea and Australia .
Vulpia myuros , the annual fescue , or rat's - tail fescue , is an annual grass species of the genus Vulpia .
Juraphyllitidae is a family of Lower Triassic phylloceratin ammonites from Europe , North Africa , and Asia characterized by narrow , evolutely coiled shells , usually with coarse ventral ribbing on the body chamber .
Eriogonum gracilipes is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name White Mountains buckwheat .
Triodopsis tridentata , common name the northern three - tooth or northern threetooth , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Polygyridae .
Adenaria is a monotypic genus of plants in the family Lythraceae containing the single species Adenaria floribunda .
Pteridophyllum racemosum is a species of flowering plant endemic to Japan .
Parancistrus is a small genus of suckermouth armored catfishes native to South America .
Sphaerocarpales is an order of plants within the liverworts .
Euchorthippus declivus , the `` sharp - tailed grasshopper , '' is a species of short - horned grasshoppers belonging to the family Acrididae , subfamily Gomphocerinae .
Eurymorion is a genus of sheet weavers .
In taxonomy , Tetrabaena is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Tetrabaenaceae .
Serapias is a genus of terrestrial orchids that can be found all over southern Europe to Asia Minor .
Crenicichla strigata is a species of cichlid native to the southern tributaries of the Amazon River basin in Brazil and Guyana .
Hulsea vestita is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name pumice alpinegold .
Agyneta pseudosaxatilis is a species of sheet weaver found in Russia and Kazakhstan .
Fucus gardneri is a species of seaweed , a brown alga living on the littoral shore of the Pacific coasts of North America .
Samolus repens is a species of water pimpernel native to Australia , New Zealand and near - by Pacific islands , and South America ( South Chile ) , where it is common in temperate and subtropic coastlines .
Solidago decurrens is an Asian species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Pterynotus tripterus , common name : the three - winged murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Streptomyces harbinensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from roots of the soybean Glycine max in Harbin in the Heilongjiang province in China .
Rhinotyphlops boylei , commonly known as Boyle 's beaked blind snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Obliquogobius is a genus of gobies native to the Indian Ocean and the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Polystichum imbricans is a species of fern known by the common names narrowleaf swordfern and imbricate sword fern .
Mermithidae is a family of nematode worms that are endoparasites in arthropods .
Lupinus truncatus is a species of lupine known by the common name collared annual lupine .
Caulkicephalus is a genus of pterosaur , belonging to the Pterodactyloidea , from the Isle of Wight off the coast of England .
Pelobacter venetianus is a species of bacteria that degrades polyethylene glycol .
Caloplaca obamae is a species of lichen in the fungus genus Caloplaca .
Diadophis punctatus regalis , commonly known as the regal ringneck snake , is a subspecies of ringneck snake endemic to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Guaiacum sanctum , commonly known as Holywood or Holywood Lignum - vitae , is a species of flowering plant in the creosote bush family , Zygophyllaceae .
Atrophaneura sycorax is a species of butterfly from the family Papilionidae that is found from South Burma to Peninsular Malaysia , and in Sumatra and West Java .
Brachyelytrum is a genus of North American and East Asian plants in the grass family , classified in its own tribe Brachyelytreae .
Hippomane spinosa is a plant species in the Euphorbiaceae described by Linnaeus in 1753 .
The Sri Lanka bush warbler is a skulky species which can very difficult to see .
Tabanus darimonti is a Mediterranean species of biting horse - fly .
It is the only described member of the genus Mysanthus , though there is a report of an undescribed species .
Apatemyidae is an extinct family of placental mammals that took part in the first placental evolutionary radiation together with other early mammals such as the leptictids .
Appalachia arcana is a species of grasshopper in the family Acrididae .
Stachys byzantina ( syn . S. lanata ; lamb's - ear or woolly hedgenettle ) is a species of Stachys , native to Turkey , Armenia , and Iran .
Locustellidae is a newly recognized family of small insectivorous songbirds ( `` warblers '' ) , formerly placed in the Old World warbler `` wastebin '' family .
Oroya is a genus of cacti ( family Cactaceae ) , originating from Peru .
Spoonwings or Nemopteridae are a family of neuropteran insects .
Sinopterus ( meaning `` Chinese wing '' ) was a genus of tapejarid pterodactyloid pterosaur from the Aptian - age Lower Cretaceous Jiufotang Formation of Chaoyang , Liaoning , China .
Laytonia is an extinct genus of prehistoric halosaur that lived in deep water off the North American Pacific Coast from the Zemorrian Epoch ( comprising either the latest Oligocene or lower Miocene ) until during the Upper Miocene subepoch , when tectonic uplift effectively destroyed the genus ' habitat by making the deep water too shallow .
Tillandsia bulbosa , the bulbous airplant , is a species in the genus Tillandsia .
Micrixalus kodayari , also known as the kodayar dancing frog , is a newly described species of frog in the Micrixalidae family .
Coupatezia is a prehistoric genus of ray whose fossils are found in strata dating from the Maastrichtian stage until the last species ' extinction during the Middle Eocene .
Gloxinia perennis is a species of tropical rhizomatous herbaceous flowering plant belonging to the family Gesneriaceae .
Milacidae is a family of air - breathing , keeled , land slugs .
Drakaea gracilis , commonly known as slender hammer orchid is a species of orchid endemic to the south -- west of Western Australia .
Mimothelais fruhstorferi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimothelais .
Osteopelta ceticola is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Osteopeltidae .
Anacamptis laxiflora ( lax - flowered orchid , loose - flowered orchid , or green - winged meadow orchid ) is a species of orchid .
Pachyagrotis is a genus of moths of the Noctuidea family .
Haplosyllis spongicola , the sponge worm , is a species of polychaete worm in the family Syllidae .
Europelta is an extinct genus of struthiosaurine nodosaurid dinosaur known from the Early Cretaceous ( early Albian stage ) lower Escucha Formation of Teruel Province , northeastern Spain .
Astragalus australis is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name Indian milkvetch .
Hemilampra is a genus of hoverflies
Richardsonichthys leucogaster , the Whiteface waspfish , is a species of waspfish native to reefs of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Bonapartia pedaliota , the Longray Fangjaw , is a species of bristlemouth found in the Atlantic and Indian Oceans .
Eimeria tenella is a species of Eimeria that causes hemorrhagic cecal coccidiosis in young poultry .
Rubus curtipes , the shortstalk dewberry , is an uncommon North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Aeolidioidea is a superfamily of sea slugs , the aeolid nudibranchs .
Algeripithecus is an extinct genus of early fossil primate , weighing approximately 65 to 85 grams ( 2.3 to 3.0 oz ) .
The Cordycipitaceae are a family of parasitic fungi in the Ascomycota , class Sordariomycetes .
Euroschinus falcatus ( sometimes spelled Euroschinus falcata ) is a species of tree in the Anacardiaceae family .
Sturisomatichthys citurensis is a species of armored catfish of the family Loricariidae endemic to Panama where it occurs in the Tuira and Bayano River basins .
Capperia browni is a species of moth in the genus Capperia , known from Mexico .
Tabanus sudeticus also known as the dark giant horsefly is a species of biting horse - fly .
Pentaedrusaurus is an extinct genus of procolophonid parareptile from the Early Triassic of China .
Cryptochloa is a genus of Neotropical plants in the grass family , widespread across much of Mexico , Central America , and South America .
Carya texana is an endangered species in southwestern Indiana .
The Amoebidae are a family of Amoebozoa , including naked amoebae that produce multiple pseudopodia of indeterminate length .
Guaiacum officinale , commonly known as roughbark lignum - vitae , guaiacwood or gaïacwood , is a species of tree in the caltrop family , Zygophyllaceae , that is native to the Caribbean and the northern coast of South America .
The common torrent hawk , ( Epophthalmia vittata ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Macromiidae .
Omoglymmius regius is a species of beetle in the subfamily Rhysodidae .
Yucca baileyi is a relatively small species , usually acaulescent but sometimes with a short leafy stem .
Afrocarpus falcatus ( syn . Podocarpus falcatus ) is a species of tree in the family Podocarpaceae .
Panzerina is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae first described in 1982 .
Mystacoleucus is a genus of cyprinid fishes that are found in Southeast Asia .
Pseudocuma longicorne is a marine species of cumacean in the family Pseudocumatidae .
Metoecis carnifex is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Metoecis .
Pollenia rudis , the common cluster fly , is a species of fly in the family Calliphoridae .
Anomia trigonopsis , also known as the New Zealand jingle , is a species of marine bivalve mollusc in the family Anomiidae , the anomiids .
Doronicum plantagineum , the plantain - leaved leopard's - bane or plantain false leopardbane , is a European plant species in the sunflower family .
Bignonia binata is a flowering plant species in the genus Bignonia .
Monardella douglasii is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Douglas ' monardella .
Aloe affinis is a species of aloe plant , endemic to Limpopo , Gauteng , and Mpumalanga , of South Africa .
Maniltoa grandiflora is a species of plant in the legume family ( Fabaceae ) .
Chamonixia pachydermis , is a species of fungus in the Boletaceae family , found in New Zealand .
Cryptocheilus elegans is a spider wasp species in the genus Cryptocheilus found in Europe .
Heterotaxis is a genus of orchids native to Latin America from central Mexico to Bolivia , and also to parts of the West Indies .
Orthocarpus imbricatus is a species of flowering plant in the broomrape family known by the common name mountain owl's - clover .
Diaporthe is a genus of endophytic filamentous fungus plant pathogens .
Lyginopteris is a genus of Late Carboniferous seed fern that was sometimes parasitized .
Erosaria helvola , common name : the honey cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
The Day 's Cymbidium ( Cymbidium dayanum ) is a species of orchid , also known as the Phoenix Orchid or Tree Orchid .
Alcithoe knoxi is a species of deepwater sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Qingxiusaurus is a genus of titanosaur sauropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of Guangxi , China .
Orthotylus divisus is a species of bug from a family of Miridae that can be found in Greece , Spain , and on islands such as Sardinia , Sicily , and Canary Islands .
Tristachya ( common name Trident grasses ) is a genus of African and Latin American plants in tribe Tristachyideae within the grass family .
It contains only one species , Apsidophora purpurorbis , which is found in Thailand , the Malay Peninsula , Sumatra and New Guinea .
Conus tessulatus , common name the tessellated cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Berryteuthis anonychus , also known as the minimal armhook squid or smallfin gonate squid , is a species of squid in the family Gonatidae .
It contains only one species , Mersa metochia , which is found on Seram .
Isocoma humilis , common names Zion goldenbush or Zion jimmyweed , is a rare North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Hyloxalus idiomelus ( Rivero 's rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Houlletia odoratissima is a species of orchid that occurs in the Andes from Panama to Bolivia .
Amblycheila cylindriformis is a species of flightless tiger beetle .
Eucalyptus × tetragona is a hybrid species in the genus Eucalyptus .
Tachypeles rossii is a species of ground beetle in the subfamily Paussinae in the genus Tachypeles .
Aulactinia verrucosa , the gem anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Actiniidae .
Melica macra is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Argentina , Brazil , and Uruguay .
Paleopanax is an extinct genus of flowering plant in the Ginseng family , Araliaceae , containing the single species Paleopanax oregonensis .
Chelodina insculpta is an extinct species of snake - necked turtle that was described in 1897 from material gathered in Darling Downs , Queensland , Australia , restricted .
Yingshanosaurus ( meaning `` Yingshan or Golden Hills reptile '' ) is a genus of quadrupedal herbivorous dinosaur from the Late Jurassic , around 155 million years ago .
Tentaculita is an extinct class of uncertain placement ranging from the Early Ordovician to the Middle Jurassic .
Guancha camura is a species of calcareous sponge from Norway .
Xylotoles costatus , the Pitt Island longhorn beetle , is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae .
