Guancha pulcherrima is a species of calcareous sponge from Australia
Bosellia mimetica is a species of sea slug , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Boselliidae .
Dictyna civica is spider species found in Europe , North Africa , Turkey and North America .
Oncocnemis was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Sympistis
Conus purpurascens , common name the purple cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Ziziphus mauritiana , also known as Chinese date , ber , Chinee apple , jujube , Indian plum , Regi pandu , Indian jujube and masau , is a tropical fruit tree species belonging to the family Rhamnaceae .
Luciliocline is a genus of flowering plants in the pussy's - toes tribe with the daisy family .
Dawsonicyon is an extinct genus of basal carnivoramorphan which existed in Wyoming , USA , during the middle Eocene .
Rhagadiolus is a genus of plants in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family , native to the Mediterranean region of southern Europe , northern Africa , and the Middle East .
Appendicula calcarata is a species of orchid that can be found on the islands of Sumatra and Borneo in Indonesia and Malaysia , from elevations of 700 - -1,300 m. It can be found in lower riverine montane forests , and it flowers from July--
Anomaloglossus shrevei ( common name : Shreve 's rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Theretairus is a Late Jurassic genus of sphenodont reptile from the Morrison Formation of western North America , present in stratigraphic zones 5 and 6 .
Brunneria gracilis is a species of praying mantis found in Argentina , Brazil , Paraguay , Uruguay , and Venezuela .
Amorphoscelis austrogermanica is a species of praying mantis found in Namibia , KwaZulu - Natal , Transvaal , and East Africa .
Solenogyne is a genus of Australian plants in the aster tribe within the daisy family .
Ventrifossa is a genus of rattails in the family Macrouridae .
Monodactylidae is a family of perciform bony fish commonly referred to as monos , moonyfishes or fingerfishes .
It belongs to the advanced harpaline assemblage , and if these are circumscribed sensu lato as a single subfamily , Pterostichinae are downranked to a tribe Pterostichini .
Woodwardia areolata ( netted chain fern ) is a species of fern native to eastern North America .
Ilex tarapotina is a species of holly used in northern Peru to make a special type of maté known as `` té o '' maté '' which is said to produce unknown effects .
Rondonacara hoehnei is a species of cichlid fish of the subfamily Cichlinae .
Lirularia succincta , common name the tucked lirularia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Nanohaloarchaea is a class of archaea .
Evodianthus is a genus of plants first described as a genus in 1857 .
Amblyodipsas teitana , or the Teitana purple - glossed snake , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Hypericum hartwegii is a species of shrub in the family Hypericaceae .
Saranthe is a genus of plants native to Brazil and Paraguay , described as a genus in 1861 .
Salea horsfieldii , commonly known as Horsfield 's spiny lizard or the Nilgiri salea , is a species of agamid , which is endemic to the Nilgiri Hills of India .
Pontosmilus is a genus of machairodontine saber - toothed cats .
Tityus pococki is a species of scorpion belonging to the family Buthidae .
Nepagyrtes piriana is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Nepagyrtes .
Bothrops jararacussu , commonly known in English as the jararacussu , is a venomous pit viper species endemic to South America .
Deinandra palmeri is a rare North American species of plants in the tarweed tribe within the ( sunflower family ) .
Drosophila sechellia is a species of fruit fly , used in lab studies of speciation because can mate with Drosophila simulans .
Verbascum bugulifolium is a species of Verbascum native to Bulgaria and western Turkey .
Kenneth 's white - toothed rat ( Berylmys mackenziei ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Boiga dightoni , commonly known as the Pirmad cat snake or the Travancore cat snake , is a species of rear - fanged colubrid endemic to the Western Ghats of India .
Erigeron religiosus is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Clear Creek fleabane .
Trifolium beckwithii is a species of clover known by the common name Beckwith 's clover .
Sinotyrannus ( meaning `` Chinese tyrant '' ) is a genus of large basal proceratosaurid dinosaur , a relative of tyrannosaurids which flourished in North America and Asia during the Jurassic and early Cretaceous periods .
Horkelia sericata is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common names silky horkelia and Howell 's horkelia .
The genus Nelepsittacus consists of four extinct parrot species and is closely related to the genus Nestor .
Selineae is the Angelica or Arracacia clade or tribe of the family Apiaceae .
Chromolaena geraniifolia ( geraniumleaf thoroughwort ) , is a West Indian species of flowering shrub in the sunflower family .
Psaltoda flavescens , commonly known as the golden knight , is a species of cicada native to Queensland in eastern Australia .
Bartonella japonica is a species of proteobacteria in the genus Bartonella .
Cetopsidium pemon is a species of whale catfish found in the Caroni River and the Caura River basins , southern tributaries of the Orinoco in eastern Venezuela , the Meta River basin of the western portions of the Orinoco system in eastern Colombia , and the upper portions of the Branco River in northern Brazil .
The Glossosomatidae are a family of the class Insecta and order Trichoptera . The family contains 23 genera in three subfamilies .
Phippsia is a genus of Arctic and alpine plants in the grass family .
Mormodes atropurpurea is a species of orchid native to Panama , Venezuela , and Brazil .
Erquitaia is a poorly known genus of prehistoric galeomorph shark whose fossils are found in rocks dating from the Maastrichtian stage .
Kiwa puravida is a species of deep - sea dwelling decapod , a member of the genus Kiwa , a genus of animals sometimes informally known as `` yeti crabs '' .
Rahiolisaurus is a genus of abelisaurid theropod dinosaur which existed in India during the Late Cretaceous period .
Inape circumsetae is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family and is endemic to Colombia .
Paramischocyttarus is a small afrotropical and palearctic Zethus - like genus of potter wasps .
Oeceoclades pandurata is a terrestrial and epiphytic orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is native to eastern Zimbabwe and Madagascar .
Clinus robustus , the Robust klipfish , is a species of clinid that occurs in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean around South Africa where it can be found in the subtidal zone in areas with plentiful seaweed growth .
Algia is a genus of butterflies of the subfamily Heliconiinae in the family Nymphalidae found in southeast Asia . The genus ranges from Burma to New Guinea .
Eusparassus dufouri is a species of huntsman spider found in the Western Mediterranean Basin , Portugal and Spain .
Dysoneuridae is an extinct family of insect in the order Trichoptera .
Xyris difformis , the bog yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plant in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Harpa costata , common name the ribbed harp , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Harpidae , the harp snails .
Takakia lepidozioides is a species of moss in the Takakiaceae family , one of two species of Takakia .
The Hymenophyllaceae ( filmy ferns and bristle ferns ) is a family of two or more genera and over 600 species of ferns , with a subcosmopolitan distribution , but generally restricted to very damp places or to locations where they are wetted by spray from waterfalls or springs .
Hazardia detonsa is a rare species of shrub in the daisy family known by the common name island bristleweed .
Impatiens meruensis is a species of flowering plant in the family Balsaminaceae .
Athericidae is a small family of flies known as water snipe flies or ibis flies .
Kronosaurus ( /ˌkrɒnoʊˈsɔrəs/ KRON - o - SAWR - əs ; meaning `` lizard of Kronos '' ) is an extinct genus of short - necked pliosaur .
Carlephyton glaucophyllum is a species of arum endemic to Madagascar .
Helicostyla smargadina is a species of small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Bradybaenidae .
Even though the Siberian chipmunk normally grows to 50 - -150 grams , this species is relatively small compared to other Sciuridae , such as the Red Squirrel .
Gyraulus crista , commonly called the Nautilus ramshorn , is a minute species of freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails .
Stachyridopsis is a genus of bird in the Timaliidae family .
Clara 's echymipera ( Echymipera clara ) , or Clara 's spiny bandicoot or white - lipped bandicoot , is a species of marsupial in the family Peramelidae .
Ancistrus temminckii is a species of armoured suckermouth catfish in the family Loricariidae of order Siluriformes .
Antirrhinum subbaeticum is a species of plant in the Plantaginaceae family .
Liuixalus ocellatus ( common names ocellated bubble - nest frog and ocellated small treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Podoserpula pusio , commonly known as the pagoda fungus , is a species of fungus in the family Amylocorticiaceae .
Leptachatina lepida is a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Amastridae .
Babesiosoma is a genus of parasitic protozoa in the phylum Apicomplexia .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Scepastocarpus peritheciiformis .
Westringia eremicola , commonly known as slender westringia or slender western rosemary , is a flowering plant species that is endemic to south - eastern Australia It is a slender shrub growing to 1.5 metres high .
Crataegus nigra , the Hungarian thorn or Hungarian hawthorn , is a black - fruited species of hawthorn native to Czechoslovakia , Hungary , Albania and Yugoslavia .
Sason colemani is a species of barychelid trapdoor spiders that has only been found in a natural swamp in the Botanical Gardens in Cairns , Queensland .
Grant 's bushbaby ( Galagoides granti ) , also known as Grant 's lesser bushbaby or the Mozambique lesser bushbaby is a species of primate in the family Galagidae .
Calathea warscewiczii is a species of evergreen , perennial , herbaceous plant in the Marantaceae family , endemic to Costa Rica and Nicaragua .
Rhododendron bureavii is a rhododendron species native to western Sichuan and northern Yunnan , China , where it grows at altitudes of 2800 - -4500 meters .
Achatina reticulata is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinidae , the giant African snails .
Caenagnathus ( ' recent jaw ' ) is a genus of caenagnathid oviraptorosaurian dinosaur from the late Cretaceous ( Campanian ; ~75 million years ago ) .
Megalochelys is an extinct genus of cryptodiran turtle which lived from the Miocene to Pleistocene , across Asia and possibly East Europe .
Argyrodes lepidus is a species of tangle web spider in the genus Argyrodes
Odorrana hainanensis is a species of frog in the Ranidae family that might be endemic to Hainan Island , China ; there is one record from Guangxi .
Berberis andrieuxii is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1838 .
Colus hirudinosus is a species of stinkhorn fungus found in Asia , Australia , northern Africa , and southern Europe .
Drosera intermedia , commonly known as the oblong - leaved sundew , spoonleaf sundew , or spatulate leaved sundew , is an insectivorous plant species belonging to the sundew genus .
Asplenium virens is a species of fern in the family Aspleniaceae .
Sporobolus airoides is a species of grass known by the common name alkali sacaton .
The Pavoraja nitida ( Peacock skate ) is a species of fish in Rajidae family .
Taxus wallichiana , the Himalayan yew , is a species of yew , native to the Himalaya and parts of south - east Asia .
Vagaceratops ( meaning `` wandering ( vagus , Latin ) horned face '' , in reference to its close relationship with Kosmoceratops from Utah ) is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsian dinosaur .
Agyneta kopetdaghensis is a species of sheet weaver found in Iran and Turkmenistan .
Pterolepis glomerata , the false meadowbeauty , is a plant species in the family Melastomataceae .
Carex mckittrickensis , the Guadalupe Mountain sedge , is a species of sedge endemic to Guadalupe Mountains National Park in western Texas .
Callionymus draconis is a species of dragonet native to temperate regions of the Indian and Pacific oceans around Japan and western Australia where it occurs at depths of around 138 metres ( 453 ft ) .
Acanthemblemaria harpeza is a species of chaenopsid blenny found around Navassa Island , in the western central Atlantic ocean .
The type species is Nasutoceratops titusi .

Potamocypris variegata is a species of ostracod crustacean in the family Cyprididae , subfamily Cypridopsinae .

Acanthoceratidae is an extinct family of acanthoceratoid cephalopods in the order Ammonitida , known from the Upper Cretaceous .
Ventricolaria rugatina , or the queen venus clam , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .

Magnolia globosa ( commonly known as Globe magnolia or Hen magnolia ) is a species of Magnolia native to Bhutan , southwestern China ( Sichuan , Xizang , Yunnan ) , northeastern India ( Assam , Sikkim ) , northern Myanmar - Burma , and eastern Nepal .
Sebastes ventricosus is a species of fish in the rockfish family found in the Northwest Pacific
Yanoconodon is a monotypic genus of extinct early mammal whose representative species Yanoconodon allini lived during the Mesozoic in what is now China .
Naucleopsis glabra is a South American plant species in the family Moraceae .
Panulirus echinatus , the brown spiny lobster , is a species of spiny lobster that lives on rocky reefs in the tropical western Atlantic Ocean and central Atlantic Islands .
Silene rupestris or rock campion is a plant species of the genus Silene .
Nessia burtonii , commonly known as Burton 's nessia , the three - toed snake skink , or Gray 's snake skink , is a species of skink endemic to the island of Sri Lanka .
Synodontis matthesi is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to Tanzania where it occurs in the Rufiji River basin .
Zombia antillarum , commonly known as the zombie palm , is a species of palm tree and the only member of the genus Zombia .
Erica capensis ( or the Cape Heath ) is a species of erica that was naturally restricted to the city of Cape Town , South Africa .
Coregonus gutturosus , the Lake Constance whitefish , is an extinct species of whitefish in the salmon family Salmonidae .
Callobius severus is a species of spider found in parts of North America .
The Ranellidae , common name the triton shells or tritons , are a taxonomic family of small to very large predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Planocraniidae is an extinct family of basal crocodylian that existed during the Eocene in Asia , Europe and North America .
Penicillium cyaneum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from a oil - field .
Eurycotis is a genus of cockroaches .
Pelobates fuscus is a species of toad in the family Pelobatidae , native to an area extending from Central Europe to Western Asia .
Oxymeris senegalensis , common name : the Faval Auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .

The genus is monotypic containing the single species Ianusanta ianusi from Peru .
Leptotyphlops maximus , or the Giant blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
The sage - grouse are the two species in the bird genus Centrocercus .
Aphomia argentia is a species of snout moth in the genus Aphomia .
Eucalyptus bicostata , commonly known as southern blue gum , Victorian blue gum or eurabbie , is a eucalypt species native to Victoria and eastern New South Wales , Australia .
Neomyxine biniplicata also known as the slender hagfish is a species of hagfish endemic to New Zealand .
The Bongolava mouse lemur ( Microcebus bongolavensis ) is a species of mouse lemur endemic to Madagascar .

Laminacauda newtoni is a species of sheet weaver found in Chile and Argentina .
Melindea nigrita is a species of leaf beetle native to the Democratic Republic of the Congo , observed by Jacoby in 1901 .
Cydalima perspectalis or the box tree moth is a species of moth of the family Crambidae .
Opsilia coerulescens is a gray coloured species of a beetle from family longhorn beetle , subfamily Lamiinae .
Trichomanes angustatum is a species of fern in the Hymenophyllaceae family .
Bambusa multiplex is a species of bamboo native to China ( provinces of Guangdong , Guangxi , Hainan , Hunan , Jiangxi , Sichuan , Yunnan ) , Nepal , Bhutan , Assam , Sri Lanka , Taiwan , and northern Indochina .
Eledone nigra is a little - known species of octopus described from one male and six females which were taken in Luderitz Bay , Namibia and has only been recorded subsequently in 1941 .
Acalypta hellenica is a species of bugs from Tingidae family , and Tinginae subfamily that can be found in Bosnia , Bulgaria , Canary Islands , Croatia , France , Denmark , Greece , Italy , Spain , and Ukraine .
Muzimes collaris is a species of blister beetles belonging to the family Meloidae .
Neoraimondia is a genus of medium to large cacti from Peru .
Barsine pallinflexa is a species of lichen - moths of the Erebidae family , Arctiinae subfamily .
Chloridops is an extinct genus of birds .
Beaufortia decussata was first species of Beaufortia to be described .
Myriophyllum hippuroides is a species of water milfoil known by the common name western watermilfoil .
Stenomorda fasciata is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , which is in the genus Stenomorda .
Solidago rupestris , the rock goldenrod or riverbank goldenrod , is a North American species of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Ernobius abietis is a species of beetles in the genus Ernobius of the family Anobiidae .
Strategus aloeus , the ox beetle , is a species of rhinoceros beetle .
Acrosticta foveolata is a species of ulidiidae or picture - winged fly in the genus Acrosticta of the family Ulidiidae .
Triplophysa hutjertjuensis is a species of stone loach found in Mongolia and China .
Juncus nodosus is a species of rush known by the common name knotted rush .
Cyrtophora parangexanthematica is a species of tent spider found in the Philippines .
Tetragondacnus spilotus is a species of pearlfish found in the Pacific waters off of Sumatra where it has been recovered at a depth of just over 500 metres ( 1,600 ft ) .
Cercocarpus traskiae , known by the common names Santa Catalina Island mountain - mahogany and Catalina mahogany , is a rare species of plant in the rose family .
Potamonautes raybouldi is a species of freshwater crab .
Promyopias is an Afrotropical genus of ant in the subfamily Ponerinae containing the single species Promyopias silvestrii .
Rana weiningensis is a species of frog in the Ranidae family endemic to China .
Catharsius gorilla is a species of African dung beetles belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Calystegia purpurata is a species of morning glory known by the common name Pacific false bindweed .
Thorius macdougalli ( common name MacDougall 's pigmy salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Adetomeris is a genus of moths in the Saturniidae family .
Eriophyoidea are a superfamily of herbivorous mites .
Pyrola rotundifolia or round - leaved wintergreen is a plant species of the genus Pyrola .
Erythrina burttii is a flowering plant species in the genus of Erythrina found in Kenya and Ethiopia .
Solidago petiolaris is a North American species of goldenrod commonly called the downy ragged goldenrod .
Agonum extensicolle is a species of ground beetle from Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Arizona , United States and Canada .
Cinetorhynchus reticulatus is a species of shrimp belonging to the family Rhynchocinetidae , known by the common name green - eye dancing shrimp or reticulated hinge - beak shrimp .
Coccocarpia is a lichenized genus of fungi within the Coccocarpiaceae family .
Diodora aspera , common name the rough keyhole limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Penicillium coprophilum is a species of the genus of Penicillium which produces roquefortine C , griseofulvin and oxaline .
Taraxacum centrasiaticum is a rare and little - known species of dandelion known only from alpine meadows at an elevation of 3,400 - -3,500 m ( 11,200 - -11,500 ft ) in Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region of western China .
Sagartia troglodytes is a species of sea anemone in the family Sagartiidae , also known as the mud sagartia or the cave - dwelling anemone .
Ehrlichia is a genus of rickettsiales bacteria that is transmitted to vertebrates by ticks .
Berberis ( /ˈbɜːrbərɪs/ ) is a large genus of deciduous and evergreen shrubs from 1 - -5 m ( 3.3 - -16.4 ft ) tall found throughout the temperate and subtropical regions of the world ( apart from Australia ) .
Parafreoides ghanaensis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parafreoides .
Drosera silvicola is a species of pygmy sundew from Western Australia .
The Holectypoida are an order of sea urchins related to the sand dollars .
Corydoras garbei is a species of catfish in the family Callichthyidae endemic to Brazil where it is found in the São Francisco River basin .
Corylus johnsonii is an extinct species of hazel known from fossil fruits found in the Klondike Mountain Formation deposits of Northern Washington State , dated to the early Eocene Ypresian stage ( 56 to 48 million years ago ) .
Amyris polymorpha is a species of flowering plant in the citrus family , Rutaceae , that is endemic to Cuba .
Hypericum crux - andreae , commonly called St. Peter's - wort , is a species of flowering plant in the Hypericaceae ( St. John 's wort ) family .
Dugesia japonica is a species of dugesiid triclad that inhabits the freshwater bodies of East Asia .
Micraira is the only genus of tribe Micraireae in the grass family , native to Australia .
Childrena childreni , the large silverstripe , is a species nymphalid butterfly was first described by Gray in 1831 .
Sphenotitan is an extinct genus of basal opisthodontian sphenodontian reptile known from the Late Triassic Quebrada del Barro Formation of northwestern Argentina .
Neotysonia is a genus of Australian plants in pussy's - toes tribe within the daisy family .
Erigeron watsonii is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Watson 's fleabane .
Stokesia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Stokesia laevis .
Erica cerinthoides is a species of heath native to South Africa ( the Cape Provinces , the Free State , KwaZulu - Natal , the Northern Provinces ) , Lesotho and Swaziland .
Helianthella uniflora , oneflower helianthella , is a North American plant species in the sunflower family .
Fritzolenellus is an extinct genus from a well - known class of fossil marine arthropods , the trilobites , with three known species .
The genus consists of the single species Xenoposeidon proneneukos .
Echinostelium is a genus of slime mould , and the only genus in the family Echinosteliaceae , or Echinosteliidae .
The Carrot - tail Viper Gecko ( Teratolepis fasciata ) is a species of gecko found in India and Pakistan .
Acanthognathus stipulosus is a species of ant belonging to the Acanthognathus genus .
Phidippus zethus is a species of jumping spider ( Salticidae ) native to Mexico .
Haplochromis eduardianus is a species of cichlid endemic to Uganda where it is found in Lake George , Lake Edward and the Kazinga Channel .
Ericameria laricifolia is a North American species of flowering shrub in the daisy family known by the common name turpentine bush , or turpentine - brush .
Heterodontosuchus is a dubious genus of extinct phytosaur .
Microlophus peruvianus , the Peru Pacific iguana , is a species of lava lizard endemic to the Ecuador , Peru , and Chile .
Cassia aubrevillei is a legume species in the subfamily Caesalpinioideae .
Cynegetis impunctata is a species of Ladybird native to continental Europe .
The Pteromalidae are a very large family of parasitoid wasps , with some 3,450 described species in about 640 genera ( the number was greater , but many species and genera have been reduced to synonymy in recent years ) .
Anabarilius brevianalis is a species of cyprinid fish from the Jinsha River basin in China .
Amphorosteus is a dubious genus of mosasaur from the Late Cretaceous of North America .
Pusia voncoseli is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Costellariidae .
Antirrhinum multiflorum ( syn . Sairocarpus multiflorus ) is a species of New World snapdragon known by the common name Sierra snapdragon .
Bituminaria is small genus of perennial herbs in the bean family .
Sinezona rimuloides is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Scissurellidae , the little slit snails .
Nesodactylus was a genus of `` rhamphorhynchoid '' pterosaur from the middle - late Oxfordian age Upper Jurassic Jagua Formation of Pinar del Río , western Cuba .
The Congo serpent eagle ( Dryotriorchis spectabilis ) is a species of bird of prey in the family Accipitridae , and is placed in the monotypic genus Dryotriorchis .
Leathesia difformis , the sea potato , is a species of littoral brown algae in the class Phaeophyceae and the order Ectocarpales which is commonly attached to other seaweeds and sometimes rocks .
Aplysiopsis sinusmensalis , the Table Bay nudibranch , is a species of sacoglossan sea slug , a shell - less marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusk in the family Hermaeidae .
It was described by Rothschild in 1916 , and contains the single species Anaphleps angustipennis , which is found on Volcan Island .
Osedax japonicus is a species of bathypelagic polychaete tube worm that lives at great depths on the seabed and is able to sustain itself on the bones of a dead whale .
Saltoposuchus is an extinct genus of small ( 1 - 1.5 m and 10 - 15 kg ) , long - tailed crocodylomorph reptile ( Sphenosuchia ) , from the Norian ( Late Triassic ) of Europe .
Pristimantis citriogaster , sometimes known as the throated robber frog , is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
The primary species , Viridomys orbatus , is known from fossils found in Campanian ( Upper Cretaceous)-aged strata of the Upper Milk River Formation in Alberta , Canada .
Aethes argentilimitana , the silver - bordered aethes , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Tenuivirus is a plant virus genus , of which the type member is Rice stripe virus .
Tudorella sulcata is a species of land snail which has an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiidae .
Sophora chrysophylla , known as Māmane in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering plant in the pea and bean family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Penicillium glandicola is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces penitrem A , patulin , 2,4,6-trichloroanisole and roquefortine C
Senecio crassissimus is a species of the genus Senecio , family Asteraceae and endemic to Madagascar .
Yantaromyrmex is an extinct genus of ants first described in 2013 .
Hectopsyllidae is a small family of fleas , containing only the chigoe fleas and the sticktight fleas .
Acca lanuginosa is a species of shrub in the Myrtaceae family , related to feijoa .
Acetes is a genus of small , krill - like prawns .
Lomatium dissectum is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name fernleaf biscuitroot .
Crepis vesicaria is a European species of flowering plant in the daisy family with the common name beaked hawk's - beard .
Cystiscidae is a taxonomic family of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks .
Melapedalion breve , the Philippine snubnose halfbeak , is a species of halfbeak .
The Anchariidae are a family of catfishes containing two genera , Ancharius and Gogo with 6 species .
Gibbaeum heathii is a species of succulent plant in the Gibbaeum genus , endemic to South Africa .
Caymanabyssiidae is a family of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Lorius is a genus of lorikeet in the parrot family Psittaculidae .
Allium geyeri is a North American species of onion widespread in the western United States and in western Canada .
Hydrostachys imbricata is a species of aquatic flowering plant in the genus Hydrostachys .
Trillium gracile , common names Sabine River wakerobin , slender trillium or graceful trillium , is a plant species native to the region along the Sabine River in western Louisiana and eastern Texas .
Rhacophorus dorsoviridis ( green - back treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family that is found in northern Vietnam and southern China ( Yunnan ) .
Schiedea lydgatei is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Kamalo Gulch schiedea and Pacific schiedea .
Diguetia canities , commonly called the desert bush spider is a species of coneweb spider found in desert and semidesert habitats in the United States from California eastward to Oklahoma and Texas .
Brochiloricaria chauliodon is a species of armored catfish endemic to Argentina where it is found in the Rio de la Plata Basin .
Kabirmys is an extinct genus of anomaluroid ( scaly - tailed flying squirrel ) rodent from the earliest late Eocene of the Birket Qarun Formation from northern Egypt .
Masracetus ( from Arabic Masr , `` Egypt '' , and Greek ketos , `` whale '' ) is an extinct genus of basilosaurid ancient whale known from the Late Eocene ( Priabonian , 37.2 to 33.9 million years ago ) of Egypt .
Loxa is an insect genus in the large family of shield bugs .
Imperator luteocupreus is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae native to southern Europe , where it is found under chestnut ( Castanea ) .
Rhacophorus yinggelingensis ( Yinggeling treefrog ) is a species of frog in the family Rhacophoridae endemic to Hainan Island , China .
Colymbiculus is an extinct genus of loon found in Eocene Novopskov , Ukraine .
Ctenisolabis is a genus of earwigs in the subfamily Brachylabinae .
Ichthyophis pseudangularis is a species of caecilian endemic to Sri Lanka .
Olyra latifolia , carrycillo , is a grass species in the Poaceae family .
Sida fallax , known as yellow ' ilima , or in Hawaiian , ʻilima , is a species of herbaceous flowering plant in the Hibiscus family , Malvaceae , that occurs on some Pacific Islands .
Phascolosomatidea is a class of peanut worms containing two orders :
Lathyrus biflorus is a rare species of wild pea known by the common name twoflower pea .
Lithodora oleifolia , the olive - leaved gromwell ( syn . Lithospermum oleifolium ) , is a species of flowering plant in the family Boraginaceae .
Pleodendron macranthum ( chupacallos ) is a rare species of tree in the Canellaceae family .
Cerapachys elegans is an ant species in the genus Cerapachys found in Australia .
Palythoa is a genus of anthozoans in the order Zoantharia .
Mendoncia mollis is a plant species in the family Acanthaceae ( or according to some specialists in the family Mendonciaceae ) .
Eucrypta is a genus of flowering plants containing only two species .
Drymophila cyanocarpa , also known as Turquoise Berry or Native Solomon 's Seal , is a species of flowering plant in the family Alstroemeriaceae .
Curculigo orchioides ( commonly called golden eye - grass , xian mao , weevil - wort , black musli , Kali musli , or Kali Musali ) is a flowering plant species in the genus Curculigo .
Pachylaena is a genus of South American flowering plants in the gerbera tribe within the daisy family .
Banksia blechnifolia is a species of prostrate shrub in the plant genus Banksia .
Oceanosuchus is a genus of pholidosaurid mesoeucrocodylian , a type of marine crocodylomorph .
Gymnodoris ceylonica is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Gymnodorididae .
Dendrobium infundibulum , the Small - funnel - lipped Dendrobium , is a species of orchid .
Sagittaria australis , the Appalachian Arrowhead or longbeak arrowhead , is a plant species native to much of the eastern part of the United States , from Louisiana to Iowa to New York State to Florida , mostly between New Jersey and Mississippi with scattered locations elsewhere in the range .
Anisus vortex is a species of small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Baroa is a genus of oriental noctuoid moths in the Erebidae family , Arctiinae subfamily .
Pellasimnia brunneiterma is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ovulidae .
Grylloblatta barberi is a species of insect in the genus Grylloblatta .
Riccia atlantica is a species of liverwort in the Ricciaceae family .
Prunus nigra , the Canada plum , Canadian plum or black plum , is a species of Prunus , native to eastern North America from Nova Scotia west to Minnesota and southeastern Manitoba , and south as far as Connecticut , Illinois , and Iowa .
Nebria peristerica is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae family that can be found in Greece and Republic of Macedonia .
Architectonica perspectiva , common name the clear or perspective sundial shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Architectonicidae , which are known as the staircase shells or sundials .
The family contains the single genus Mycogelidium , which in turn contains the single species Mycogelidium sinense , found in China .
Imantodes gemmistratus is a snake species in the colubrid family , found from Mexico , through Central America and Colombia .
Sannantha similis is a flowering shrub or small tree species in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
Dicromantispa moronei is an extinct species of mantidfly in the neuropteran family Mantispidae known from a fossil found in the Caribbean .
Adesmiella cordipicta is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Adesmiella .
Schumacheria alnifolia is a species of plant in the Dilleniaceae family .
Theocolax elegans is a parasitic wasp species in the genus Theocolax .
Plectranthus , with some 350 species , is a genus of warm - climate plants occurring largely in the southern hemisphere , in sub - Saharan Africa , Madagascar , India and the Indonesian archipelago down to Australia and some Pacific Islands .
Fissurellidae , common name the keyhole limpets and slit limpets , is a taxonomic family of limpet - like sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Vetigastropoda .
Xoes egeria is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Xoes .
Clevosaurus ( CLEE - vo - SORE - us ) ( Gloucester lizard ) is an extinct genus of sphenodontian reptile from the Triassic and the Jurassic periods of Nova Scotia , Great Britain , ( C. bairdi ) and Yunnan ( C. mcgilli ) .
Patellidae is a taxonomic family of sea snails or true limpets , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Patellogastropoda .
Bifrenaria harrisoniae is a species of orchid native to Brazil .
Chabanaudia is a genus of central African lizard in the family Scincidae commonly known as skinks .
†Naricopsinidae was an extinct family of fossil operculate gastropod mollusks in the informal group Architaenioglossa .
The sole species is Haplocoelopsis africana .
Lecythium is a genus of testate amoebae within the Chlamydophryidae .
Himeroconcha quadrasi is a species of gastropod in the Charopidae family .
In comparing Europasaurus with Brachiosaurus , the former genus differs from the latter by having a shorter muzzle , a quadratojugal which makes contact with the squamosal , and an anteromedially flattened humerus possessing unaligned proximal and distal epiphyses .
Chicoreus brevifrons , common name the West Indian murex , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails .
Dexteria floridana was a species of fairy shrimp in the family Chirocephalidae , the only species in the genus Dexteria .
Brookesia ambreensis , also commonly known as the Amber Mountain leaf chameleon , is a species of chameleon endemic to Madagascar .
Cladanthus is a genus of plants in the family sunflower family , native to the Mediterranean region .
Templetonia stenophylla , commonly known as leafy templetonia , is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae .
Brodiaea filifolia , known by the common name threadleaf brodiaea , is a rare species of flowering plant in the cluster - lily genus .
Systomus jayarami is a species of cyprinid fish native to Manipur , India .
Wislizenia is a genus of flowering plants containing three recognized species native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Gracilinanus is a genus of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Russula paludosa is an edible species of mushroom within the large Russula genus .
Protocreopsis is a genus of fungi in the class Sordariomycetes .
Menoponidae is a monophyletic family of lice in the suborder / order of chewing lice , Mallophaga , often referred to as the chicken body louse family .
Menegazzia megalospora is a species of lichen from South America .
Salvia pratensis ( meadow clary or meadow sage ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to Europe , western Asia and northern Africa .
Hyperolius montanus ( common name : mountain reed frog or montane reed frog ) is a species of frog in the Hyperoliidae family .
Nogodinidae is a family of planthoppers .
Pterocalla guttulata is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Pterocalla of the family Ulidiidae .
Launaea sarmentosa is a perennial herb species in the family Asteraceae .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Lineostroma banksiae .
Populus balsamifera , commonly called balsam poplar , bam , bamtree , eastern balsam - poplar , hackmatack , tacamahac poplar , tacamahaca , is a tree species in the balsam poplar species group in the poplar genus , Populus .
Spathopsis wissmanni is a species of bivalve in the Mutelidae family .
Adilophontes is an extinct genus of large , mostly carnivorous bone - crushing mammals known as bear dogs , of the family Amphicyonidae , endemic to North America during the Oligocene to Miocene , living from 24.8 - -20.6 Ma and existed for approximately 4.2 million years .
Tenagodus cumingii is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Siliquariidae .
Dalbergia odorifera , or fragrant rosewood ( Chinese : 降香黄檀 ; pinyin : jiàngxiāng huángtán ; literally : `` drooping fragrant dalbergia '' ) , is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family .
Kosmoclymenia is a genus in the ammonoid order Clymeniida , in the family Kosmoclymeniidae .
Syrrhaptes is a genus of birds in the sandgrouse family .
Rhizocyon was similar to a contemporary species , Archaeocyon leptodus , from the Great Plains , but it shows a few subtle differences in the structure of the skull and dentition that indicate that Rhizocyon may be close to the ancestry of later borophagines .
Spirogyra ( common names include water silk , mermaid 's tressses , and blanket weed ) is a genus of filamentous charophyte green algae of the order Zygnematales , named for the helical or spiral arrangement of the chloroplasts that is diagnostic of the genus .
Serratia symbiotica is a species of bacteria that lives as a symbiont of aphids .
Nebria acuta is a species of black coloured ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Canada and United States , in states like Alaska , California , Oregon , and Washington .
Crellidae is a family of marine demosponges in the order Poecilosclerida .
Buddleja ramboi is a very rare Brazilian species found only infrequently in the shrubby or grassy fields of Santa Catarina and Rio Grande do Sul .
Blue Mist , ( Memecylon angustifolium ) , is a species of plant in the Melastomataceae family .
The Galápagos land iguanas comprise the genus Conolophus of the Galápagos Islands .
Gulella taitensis is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .
Neopaschia flavociliata is a species of snout moth in the genus Neopaschia .
Ambrosia tomentosa , the skeletonleaf bur ragweed , silverleaf povertyweed , or skeleton - leaf bursage , is a North American species of perennial plants in the ( aster family ) .
Chilobrachys guangxiensis ( known as the `` Chinese fawn tarantula '' ) is a species of tarantula native to Southern China , in Hainan .
Phyllocephalum is a genus of Asian flowering plants in the evil tribe within the sunflower family .
Bhutanitis thaidina , commonly known as the Chinese Three - tailed Swallowtail , is a rare species of butterfly in the family Papilionidae .
Juglans venezuelensis , or Nogal de Caracas , is a species of black walnut endemic to Venezuela .
Menon 's caecilian , Uraeotyphlus menoni , is a species of caecilian found in the Western Ghats of India .
Belonogaster juncea juncea is a subspecies of Belonogaster juncea and is classified as a primitively eusocial wasp , meaning that the species is social while exhibiting a morphology that is indistinguishable from that of other castes .
Omnivoropteryx ( meaning `` omnivorous wing '' ) is a genus of primitive flying bird from the early Cretaceous Upper Jiufotang Formation of China .
Pseudochazara turkestana ( Grum - Grshimailo , 1893 ) is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
The Sichuan deer ( Cervus canadensis macneilli ) also known as MacNeill 's deer is a subspecies of Wapiti native to Western China .
Tubeufia is a genus in the Tubeufiaceae family of fungi .
It contains a single species , Kazaklambia convincens .
Descolea is a genus of fungi in the family Bolbitiaceae .
Basiphyllaea corallicola is a species of orchid native to Florida , Bahamas , Cuba , Hispaniola , and Puerto Rico .
Artemisia carruthii , common name Carruth 's sagewort or Carruth wormwood , is a North American species of shrubs in the daisy family native to much of south - central and southwestern United States ( Nevada , Arizona , New Mexico , Utah , Colorado , Kansas , Oklahoma , northern + western Texas ) .
Felimida marislae is a species of colorful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chromodorididae .
Dioryctria disclusa , the webbing coneworm or rusty pine cone moth , is a species of moth of the family Pyralidae .
Exyrias akihito is a species of marine goby .
The Atlantic cod is one of three cod species in the genus Gadus along with Pacific cod and Greenland cod . A variety of fish species are colloquially known as cod though they are not strictly classified within the Gadus genus , though some are in the Atlantic cod family , Gadidae .
Guavina is a genus of sleeper gobies native to fresh , marine , and brackish waters of the Pacific and Atlantic coasts of the Americas .
Bullockia maldonadoi is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Trichomycteridae , and the only species of the genus Bullockia .
Ambedus is an extinct genus of diadectid reptiliomorph .
Acanthocephala declivis is a species of North American true bugs with a range from the southern United States to Guatemala and some Caribbean islands .
Idiosepius picteti is a species of bobtail squid native to the Indo - Pacific waters off eastern Indonesia .
Erika Köth ( September 15 , 1925 , Darmstadt - February 21 , 1989 , Speyer ) was a German operatic high coloratura soprano , particularly associated with the roles of Zerbinetta and Zerlina .
Judith Bettina is an American soprano particularly noted for her performances of contemporary classical music .
Janice Felty is an American operatic mezzo - soprano .
Pietro Ballo ( born October 2 , 1952 in Palermo ) , is an Italian operatic tenor singer .
Dame Eva Turner DBE ( 10 March 1892 - 16 June 1990 ) was an English dramatic soprano with an international reputation .
Geeta Novotny ( born Geeta Bhatnagar ) is an American mezzo - soprano , actor , published writer and columnist .
Stafford Dean ( born 20 June 1937 ) is a British bass opera singer .
Renato Capecchi ( born Cairo , November 6 , 1923 ; died Milan , June 30 , 1998 ) was an Italian baritone , actor , and opera director .
Irena Troupová ( Irena Troupova - Wilke ) is a Czech soprano and early music specialist .
Alaine Rodin is an American operatic soprano who has sung leading roles both in the United States and internationally .
Gunthild Weber ( 1909 -- ? ) is a German soprano , a concert singer who recorded Bach cantatas and his Mass in B minor with Fritz Lehmann .
Marie Wilt ( also Maria Vilda and Marie Liebenthaler ) ( 30 January 1833 -- 24 September 1891 ) was an Austrian dramatic coloratura soprano .
Giorgio Zancanaro ( born 9 May 1939 ) is an Italian baritone , particularly associated with the Italian repertory , especially Verdi .
Lucia Elizabeth Vestris ( January 1797 -- 8 August 1856 ) was an English actress and a contralto opera singer , appearing in works by Mozart and Rossini .
Jeanne Gerville - Réache ( 26 March 1882 -- 5 January 1915 ) was a French operatic contralto from the Belle Époque .
Marco Lazzara ( born 1962 ) is an Italian countertenor who sings a wide - ranging repertoire from baroque composers to those of the 20th century and has performed in a number of notable premieres and revivals of rarely performed operas .
Isabel Rey ( born in Valencia ) is a Spanish operatic soprano who has performed leading roles in the opera houses of Europe and appears on many recordings .
Edita Adlerová ( born 27 August 1971 ) is a Czech classical mezzo - soprano who has been active in operas , concerts , and recitals since the early 1990s .
Carlos Mena ( born 1971 , Vitoria - Gasteiz ) is a Spanish countertenor .
Deborah Riedel ( 31 July 1958 -- 8 January 2009 ) was an Australian operatic soprano .
Jami Rogers - Anderson ( born September 2 , 1970 ) is an American soprano opera singer .
Robert Rounseville ( 25 March 1914 -- 6 August 1974 ) was an American tenor , who appeared in opera , operetta , and Broadway musicals .
Natalia Rom , soprano , was born in Kazan , in the Soviet Union ( also the city of Feodor Chaliapin 's birth ) , on May 14 , 1950 , and graduated ( as a conductor ) from the Leningrad Conservatory .
Maria Callas , Commendatore OMRI ( Greek : Μαρία Κάλλας ; December 2 , 1923 -- September 16 , 1977 ) , was a Greek - American soprano , and one of the most renowned and influential opera singers of the 20th century .
Gustave Garcia ( February 1 , 1837 -- June 12 , 1925 ) was an Italian baritone opera singer and singing teacher .
Peter Hofmann ( 22 August 1944 -- 30 November 2010 ) was a German tenor who had a successful performance career within the fields of opera , rock , pop , and musical theatre .
Antonietta Marini - Rainieri was an Italian operatic soprano active during the first half of the 19th century .
Alan Opie OBE ( born 22 March 1945 , Redruth ) is a Cornish baritone , primarily known as an opera singer .
Barry Morell ( March 30 , 1927 -- December 4 , 2003 ) was an American operatic tenor , particularly associated with the Italian and French repertoire .
